Product: Knixmax Women Men Memory Foam Insoles Comfort Shoe Inserts Shock Absorption Cushioning Foot Support Pads Inner Soles for Trainers Boots Wellies
Review: I have severe scar tissue that resulted from Morton’s Neuroma surgery that I had on both feet in 2014. Two years later, I had a revision on the right foot which increased the scar tissue problem even more. I went to PT twice a week for a year which helped reduce nodules and the pain of the scar tissue, however, I have struggled since to find comfortable shoes and to figure out how to reduce the pain of the scar tissue that I feel with EVERY SINGLE step. I now have custom 3/4 orthotics that I put in my shoes over these inserts. These are the best inserts that I’ve found so far because they provide a firm, but cushioned support for my feet. The more support, the less I feel the scar tissue. I’ve ordered several pairs and am thankful for some relief!!

Product: Knixmax Women Men Memory Foam Insoles Comfort Shoe Inserts Shock Absorption Cushioning Foot Support Pads Inner Soles for Trainers Boots Wellies
Review: I bought these to replace the insoles in my slippers. One side had a really rough texture which I assumed was intended to go on the bottom to prevent sliding. The otherside has slightly slippery texture. The foam doesn't reach all the way to the edge which I found rather annoying, and uncomfortable since my flat feet don't conform to the standard foot shape. I ended up turning them upside-down (rough side up) and putting the left in the right, and the right in the left, before putting my old flattened out insoles back on top. Made the slippers a bit snug, but much more comfortable for me this way.UPDATE: a little over two weeks and these have gone completely flat and no longer provide any cushion. Keep looking folks, these aren't worth it.

Product: Knixmax Women Men Memory Foam Insoles Comfort Shoe Inserts Shock Absorption Cushioning Foot Support Pads Inner Soles for Trainers Boots Wellies
Review: These inserts flattened out after I wore them for 1 day, although they were very thin to start with.  The imprint of my feet stayed in them and they never bounced back as memory foam should.  The bottom of the inserts seems to be made of cardboard and they are very firm, even after they warm up.  I am a long distance runner and after 1 use on my treadmill my feet felt like they had run on stone.  Memory foam should be thick and soft, yet supportive.  It should refill the impressions after you remove the shoes so they are thick and soft again for the next day.  Such a disappointment.

Product: Knixmax Women Men Memory Foam Insoles Comfort Shoe Inserts Shock Absorption Cushioning Foot Support Pads Inner Soles for Trainers Boots Wellies
Review: Fantastic! I have plantar fasciitis on both feet, I need all the memory foam I can get. True to size. I am 5.5 shoe size, I put these in my walking shoe when the insole flattens out a bit or I simply don't like it. The size 5 fits a 5.5 perfectly. I put these insoles in everything from wellies to slippers. You will love these insoles, I promise.

Product: Havaianas Unisex's Top Flip Flops
Review:
This is the third pair which have broken. Each of them have lasted three to four months with infrequent use. The straps break away at some point, rendering them unusable. Havaianas, as they describe their product, are “Comfortable, durable, lightweight, heat-resistant, non-slip and water-resistant”.

Comfort - for the first three hours, these using these can feel like the straps are cutting into your skin. They are almost sharp. After that, they do become more comfortable.

Durable - laughable, as I’ve gone through three pairs in under a year.

Lightweight - that’s relative, though. They are about the same weight as most other major brands.

Heat resistant - they soak up the heat when left in the sun, and the tread pattern on the bottom melts away at about 35 celcius.

Non slip - for about ten hours of use, this is accurate. After that, they lose all grip between your foot and the top, and after about thirty hours, the tread has worn away.

Water resistant - the only claim that’s true. Salt water is different. Exposure to salt seems to make the material wear away at a much faster rate.

I cannot recommend these.

Product: Havaianas Unisex's Top Flip Flops
Review: I have been looking for some slim black Havianas for some time now but didn’t want to pay over £20 for a pair of flip flops. These are a bit chunkier than expected and the toe separator does rub. They are, however, very comfy and bouncy, they look good. I’m a size 5 which they didn’t have so bought a 4-5 and they just about fit without my toes dangling over the edge so I would so true to size while possibly being just a tad too small.

Product: Havaianas Unisex's Top Flip Flops
Review: I was searching hi quality flip flops and due internet research those seems one of the best on market.After two weeks of normal use they loose completely and it was hard to control them during walk. Now they're in garbage.DON'T BUY THEM!

Product: Havaianas Unisex's Top Flip Flops
Review:
I am extremely disappointed with this purchase. The ‘V’ of the strap (which sits on the top of the foot) Does not sit flat, causing a point which digs in to the top of my foot and has bruised both tops of my feet and are very sore. The moulding of the straps seems a little off and the positioning misplaced. After a couple of days of preserving, I have come to the conclusion that I will have to give up!

I have bought and worn Havaianas for many years and have never had this issue. All previous purchases have been instantly comfortable and incredibly durable.

Just wish I hadn’t worn them outside in my efforts to ‘wear them in’ as now I can’t send them back.

Product: Crocs Classic Marbled Clog
Review:
I bought the first pair of crocs I ever owned a little over five months ago, and I wear them nearly every day. During the summer, I wear them when I go out, and in the garden, and when it starts getting wet outside, I wear them daily in the house. They're very comfortable, and easy to just slip on when you don't want to walk barefoot, like when you have to go outside for a moment.

I can also walk through the store in them, and they're easy on my feet.

I'll be buying another pair, probably in an "awful" bright color, just to further stick it to the haters.

Product: Crocs Classic Marbled Clog
Review: Not as comfy as my original crocks from many years back.  I have a wide foot and just my pinky toe is too snug against the top of the shoe.  States relaxed fit or something similar on packaging, but not quite as relaxed/ loose fit as the originals.  However these are more loose fit than the crocks I have bought from another seller on Amazon, which were also a different style than these.  These crocks are also a size up from the originals from years back.  They are proportionately a bit longer, but not wider. I think they would be better with arch support, like some styles of crocks, although my arches do not get sore.Also, these seem a bit firmer than my old ones.

Product: Crocs Classic Marbled Clog
Review: I love how comfortable these crocs fit, reason why i choose low stars is because of how they sweak when i walk that is very very annoying, i hardly wear them because of that. Don't wear these crocs in the rain after i was caught in the rain is when my crocs started to sweak.

Review: These were perfect for my 12 year old brother. He wanted something to slip on and off and these worked great. Unfortunately they already wore out and the band broke off after just a month and a half. They weren’t worn every day or with rough use either which was just disappointing.

Product: Zone - Kids Navy and Lime Welly Boot Kids Size 8 to13
Review: Bought for my son who is always outside on the farm and goes through wellies at a rate of knots! He loves these as they are higher up the leg than some and simply constructed in terms of minimal lining, meaning they dry out quicker when he’s been in the river! When they get stinky I simply swill out with a mild detergent solution and hang upside down on the airer. Quite a firm construction on the sole so good for uneven ground and a good tread. We’ve gone through many, much more expensive brands in the past and so far these are proving to be better.

Product: Zone - Kids Navy and Lime Welly Boot Kids Size 8 to13

Product: HKR Women Trainers Athletic Running Shoes Sport Walking Sneakers Lightweight Tennis Shoes
Review:
These Trainers are cheaply made in my opinion.
In fact I could see the dried on glue around the edges. They are my size but very uncomfortable, stiff material that dug into my ankles when walking.
Worst of all though was the trail of thick dirty black marks on my carpet and kitchen floor with each foot-step as I was walking around the house in them. I was horrified - I have never seen anything like it.
Unfortunately these trainers are so disgusting they went straight into the dust bin.
I would not even donate these trainers to a charity shop.
I gave one star as no other option below one star. The only good thing was they arrived swiftly.

Product: HKR Women Trainers Athletic Running Shoes Sport Walking Sneakers Lightweight Tennis Shoes
Review: I ordered UK size 7 which I normally do because my foot is EU size 40. The shoes were too big so I ordered UK size 6 which apparently corresponds with EU 40. They fit perfectly. The laces are mainly decorative so you don’t need to worry about them, just put the shoes on and go!

Product: HKR Women Trainers Athletic Running Shoes Sport Walking Sneakers Lightweight Tennis Shoes
Review: Fitted perfectly at first so thought I would wear them to the park directly behind our house before going running in them the next morning. Product: Scholl Women’S Gel Activ Work Insoles UK Size 3.5-7.5
Review: I rarely write reviews, but I had to write this one to warn people. This is THE WORST pair of soles you can buy for your shoes. I work 12 hour shifts and I need comfortable soles. These are not comfortable at all. In the opposite, it felt like there was nothing between my feet and the shoes. Also my feet were getting so incredibly sweaty that they started to peel off really bad. Believe it or not, once Primark opened up I bought new soles of the price of £1, my feet feel comfy, and no more creazy sweat.

Product: Scholl Women’S Gel Activ Work Insoles UK Size 3.5-7.5
Review: I bought boots in Deichmann shoes. Never again. I swear. First day I felt like my feet are hurting but I thought it's new shoes, leather, it will be be ok, just need to wear them for bit... Second day was worst. Third day I went home limping. It was soils. Seriously hurting my feet, especially heels, that soft spot in the middle of foot where hill starts. I bought ordinary soils from clarks. Good. Cheep. But after 2-3 weeks it started to crumbling and when I removed my boots it left white bits on my socks. So I bought new pair of soils. Same again. This was my last resort before throwing boots to bin or set them on fire. I was wearing them all day long for weeks and nothing. My feet stopped hurting. My heels healed. Very comfy. Bit pricey. Not going to lie. But it was definitely worth it.

Product: Scholl Women’S Gel Activ Work Insoles UK Size 3.5-7.5
Review: I bought these as my new work trainers were hurting my heels. I work very long hours stood on my feet all day running a dog grooming salon. I used these and they did fix the problem with my heels but I’ve had to stop using them immediately as the arch of both of my feet are killing me! It’s incredibly painful and they’ve swelled up and gone all red. I had to keep taking them off at work and having breaks as I couldn’t stand any longer in them, I even swapped shoes with someone as I was in that much pain!! I’ve tried moving the insole to each side to see if that helps and nothing at all came of that. Not good at all so if you ask me I wouldn’t recommend. Will have to find some others I guess. Just a shame I spent so much on these after the great reviews and the brand.

Product: Scholl Women’S Gel Activ Work Insoles UK Size 3.5-7.5
Review: So comfy. Brilliant for being on feet all day. Great value. Used in a pair of Converse as often find they're very flat and become uncomfortable after long periods, these worked wonders! No more aching calves!

Product: Scholl Women’S Gel Activ Work Insoles UK Size 3.5-7.5
Review: These have made my smart work boots so much conifer after the inside soles started to wear through, I've ordered another pair so I don't have to keep swapping them to other shoes

Product: Scholl Women’S Gel Activ Work Insoles UK Size 3.5-7.5
Review: Wore these on a 13 hour hospital shift and honestly there's no difference. My feet still hurt the same as without them and on one foot it's dug into me and hurts like hell. It's also made my foot swollen and I have to go and work another 13 hour shift tomorrow!! wouldn't recommend. They are not comfortable at all and not worth £8.

Product: Scholl Women’S Gel Activ Work Insoles UK Size 3.5-7.5
Review: I have had these for a little over two weeks now and I can tell you they are not made for those who are on their feet all day! This product has little grooves on the heal (the oval part around the word scholl) and you can feel every last groove on your heal! By the end of the day I’m tip toeing because I’m in so much pain with my heals! Do not recommend to anyone!

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: There is central zone on these inserts and thin sealed edge.  While the centre may have the memory foam in it's not very supportive at all.  After walking a few hundred meters they were worn out and provided no comfort at all, leaving me hobbling along in agony until I could find somewhere I could get my shoes off.  I suspect I'd have been better in bare feet than using these things.Not even as good as useless.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: I can only assume the other reviews are fraudulent. This item arrived today. The foam is indeed soft but the sizing is not for the foam part, it is for the hard plastic outer. The inside part is around a size smaller, giving the impression of walking on a beam narrower than your foot. In addition, somehow buying these using the one click feature selected 'express delivery' despite the item being prime and labelled as free next day delivery. Thrown the lot in the bin, absolute cheap tat, avoid

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: At first, having had to cut them down to fit, they felt great in the hard-soled slippers I'd bought a matter of weeks before. As I am at home all day, I wear those slippers for hours on end, and had been surprised when the fitted insole in them thinned to the point of uselessness, leaving the hard plastic waffle-patterned heel digging into my feet. Buying thick, plush insoles seemed like a good solution, providing a good layer of cushioning for less money than a new pair of slippers. I wore them for a couple of hours, and all was well. The next day, I realised there was a soreness in my heels again, despite the insoles being apparently about as thick as before - was it that I was on my feet more, and so getting a more accurate sense of the product? On the third day, I wore them without socks, and after a while got the uncomfortable itching I usually get when exposed to latex. Checking the order, I confirmed that latex wasn't mentioned, so either they're not mentioning a common allergen, or the insoles are made of something else that causes the same irritation.It's frustrating.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: Really like these insoles, I’m on my second pair!. Nice thickness and a great fit, no trimming at all. Wondered on the first pair how they would last. I’m using them in work boots 10-12 hours a day and they are great!. First pair I bought last November and have worn them out!. That’s where the 4 stars comes in........they literally wore through!, two on the ball of my foot and one on the heel. Daft thing is I didn’t really notice until I felt the holes.... I must have been wearing them with the holes for weeks🤣. No hesitation in buying a second pair......I know they will only last a few months but they turned a pair of work boots into a nice comfy pair of shoes and got that I am grateful!. You will love these but they won’t last but they should leave you wanting to get another pair. Mine are for long hours at work so have been working overtime in the scheme of things. Will be getting another pair before Xmas for sure!.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: I had some of these made for me for my fallen arches by the Podiaatry clinic which were nice but they were bulky in certain shoes/boots so i could not always wear them and then you get in the habit of not always wearing them so i chanced upon these whilst looking for something completely different, i read the reviews and thought i'd give these a try. Wow i'm glad i did i first tried them in a pair of boots that were slightly roomy and they fitted perfectly and the feeling of your arches being risen again was great, i took the dog for a walk and my feet felt great you could almost feel your arches being massarged whilst walking and it felt great. I have tried in other boots and they fit perfectly which is greati haven't tried in shoes yet but i think they should fit perfectly just as with my boots. For the price these are great memory inserts that are just as good as my pair that were made for my fallen arches, would recommend.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review:
I bought these to put in my fishing waders.
After always buying the "cut to size" type of insoles in the past but never being really happy with the fit & comfort of them i decided to try these.
Have to say they are the comfiest insoles i've tried.
Because they're a "tailored" shoe size they don't slid about or scrunge up in my waders.
Normally after a beach fishing session my feet are sore with constantly walking over pebbles, stones & hard ridges of sand but after several fishing trips with these in my waders & hours at a time of wading up & down the beach- no sore feet!
Big thumbs up from me & will definitely buy again

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: My first review needs editing as these inserts have failed after light usage over a short period of time. See photo. Only buy if you need a cheap low quality solution. This was my original review...  Here is one of those cheap products that shouldn't be good but actually is! I put these in my sturdy but uncomfortable dog walking shoes. What a transformation! They took a few miles to bed in but after that they became wonderful. Good product.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review:
I bought these to fit in my Hunter boots and the first time I slotted them in, they fitted absolutely PERFECT. I was made up because Hunter do there own insoles and they would have cost more than double the price.

As I had another pair, I took one insole out and tried it with the other boots and the fit was great. They are very comfortable and wedge my foot inside the boot very well. So I slotted that insole back into my first boots and couldn't wait to give them a test run on my dog walk.

I was planning on giving these insoles a 5 star rating, however. On the day I tested my insoles, one insole felt like it was sliding away from my boot. Surprisingly, it was the insole I took out try with my other boots. I took off my boot and slotted the insole back in. However after a few minutes of walking, the same thing happened again. By the time I got back home, I had to stop at least 4 times to re slot my insole. I couldn't keep doing this every time I take the dog for a walk.

However I decided not to give up on my insoles and tried different ways of keeping them slotted. I used sport socks on my test walk and tried adding more layers to my feet. It didn't stop the slipping unfortunately. I considered Velcro and double sided tape, however I wouldn't have been able to wash in insoles and it could damage my Hunter boots.

Then I realised I had some Blue Tack and I stuck a thick rounded chunk to the underside of the offending insole and tacked it into my boot. I wore an extra socks on the foot and it seemed to have done the trick. Overtime the Blue Tack has actually moulded to my foot shape and the support of the insole has made the boot feel comfortable again. The best bit of course is the Blue Tack would come out easily enough when I come to wash the insole/move them into the other boots (Without damaging them as well) and I can just reform the putty and place it back onto the insoles.

I am happy with my purchase overall and I can now look forward to wearing my boots with comfort and security of course.

Review: Before I bought these I saw some reviews complaining too thick, and others too thin. It's really both. The foam feels a bit too thick and hard at first, but like most foam it softens with the pressure and heat of your foot, and eventually I found that it was a little too thin after several hours of use. I normally wear more expensive gel inserts in my shoes so these were a lot cheaper. I think they do a reasonable job at their price point and are good for light duty use, but I would not recommend them for the on your feet all day person.  The one thing I especially did like was that they came perfectly sized, no cutting and shaping. Out of the bag and into the shoe.

Review: I have neuropathy in my feet, so they hurt all the time.  However, with these inserts, they hurt less.  I bought several pair and use them in place of original liners in my shoes; actually, mostly boots.  My boots are a half-size bigger than shoes as I usually wear thicker socks.  However, I would advise that these inserts take up about a half-size in the shoe.  They are fine in my boots, but for shoes/sneakers that are a half-size smaller than my boots, these don’t give my feet enough room.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: I replaced the inner lining of my Ugg slippers with these, I've had the slippers for over ten years, they dont look brand new but the feel brand new. I used Gorrilla glue to do this and got glue on the heal of the liner when I did it. :(EDIT: These actually suck, they have lost all memory they are flat and not comfortable after 2 months2nd edit. These guys contacted me and sent me a new pair right away after my 1st edit which is pretty cool in itself, they definitely have great customer service. I'm going to pop these in my work shoes, maybe the first pair were bunk.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: I you would like some soft padding for your shoe or boot, rather than a high tech conglomeration of rubbery arch support, special areas for heel, ball of foot, etc. these memory foam pads are for you. I have flat feet and don't tolerate a sculpted insole, unless it has softness and some rebound. These do this without being thick, a rare trick.They are are well made and similar to expensive insoles--but if you want or need to change your insole every 6months or so, why spend the money? Mine get heavy use because I walk in well worn Born chelsea boots everyday and have worn out my original insoles. Same as the Born insole, these are not hard or stiff and fit nicely into my boots.If you have very pointed shoes these probably would not work. They are also true to size and washable.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review:
Most comfort shoe inserts come with something to keep them in place -- little gel spots or a few inches of double-sided tape. Not these! Which means they'll scooch around as you walk unless you add something to control that movement,

The comfort is only so-so, but I prefer this over a foam or plastic molded piece (like awful Dr Scholl's products).

The major failing of Memory Foam in shoe inserts is that the foam moves AWAY from the parts that need the padding most. But I was hoping it'd be thick enough for comfort. Ultimately, it's better than other similar pads and worse than others.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: I expected a little more. Ordered two pairs and when they arrived I noticed one of the packages was opened and the insoles were dirty. Apparently a return from someone else. So I opened the other package and tried them. They are very narrow and offer no support as they are just flat, no arch support.Spend a little more on some of the others listed.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: When I first opened the package I didn’t think it would be as comfortable as they turned out to be. The first time I wore them I thought I had wasted my money again. After the second time I thought “Hmmm, not bad”. The more I wore them the better they felt. What’s really great is they don’t take a lot of shoe room, they don’t flatten with repeated wear, I find they make my shoes comfortable to wear, and I didn’t have to trim them. I have arthritic feet and these worked for me. In addition, I rarely go bare footed in shoes because I don’t like the feeling but tried going bare footed in some shoes that had these inserts. My feet didn’t feel icky so I like them.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: These are hard and do not offer any additional comfort. They're like hard, plastic inserts that'll just make your shoe fit more tight. So if that's what you need, these would work. But they definitely do not add one ounce of comfort. I do really like the fact that they're cut to size. I just wish they were made with better materials.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: I bought a few of these to put into different pairs of boots for a two week walking trip vacation.  At no point did I feel they were uncomfortable, and at the end of the day my feet were in great shape still.  I have bought more of these for everyday use, and put a pair into my sketchers that were old and breaking down. This is a great product - much better than anything I've been able to find in brick and mortar stores.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: Exact fit for puma Enzo or any puma using cloudfoam insoles... this product revived my old shoes! I will order more for sure...just make sure your measure your old insoles preferably in “cm” and cross reference the respective US size by their sizing table (triple check)  Note: everything you order is in a US size!

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: The outside edge of these insoles fit my shoes perfectly. However, the actual foam part starts tapering off half an inch away from that edge, leaving my toes feeling like they are in a ditch. This causes me to compensate due to the lack of proper support, which ends up making my foot hurt within a few minutes. Returning.

Product: riemot Memory Foam Insoles for Men and Women,Replacement Shoe Inserts for Sports Shoes,Trainers,Sneakers,Work Boots and Walking Shoes,Comfort,Cushioning
Review: Bought a pair of Vionic slippers that were a bit big. I needed the arch support in the insole, but for slippers they just weren't cushion-ey enough. Review: I had some wear on the heal inside my favorite golf shoes so I bought these insole because they looked flat. I purchased size 11 for size 11 shoes and they fit perfectly...no movement. They provided just a little cushion. That’s what I was looking for

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review: Bought these for my son who has autism and adhd to make it easier for him to not have to have someone constantly tie his shoes when they come undone. I thought it was my son who kept pulling the laces out of the holes but learned from his teachers that it was the rubber lace kept coming out on their own. My son also complained of them saying the shoes were too tight which they were a bit snug. And he does well with deep pressure so this was kind of an odd complaint for him. I had to put his old laces back in the shoes fir him to consider even wearing the shoes again since he associated it with the pain from the tightness. Not sure if this brand was just a cheaper off brand or what. Not sure I would recommend this brand to another parent. Was disappointed cuz I was going to try the adult ones next but not after his issues with them. Waste of money at this point.

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review: Looked for some laces that wouldn’t soak up whatever fluids may be splashed at my shoes and these rubber laces do the job. Now my shoes are completely waterproof and wipeable. Chose bright orange because it doesn’t hurt to show a little individuality.They come with a lot of “laces” and I found the middle sizes worked best with my narrow fit size 10 UK shoes. Getting them in to the eyelets was a bit annoying but they stay there. Wouldn’t work on shoes with larger eyelets or the loop/wing eyelets.

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review:
These are awsome.
The laces came and i was very suprised as to how secure they are.
My son can tie his shoe laces but is lacking in the tighning of them so i thought as he is going on a residential with school in a few months this will be the nest thing for him to simply slip on his shoes so he is not worrying about his laces coming un-done.
They are great in colour snd are very strong interms of fabric.
I cannot thabk you enough for the confidence it gives my son now to not worry about a simple little problem and they look so cool
Will defo beordering a few more pairs so all his shoes are wearing them.

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review: These are really good. I call them 'lazy laces'! Easily pull on and pull off trainers without having to deal with fiddly laces.This is the 2nd order I've made. I'm not sure if they are designed to be taken off and put on new trainers. By doing that the end piece that holds then in place broke. I will buy these again when I buy new trainers.

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review: I purchased these for a walking trip last year and since then have purchased more for myself and for others as gifts.They're so handy, I haven't had to bend down to retie laces in a year.Putting shoes on / taking them off takes a split second now. I know it's not exactly much change, but once you don't have to tie laces anymore you feel really smug whenever someone you're with has to retie theirs.

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review: A friend introduced me to the concept and what a game changer these things are. In the process of switching out laces from my life and replacing with these. Can’t believe I’ve only just discovered them.So far I have used them on a pair of white arigato trainers and they complement really well as well as the grey ones on a pair of undandy sneakers, again fits and looks good

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review:

Look really good, give a good amount of tightness, although these shoes are sock like - I would definitely recommend them for this type of shoe.

Only one 'lace' has snapped but these shoes are used 9 hours a day 5 days a week.

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review: I bought these for my wife’s child sized trainers. The differently sized ‘laces’ made little sense to me when I first saw them and even less sense when fitting them. They didn’t work at all for us and when removing them one broke. They went in the bin and it all felt very wasteful.

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review: The smallest couple of sizes would only fit a toddlers shoe.  Not enough of the right size for adult shoes.  You'll need two packs per shoe.  Too much difference in length between sizes.  Good quality and looks great but get two packs.

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces
Review: I have joint problems and have found these laces have given me a bit of independence back. On receipt I was concerned they may make the shoes feel loose but I was totally wrong. I am using them with high tops and am a size 8 and have had no problems so far! The only comment I will make is the shoes i have put them in did not have metal eyelets just holes punched into the leather, this made it a bit of a pain to get the ends through and I did break the end of one of them. Overall exactly what i wanted and I'll definitely be buying more!

Product: INMAKER No Tie Laces for Kids and Adults, Silicone Flat Shoe Laces for Trainer, Elastic Waterproof Tieless Running Shoe Laces

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review:
Bought the 'mesh' variant for cycling and knocking around at the weekend.

Brought one pair earlier in the year (my usual size 9) but the were a bit tight and my toes were touching the end. Gave those to a relative and bought myself a size 10 - much better fit, perhaps a fraction too large, but ok.

The first pair needed some superglue as part of the lower edge of the sole peeled away. It was fine after that.

For the price they're fine. Very light and don't need breaking in. No branding/logos on them which I prefer. They look nice too.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review:
I was looking for a pair of cheap trainers to skip with indoors. I came across these and bought them. However due to my fitness level being so low I started running instead, I've now been running in these 3 times a week for 3 & 1/2 months. Started off few hundred meters per run and now clocking in 8km each run so they have seem some use.

The positives:
- The price
They are cheap, the quality was a bit better than I expected. Also means not to bothered about them.

- Light.

- Sturdy
More hard wearing than I expected. After 3 months use only the inner lining of the soles has started to slip but this is easily addressable.

Negatives:
- Cheap,
The formation of the sole feels a slightly weird shape on my feet. More curved on the flat and tighter around the middle than expected.

- Not breathable
As others have said they will make your feet sweat and soak your socks if you are working out in them.

- Not waterproof
If you are running in the rain or after it has rained then your are going to get wet feet.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review:
Best thing I can say is; I bought these in orange, then bought another two pair. (Yellow, and blue)
I love them, but... they aren't built for joggers/runners.
The first pair I bought lasted 15 miles before the heel wore away, but Amazon being Zon accepted them for a full refund, no problem, then I bought another pair to replace them.
They're very comfortable, look good, and the price is excellent.
I have no problem recommending these to anyone, just as long as you don't intend to jog. ;-)

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: They don't last all that long. I wear mine every day and they usually wear through the sole in the vicinity of the ball of my foot in about 3 or 4 months (I always just buy them again, as I said they're so cheap its worth it). Comfortable enough, especially if you get the version with the memory foam insole. Those are a little tighter though so you may consider going a half size up. Overall I'd say value for money is 10/10

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: For the price these are excellent - this is the third pair I’ve ordered for him indoors. He wears them daily and one pair lasts for around a year to a year and a half before any major disintegration. From an environmental point of view it could be better, but it could also be far worse since many cheap shoes I’ve bought over the years have survived a mere handful of wears before literally falling to bits. I’ve attached a picture of the last very tatty and abused pair which are still intact after a year and three months’ usage and will now be relegated to lawn-mowing attire. (Note the laces aren’t original - these are the stretchy laces which mean you don’t have to do the laces up - the height of laziness and convenience!)

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: I had intended to wear this product upon my feet. Full disclosure, I am very hard wearing on shoes due to walking many miles each day and I do not expect a cheap shoe to last me more than about three months. This shoe arrived promptly and looked beautiful. From 08.00 to 11.00 I wore it around the house and it proved adequate. Unfortunately at 11.00 I walked approximately 3 miles on various pavements. This was too much for the poor shoe and by 12.00 the sole of the right shoe was hanging off. Product duly returned. I shall listen more in future to the reviewers before me who said it was flimsy.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: I got these for running with and they are comfortable enough but feel cheap on my feet.  They also let in water really easily so not waterproof at all.  Since i do dirt track running the soles are thick and bouncy enough that I dont feel the stones.  Overall they are ok running trainers but maybe best investing a little more in ones that are water resistant especially if using outdoors.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: I have tried many makes of low priced trainers - most if which have been discarded within days.Have to say these are a bit snug. As  'size 10', I expected  to have to put a liner in them but now I see that are continental 44 which 9.5 UK nominally is my fitThey feel quite substantial and I think that they will give me good support.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: Bought for my 12yr old son for PE. After losing a pair of trainers recently, I decided to not spend a fortune on a branded pair of trainers. He’s a UK 8 so into adult sizes and prices! I bought all black with black sole, they are inconspicuous so he doesn’t mind that they are not branded at all. He’s happy with them and says they were comfortable straight away. Would buy again while I can get away with spending less on something he wears for 2 hours a week!

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: I'm size 10 and ordering size 10 they are almost on the borderline of feeling a little too small.I've been out on daily walks for about 1.5 hours per day and after wearing them for just four days the sole grip pattern is very noticeably reduced. At the rate that the pattern seems to be going down they are going to be worn out after 3 weeks.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: Love these trainers very, very lightweight which I find so comfortable they fit me superbly, ok the sole feels a bit thin but they are not for running over broken house bricks, for standard road running I've found them ok, granted I'm 60yrs old & definitely not hardcore & only do approx 40m a week but they suit me to a tee.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review:
Exceptionally comfortable shoes. Sadly they are not hard wearing enough for me. After wearing them for about an hour and a half a day for three weeks, the soles were wearing out and part of the sole of one shoe was breaking away.

I have returned the shoes to Amazon today and have already received a full refund.

I would recommend these shoes for wearing inside, but certainly not for any form of running related exercise.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: Decent trainers for the price :) I've probably run about 20+ miles in them since delivery and have found them mostly comfortable for running in and decently breathable.Will say I have found them to be a bit smaller than most other shoes of the same size, but they are soft enough that it's not much of a problem

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: Ordered these for my father for the gym. He's usually a size 12 and I ordered a 13 to be safe but he still found them very tight. They're ok besides that but order a size or two up. A bit uncomfortable but he only wears them for an hour on an elliptical machine everyday so they suffice. I don't think he'd recommend them for day to day wear or for the treadmill or anything.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: For the price great! comfortable, I'm a size 12 with broad feet - luckily these aren't those ridiculously slim kind. Completely unbranded, unnamed (how I prefer) - The grip underneath is good and very thick rubber bottom so I feel like they will last me a while. Overall happy with my purchase - They haven't faced the rain properly yet but again, these things are basically £15, what more do you want other than - exactly what you need, a new cheap pair of trainers.More of a casual to wear thing though, I mean if you're like training or going Gym maybe splash out an extra £20 lol.

Product: Get Fit Mens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walking Gym Shoes Sport Run

Product: Vans Men's Yt Ward Trainers
Review: I was very sceptical when I bought there because of the mixed reviews, but after it arrived I can assure you they are real and come with the original vans box. So relax that’s all I’m saying.

Product: Vans Men's Yt Ward Trainers
Review:
Firstly, contrary to some of the reviews, they're not fake (at least in my case). Wards are a cheap but official alternative to the classic Old Skool shoe and they do come with some drawbacks. They take a long time to bed in (especially at the heel), Vans website has some tips on how to wear-in your new shoes to fit more comfortably - so even they are aware of it when it comes to all their shoes. However, Wards seem to be particularly bad in this regard.

If you have any concerns about how legit they are, make sure it says "Dispatched from and sold by Amazon". I've not had any issues with the dye running, as some have reported, so it's possible that the way this product page has being filled has changed over time and there were some dodgy third party retailers before, but Amazon at least are selling the real deal.

I've been a long time purchaser of Vans (mainly Old Skool) and, if it wasn't for lockdown, I would normally have gone to the local Vans store to get new ones. However, these came pretty fast from Amazon, all things considered. Ordered on a Thursday and arrived the following Monday.

I knocked the one star off because, being Wards, they just are not up to the same quality as Old Skools, and they are not as comfortable out of the box. They're fine though.

Product: Vans Men's Yt Ward Trainers
Review:
Great product. Only issue was the right shoe had white marks on them. It wasn't too noticeable so I just wore them anyway.

I am sure it was just due to the way they had been transported as the box was crushed.

Apart from that they fit fine and are as expected.

Product: Vans Men's Yt Ward Trainers
Review: Like other reviews, I was initially concerned these were fake, however following the checks (barcodes, sole stamp and bendable) my fears were allayed. As usual with vans, great fit and look good.

Product: Vans Men's Yt Ward Trainers
Review: I have worn Vans for over 30 years and they are still one of my favorite shoes to wear, they are none slip and tend to last for ages. They are well made and dry fast when they get wet. I usually wear Lot-tops as I find they are a great fit.

Product: Vans Men's Yt Ward Trainers

Product: Amazon Basics Stapler with 1000 Staples | Black
Review:
You get what you pay for. Bought this three months ago and it has already decided that the stapling of 3-5 pages at a time was too much for it to survive. It gave up. Opened it up and a piece of the stapler jumped off "I can't take it any more! The pressure is too great!!!"

My wife teared up as the piece was an emotional wreck. I tried to get the piece to rejoin the others, but he refused. "Why do you hate me so?" I just wanted my wife's stapler to work. "I'm not lazy, I am not up to the job, I can staple one page, maybe two."

I replied "I don't really need to staple 1 page documents, those would be placed in a folder by themselves. Two pages, those do happen, but the job is for 3-5 pages and you are obviously too soft and weak for that kind of work."

"You can return me? Get a refund? "

Sadly too late, the window to return for a refund ended May 31st.

Easy to use- if it worked, it would be a 5 star. It worked sometimes, so a 3 star.

Lightweight - that's not really a great characteristic for something that you are pressing down on to staple. I'd rather have something a bit more sturdy.

Sturdiness - you see, that's an important aspect of a stapler.. this, unfortunately is soft and weak.

Lastly - where is this mysterious stapler remover?

Product: Amazon Basics Stapler with 1000 Staples | Black
Review: I used to buy the cheapest staplers I could find, and they were always giving me trouble, but the "good ones" cost more than I was willing to pay, until I found this one! It works easily and well.  I bought a second one for the kitchen because I often cook boneless skinless chicken breasts, among other things, en papillote (in paper) to keep the surfaces from drying out. My problem was that I could never get the fold or maybe the shape of the cut parchment right, so I could not keep the packet sealed as necessary, so I tried stapling the edges, keeping the staples away from the food, and voila! Success. Now I don't even have to specially cut the cooking parchment; I just rip off a rectangle of the right size, fold it like a book over my food, and fold and staple the remaining three edges. It is hard to believe but this has radically improved my life!

Product: Amazon Basics Stapler with 1000 Staples | Black
Review: In my house we might use a couple dozen staples a year and we finally ran out in the other stapler. Searching Amazon, we could buy 5,000 staples (literally a few lifetimes worth of staples) or we could buy this and get enough staples to last us one lifetime, with another stapler thrown in.Is it the best stapler? No. Does it work? Yes. It says it's a 10-page stapler. That's a lie. I did 12 pages once. But it might jam if you're not committed to your stapling venture. But that's the price you pay for a free stapler with your lifetime supply of staples.

Product: Amazon Basics Stapler with 1000 Staples | Black

I am glad that so many had great experiences but mine has been extremely frustrating.

Product: Amazon Basics Stapler with 1000 Staples | Black

This was a replacement for a missing Swingline for my workspace.

I did not get through a full cartridge of staplers before NONE of them would penetrate more than 5 sheets of paper.

STAY AWAY FROM AMAZON BASICS. This is the third branded Item that I have encountered (first purchased), the other two a USB cable a friend bought and a Qi Charger. Both were not functional within a month.

I worked for Swingline for several years; I do know how to repair staplers, office and constructionlevel.

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review:
I have 2 senior cats (13yrs old in 2 months), and inevitably as they age they’re developing health issues.

Ziggy has Feline IBD (think Crohns Disease or Ulcerative Colitis in humans) which I’ve managed to keep under control with a high protein diet, I feed him tinned food from Thrive and no dry food whatsoever, but whenever he brings up a hairball this aggravates his system and he’ll be vomiting for several days after, he’s a pretty furry cat but he only needs a small amount of fur in his sytem to set him off so it’s far more frequently than his brother brings up hairballs.

Tiggy has issues with his anal glands, this started about 6 months ago, he’d be scooting his bottom on the floor and licking a lot more than usual, he didn’t seem distressed and it would only be a day at a time, I didn’t know what it was at first but thought I’d just keep an eye on it. It kept happening about once a month and I noticed his stool was harder than usual and smaller, and a little smellier. The last time was different, he got very distressed and was really struggling with going to the toilet, I think it was causing some pain and his scooting became a bit frantic, so I did a bit of reading and figured it out as being his anal glands, so I took him off to the vet who confirmed and expressed the glands for him. Tiggy suffers anxiety pretty badly after we all lived in a violent household for some years (free now), and the trip to the vet really set off his anxiety, it was heartbreaking for me and so decided to have a look into any natural ways of managing these gland issues to avoid the distress of repeated vet visits.

I came across this and it looked promising coupled with reviews of success with anal gland issues. Plus, I actually have Crohns Disease myself and the human equivalent of this product is a drink called Fybogel, which is a safe fibre for intestinal issues so I immediately felt safe in trying this product for both of my boys issues. The way it works is that when it comes into contact with the liquid in the gut it becomes like a slimy gel which lubricates the intestines and helps waste to slide through without issue and without irritation, very helpful to avoid inflammation with IBD and puts less strain on the anal glands so they can settle down and start working properly too.

They’ve been having it now for about a month. Tiggy hasn’t had any issues with his glands whatsoever, his stool now looks normal and there’s more in the box (I never thought I’d be happy to have more poop to scoop), no scooting and no extra licking. He’s using the litter box without distress and without straining. I’d say I started noticing a real improvement after about 2 weeks of this daily.

For Ziggy, I gave him this in the hopes that he would start passing his hair in his stool rather than vomiting it up. So far so good, after a month there’s only been one hairball up and it was tiny, there wasn’t any repeated vomiting after from irritation either which is fantastic. It also seems to have helped his acid reflux which is a part of having IBD, as I’ve not noticed any on the floor since he started this.

I use half a scoop each day (for those who’ve said the scoop wasn’t in the tub, I thought the same when I opened mine, but I emptied the tub into another container and the scoop has actually settled to the bottom of the tub), I don’t add any water to it, just mix it in their food (my boys only have wet food) and they eat it all up, they took to it straight away so I’m guessing that it tastes good as Tiggy is more than a little fussy with food!

So far, I’ve been giving this to both boys every day for a month and we’ve used about a quarter of the tub, so it should last about 4 months, which considering the benefits and the price of the tub, it’s more than good value, and to see to happier furbabies makes it priceless

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: Bought this at my vet's recommendation as I have a rescue greyhound with a chronic diarrhoea problem - months of trying different foods having little effect. Things improved after he was tested and treated for giardia and switched to prescription digestive care food (very expensive, but very good) but still in general I was often dealing with something close to yellow sludge ... Now a few days in with adding the pellets to his evening meal every day per the instructions, and he is I would say close to normal (comparing to my other greyhound, his sister, who has no gastric issues). At the moment I'm also giving him probiotics in the morning (he has a small breakfast) and they have certainly helped too, but I think this product is what's finally got him there. I'm now transferring him back to the same food as his sister (Hill's Science Plan) and so far, so good. Very relieved and will keep him on Protexin as long as my vet recommends. As for the taste, he seems to love it.

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: I read many of the reviews before buying this product to deal with our terrier's anal gland problem.  We have now used the Protexin pellets for three days and already we see a huge improvement in her toileting.  Her normal per day (usually in one walk) was firstly one soft but basically normal stool, then a second a little softer then a semi-liquid stool and finally a jellied and liquid stool.Three days in and we are having two solid, firm stools per day.  Also no "scooting" along the floor so it seems these pellets (they look like rabbit food pellets) are doing their job and the firm stools are naturally emptying her glands.  -  So hopefully no more trips to the vet to get her glands manually expressed ; an unpleasant process for dog, vet and owner.I highly recommend this product.  It literally does what it says on the canister and is great value for money.

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: I bought this for my Cat as I hoped it will keep his stools firm but it's difficult to feed to him. The product comes in tiny pellet like hamster food and an average cat would need about 20 or so of these. They also smell like hamster food and so my cat refuses to eat them. I tried putting them in his food and also adding some warm water to them to dissolve into a paste then mixing in his food and he refuses to eat his food. I tried giving him it like a tablet but he needs too many of them so that's not nice for him. I think these should come tablet sized so people can crumble them up if they want them smaller.The reason I give this 3 stars is that I gave them to my other cat on his food who will eat anything with his food and it seems to keep his stools firm and not too stinky.

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: I work at a vets and was recommended to try this on my elderly cat who suffers from constipation. I have heard so much success with this for cats and dogs with constipation in the vets over the years so thought I would try under the direction of my own vet. I was dubious as my cat suffers from a condition called Megacolon and she lacks the peristalsis movement of the colon to pass faeces. I was trying to work out whether bulking her poops would be beneficial. I spoke to the Protexin rep and she recommended to go cautiously with cats with Megacolon. I tried it for a number of weeks and it did not help her issues at all. I do not recommend using this for cats with Megacolon. If you are thinking of trying it, consult your vet first!!! It did not work for my old girl, but every case is different. Always check with your vet before getting any supplements. My cat is now on different medications to help with her condition.

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review:
I have waited a month to write this review, my frenchie had anal gland problems and this is miracle stuff, with not being able to get to the vet due to covid her glands were becoming full.

After an online consultation with a vet this was recommended and after a few days her swelling was down and her poops were solid and clearly this helped empty the anal sacks.

She doesn't even mind eating it mixed with her food, at first I was giving her it with every meal but now I do it every other day. My other Frenchie is a bit picky but eats this if you disguise it well enough with gravy or meat.

I am very happy with this product!
I don't have to go to the vets anymore for my girl to have anal glands emptied which I can't imagine is nice for her. I was skeptical but it really works!

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: My elderly dog has been suffering with anal gland issues for a number of years now. She’s raw fed but also can’t tolerate sugars in her diet due to yeast issues that effect her ears so struggle getting any fibre in her diet.Her last bad anal gland infection she ended up having to have two courses of antibiotics which played havoc on her guts, so when I noticed the signs a couple of months later that her glands were playing up again I ordered this in hope it would prevent another trip to the vets and yet more antibiotics. I was so happy when it worked! Shes been having this daily for 6 weeks now and not had any issues since! The first couple of weeks I teamed this up with yudigest and she’s now just having the profibre added to her meals and so far so good. One very happy customer 😊 I’ve just ordered again and will be using this for the foreseeable future!

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review:
This really worked well for my pup.
Took a week or so to really see the difference but his poops are now firm enough to easily scoop! After months of the vet telling us he was fine and not to worry I still wanted to try something as it was sometimes impossible to clean up after him and I worried that it could lead to anal glad issues later on.

And a huge side bonus is that he’s a lot less stinky in the gas department too. He seems happy with the taste as he’s doesn’t seem to notice it mixed in with his food.

Doesn’t smell too great from my point of view but I’m yet to find the dog complaining.

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: I was originally advised by my Vet that this only helped 50% of dogs with recurrent anal gland problems.I've obviously been lucky - it's worked for both of my dogs!  Since starting this product a couple of year's ago, neither of them have had to have their glands emptied at the Vet's.(I squidge the granules into Dairylea cheese, and they gulp it down!)I'm a repeat (and satisfied) customer! :-)

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: My Ragdoll cat had a few days where his poo wasn't quite the usual, as his stomach is quite sensitive... I'd read probiotics COULD help, however there was apparently no conclusive evidence to say they do. Thought I'd give it a try and after just one meal with this, his poos were completely back to normal. And since, I've put a little bit in his food when his poos are a bit runner than usual, and this really does the job. No issues with eating this in his food so perhaps it tastes great, although I will say my cat does have a very keen appetite and no issues with eating. My vet has confirmed there's no conclusive medical evidence to say probiotics definitely work, but in Herb's case, I really believe they do! The vet also advised there's no issue with giving him this when I think he needs it as it won't do him any harm. This has really been a great find

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: My dog has always had progressively loose poos on a walk and having recently had radiotherapy for cancer had an upset tummy too.He can normally detect meds a mile off but not this.It has worked wonders sprinkled in his meals and he has eaten it willingly with very positive results. I split his daily dose between his 2 meals and will 100% be buying it again to keep his system healthy.No wonder it has so many good reviews.

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: This was recommended to me by my vet as per our Covid consultation over the phone having worked out that my dog suffers from "BD" beach diarrhea from seawater playing ball and sadly he was in a right mess in so many ways, so with the vets recommendation to change his food to a more high quality brand than he already was on and to use Protexin in a bid to replace all his lost gut flora and it really has worked.My dog was on another brand of gut flora prior to this which cost £25 and did not work no where as well as this Protexin has.You just sprinkle some onto your dogs food and watch them enjoy it. I am so pleased to find that l could buy it here on Amazon due to covid restrictions and l am so pleased my vet gave me a fantastic consultation over the phone to direct me to here.Life is good again, eyes bright, better coat, great digestion, good stools, no smelly breath, energy and hunger are levels back, sleeps better, my friend has got his spirit back and l could not be more overjoyed. Thankyou

Product: Protexin Veterinary Pro-Fibre for Dogs and Cats, 500g
Review: This was recommended by my vet for my dogs loose stools.  It has certainly helped and I just add it to her morning meal and it has really made a difference.  Its a shame you have to purchase 2 pots because I wasn't sure if it would work and it might have been a wasteful expense if I didn't want to continue using it and I was almost tempted not go ahead with the purchase simply because I didn't want to purchase x2 without trying it first.  I  have 2 dogs and I added half a scoop to the other dogs bowl just because its good for their digestion but sometimes she gets it stuck in her beard and ends up expanding in her water bowl - yuck!

Product: Sneaky Unisex's SBTRE Shoe Tree, Black, One
Review: These shoe trees are extremely sturdy and fit wonderfully in my my size UK 9.5 Air Force 1's. Being as they are quite sturdy, you do have to put quite a bit of effort into bending them to put them inside your shoes so be careful as the spring is very strong so you have to be mindful when removing these from your shoes. If you put these in shoes that you plan to continuously use then you may find them a bit frustrating after a while but for shoe collectors you can be sure that these will keep your shoes intact.For the price, I will definitely be buying this product again to put in my growing collection of shoes.

Product: Grip Black Ballpoint Pens, Pack of 10
Review: Was quite disappointed. The grips hurt my fingers as I hold my pen quite low (though the design is probably to encourage people to hold it higher, that’s just not how i hold my pen). I also pride myself on my handwriting and the pen used is an important factor in neat writing and I only found this pen frustrating. The ink is not smooth or consistent and comes out quite light. It feels like they’re already running out after a word. I’ve just ended up buying completely different pens and will probably just give these to a high school student (as they’re the type to go through pens quickly so this cheap option will probably be okay.)

Product: Grip Black Ballpoint Pens, Pack of 10
Review: I've used Zebra pens for a long time now and have consistently been impressed by the ease of writing. The pen is quite simple and cheap but there is a calming experience of using it. Like some other well-made ballpoint pens, writing is made smooth and does not suffer from the issue of ink smudging. The rubber grip provides a firm grip and the necessary comfort to continue writing for long sessions. In all, I love Zebra pens and for the price and quality, it's a to-go purchase for pens instead of the generic and dreadful stick ballpoint pens.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: Pretty baby pink colour, knitted look, very comfortable, lightweight despite having a “proper” sole.  They feel more like little ankle boots than slippers and are so easy to wear I’ve gone outside several times before realising and nipping back inside to change into outdoors boots.The memory foam insole is amazing.  I have historic ankle damage and fibromyalgia so my ankles and feet are usually swollen and painful.  I’ve found that these slipper boots are so light they don’t pull on my feet when my legs are raised and when I walk the cushioning really seems to help with the pain.Size-wise, I think the description is about right.  I’m a 5 to 5.5 length but usually buy boots in a 6 as I have wide feet and can swop to orthotic insoles if the support isn’t great.  When I first put the slippers on (size 5 to 6) I thought they would be a little too small if you’re a true size 6 but the fluffy insides and memory foam do squish down once you start moving so I think the sizing is accurate.Longevity I can’t really comment on just yet but the quality is great so I’m sure they’ll last far longer than the 3 months my last Mountain Warehouse slipper boots managed!To sum up - these are the most comfortable slippers I’ve ever had and I’ll be buying a spare pair as soon as the price drops back down to around £15.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: I bought a pair of these slippers for myself in December 2019. They look great, but without a shadow of a doubt they are the most uncomfortable items of footwear that I have ever worn.They are cut too big, the foot is not lined at all and most importantly they rub my left outer ankle something chronic. Only the ankle vertical part is lined, one really would not know that the memory foam exists after a few wears and the material covering the ankle seems to have collapsed inwards, hence the friction.In summary, my feet are cold and sore, and due to being oversized one's socks tend to sail around one's feet. Wearing them is painful, especially over the left outer ankle. I hate the product. Please read this review carefully if you are considering purchasing these slippers, and resist the temptation to place an order/part with your money. Appearances can be deceptive, and sometimes even if one pays a decent price for a product one can end up with pure and utter garbage.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: I fell in love with the design of these slippers but am beyond disappointed. They run on the small size. I bought a 7-8 but at very best there a 7. The insole part of the slipper at first felt fat and bouncy but after just 1 week the "memory" foam has completely forgotten to bounce back into shape and are actually painful to walk on. Having a hard sole and no foam is just brutal. Like I say, the design is fab and loved the ruching detail. The fabric is chenille which is lovely but nothing makes up for just how awful these slippers are after such a short amount of time. Save your money and pass.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: Sturdy, warm and comfortable, but buy a bigger size and you'll need an additional padded insole. They have a plastic sole that does wrap around a bit so you can step outside in them to get the post. Mine have now been through the washing machine twice on a special setting and came out of it fine. Had them for months and wear them at least half the day.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: I'm a shoe size 7.5, and my feet are neither wide nor narrow. I bought the 7-8 size, and they are a good fit on me, not too sloppy like most slipper boots I've bought in the past. The insoles are cushioned and insulate against the cold, and the soles are robust enough for nipping outside on my balcony to feed the blackbird. They don't look bad either. I'm pleased with these slippers.EDIT: They are getting a little looser with wear. I may have to wear thicker socks...

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: I bought my partner these as an early Christmas present as he old ones were ready for the bin, she loves them, she did say one of them was slightly tight on her. She loves them though, nice thick sole so the laminate flooring coldness is kept as bay and they have the memory foam inserts so they are very comfy on her feet.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes

I'm wondering whether I should have bought the bigger size, but was conscious as to whether they would have been too big once I had worn them in, so I'm hoping that they will stretch a bit more so my toes aren't touching the tip!!  However, they are very comfortable and the memory insole is a beauty on my feet!  I wear them all the time and I am very happy with the quality of them.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
