Review: I got these as a Christmas present, had them on for an hour and the sole came away from the slipper, poorly made, a real shame as very comfy and warm.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: It's so difficult to find ladies/feminine footwear when you are a size 10EEE, but I came across these and loved the colour options and the ruched detailing. I ordered the light tray size 9/10. 2 day delivery and they are, by far, the best slippers I have ever purchased! Super comfy, nice and warm, supportive with a non slip firm base. I'm so pleased with them and I'll be ordering another pair soon to alternate colours! Thank you

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: I usually take a 3.5 and these fit perfectly and are snug and warm. The sole is rubber so hardy enough to pop outside and clean and the chenille fabric is soft and looks good. And it's great to find practical, on trend slippers which aren't fussy in design and good value too.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: arrived very fast, a little on the big side but fine, very good quality the smaller size would have been too small so I'm happy with this, look like they will last a long time.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: These slipper boots are really good ,wear well ,  this is my 3rd pair,  the fit is slightly neat but they stretch a reasonable amount, well worth the money!

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: Purchased as a Christmas present. They look and feel really nice slippers. I'm sure they will be a good fit as well.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: These bootie slippers will keep my feet cosy and safe.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: All good, no issues with purchase.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: These slippers are the perfect fit and warm and comfortable. Love them.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: Very comfortable warm slippers with a very good sole.

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: Warm and comfy

Product: LongBay Ladies' Chenille Knit Warm Boots Slippers Soft Plush Fleece Booties Slipper Memory Foam Women Bootee Slippers House Shoes
Review: This is much better than the one i had from the other brand ,it is more cosy and i ll definitely buy again

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Video Player is loading.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Have bought 3 pairs of these as seemed a great offer unfortunatly all three pairs are now in the bin after a week wearing them the inside heel wears through the insoles leaving a sharp place that your heel rubs on. Tried putting other onsoles in the second pair same happened tried a different size on third did the same. They havnt thought of anything to protect your foot from the plastic around the bubble.on the heel. No matter what if tried it shreds through it and causes foot blistering

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I hated these shoes at first! They were so difficult to get on, it would take me a good five minutes to cram my feet in! They were so tight that they were painful. The hole you put your foot in is just too small, and the material clings very tightly. But, I persevered and they are much easier to get on now they have expanded a little. They are bouncy and comfortable to walk on.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I bought these for my daily one exercise per during this pandemic. I was very disappointed when product arrived in a cheap plastic bag.  The smell of chemicals nearly knocked me out.  The trainers are huge, I am a wide fit 8 and they just flapped up and down as I walked.  I didn't even bother trying them outside. I would send them back if it wasn't for this virus going on at the moment.  What a waste of money!!

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I was a bit disappointed to start with as the shoe is soft all the way around the foot and the only solid part is the sole. I’ve had ankle fusion surgery so I need the support and I didn’t get it. The shoes are comfortable that’s for sure, but the lack of support did make me walk awkwardly and probably done me more harm than good. Although, they did stop the pain in the soles of my feet. I always buy a size 7 UK due to ankle issues. These were fine but I think I should have went up a size to make it easier to get into them as they are covered n last one. I did have band marks on my feet after taking them off. I think I’d stick to sketchers from now on as they do provide the support. Not a complete waste of money. They are comfortable, but provide me with nowhere near the support I need.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Most comfortable trainers I've ever worn. I'm a Healthcare Assistant, so I'm constantly on my feet and these get me through 12hr shifts better than any other trainers. The only down points to them is that they aren't waterproof on top, but they do dry out quickly and your feet will still sweat if you are wearing them for long shifts. I've found putting some odor and sweat absorbing insoles in them really helps and provides extra comfort. They are also great quality and hard-wearing despite being lightweight, which is excellent. I've put them through the ringer and they still look fairly new. We'll worth the money! I saw these while looking for Sketchers and I'm glad I took a chance on these.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Comfortable, just slightly neat fitting around the top of my foot (where laces would be if it were a lace up shoe).Definitely neat sizing so if you are at all unsure, I’d order the size up if you have a broad foot as there isn’t much in the way of space width wise. Length is normal size I’d say.I like the fact that there is a little added height due to the platform sole however beware if you have problematic ankles as I have went over on my ankles a couple of times wearing these.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I bought theses trainers to wear indoors due to suffering for months with a heel bone spur. They’re very light and fit perfectly (size 7) I do have very slender feet so they’re ideal for me. The foots slightly slides forward but in all honesty I’m struggling just trying to walk with so much foot pain. The sole is well padded. I cant comment on use for outside as that’s not what I’ll be using them for. The also look really nice.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: For the price I would say very good value for money.  They fit well ..I would recommen buying one size bigger if you have large ankles or like to wear thick socks I will order another one size bigger for winter so I can wear thick socks.  A bit of a struggle to wear but once it's worn it is very comfortable ...I could walk for miles in them . I am happy with them .

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Really impressed with these. Having Arthritic ankles, I need something comfortable with a slight heel but firm enough to walk in. These fit the bill and are the most comfortable shoes ever. I have already bought a second pair in a different colour. Super practical too as lightweight to pack and can be slipped on and off easily. Highly recommend.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: So I’m not one for wearing trainers but my daughter bought a pair of these and I tried them on. I then had to have a pair myself as they are so comfortableI will definitely order againOnly downside was out of the box there was a strong chemical smell but this disappeared

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Delivery 16/06/2020 - Worn straight away for "test walk" indoors to check for comfort. Impressed with look and considered ordering a pair in each color.Pros: They fit lovely and do not cause blisters they look good and they are very comfortable.Cons: It is very easy to turn over on your ankle in these shoes as the material gives way on uneven ground. The soles shown in picture after about a fortnight of wearing for one hour walk daily wear very very quickly.I had high hopes for these trainers but as good as they look and as comfortable as they are I cannot justify replacing them every two weeks.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: i wear mine all the time and work in logistics department so up and down quite a bit, i suffer with arthritis quite bad so although my feet still hurt these feel quite comfy.  I also do agility with my dogs and these are fine on grass not sure about in the sandschool though, most trainers let the sand in.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review:
They look nice.
I would say they are half a size to big
I’m a 7 and ordered a 7 after reading previous reviews.
I’m wearing thicker socks with them
They are comfortable but don’t feel as supportive as I hoped they would be
Wish I had returned them but I have worn them

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Really was excited to receive these shoes just before lockdown i suffer with planter fasciitis. The material is very tight making them difficult to put on. They was great comfy no heel pain. 8 weeks later and not worn everyday both shoes have completely split in two. Gutted waste of money i normally buy vionic so unfortunately you get what you pay for.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I was after a sturdy soled walking shoe that didn't cost the earth and spied this little number. Arrived quickly. Not tried mesh before.. it's a stretchy material that didn't rub or anything... instant fit. comfortable, walked miles!  It was a hot day but my feet didnt swelter ..  like them lots :-)

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Brilliant shoes for someone who does long hours on her feet and suffers with excruciating achilles tendonitis! These are the first pair of shoes I've found that actually support my feet during 10 hour kitchen shifts, and don't leave me crippled afterwards. Would seriously reccomend!

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Lightweight, comfortable fit, fast delivery gave them a road test and they are so comfortable my feet felt fab after a 4 mile walk in extremely hot weather. I wouldn't like to run in them as they wouldn't feel tight enough to stay on but if your after a fabulous walking trainer these are the bad boys of comfort.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: After reading the reviews I decided to get myself a pair. They are so comfortable and great for general wear. I bought the purple colour and my husband commented they looked like slippers. So I've decided to use these for indoors and have just ordered a black pair for outdoors.I am a size 6 but because I need a wide fitting decided to purchase a size 6.5. These fit really well and have plenty of room for thicker socks. Would recommend.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: It's nearly impossible to review shoes a few days after purchase as time will tell if they maintain shape and endure wear and tear. But for now, they look good and are very comfortable, so that's why I can only rate 4 stars. A couple of months down the line it could be 5 or even 3 depending on the condition.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Bought for mother and myself, very comfortable and easy shoe BUT only on level ground, being only thicker than a very thick sock offers next to no aid for your heel/ankle turning over the thick sole.. mum is 68, sent hers back and am careful with mine, mainly a house shoe now

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Expected it to be a comfy slip on trainer. Bought specially to be able to slip on easily when baby is in sling. Turned out to be more like a plastic/ stretchy plimsoll which you have to pull at to squeeze foot in, and then it was tight and uncomfortable. And it smelt like chemicals, I do not recommend.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Shoes are true to size, doesn’t feel like your wearing any! Have suffered with plantar fasciitis for months and within a week of wearing these my symptoms have improved immensely. Don’t normally do reviews but felt I had to recommend these are they are so comfy.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Nice looking shoe but was very disappointed I found them to be very comfortable but the sole on the right foot split across the bottom after about 4 weeks wear which I was only wearing at work. I got them as was advertised as a good shoe for my planta problem which they helped but I can't keep buying new shoes each month felt let down

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: (Pink lace up trainers) I simply adore these shoes, they are cute comfy and awesome for walking or for everyday use. I would however suggest goes the next size up as they are quite small. I am a size 5 but I should have considered going for a 5.5 or 6. It is  it much of an issue since the soles are removable but the soles add to the comfort for your foot whilst travelling and so it's well worth keeping them in.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Was told to get a trainer with an air sole as have been experiencing pain in my heels and difficulty walking after sitting for a short period of time. Read the reviews and these seemed perfect. Arrived promptly and looked ok. Size ok but quite tight on the width. I am a size 5 but if I went for the next  size up would be too big. Not that comfortable to walk in and seems to have made my problem worse. Cant see how you could run in them.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These fit too low around my heel, so were slipping with each step I took.  I am usually a size 5 UK and although the size was correct they were very uncomfortable.  They absolutely stank, it was an odour combining a top note of burnt rubber with a back note of toxic plastic,  not very pleasant!  Would not recommend.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I was so excited that I had ordered these, but a bit disappointed, the base of this shoe is very hard, there is no give in it at all...which cause the soul of ur feet to hurt, across the top of ur feet is all so quiet tight, I think with time they will stretch

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These shoes were bought for my wife who uses them for work.  The comfortable cushioned fit is ideal as she works in a care home and is on her feet all day.The shoes are lightweight which is perfect if taking when travelling.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Bought for comfort as will be on my feet for a few hours each day at new jobHave been for a walk in them, they are lovely and comfortableVery pleased with purchaseDelivered on time, driver polite and respected distancing rules

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Bought to replace my much-loved Sketchers walking shoes. Significantly cheaper, so I thought I would give these a go. Can truly say that they are excellent. Very lightweight & comfortable to wear from the start. They have been perfect for my morning walks along regular footpaths and uneven, stony paths through the local forest. Probably not up to muddy challenges but I avoid those areas anyway. Supremely pleased and will be buying again!

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These are the best shoes for travel! They are super comfortable and so light! Great for an ambling walk! Not waterproof. I like them so much I’ve purchased 2 more sets for myself and a similar pair for a lady I care for who has dementia AND they have helped with her balance and she loves them!

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Comfortable and fits nicely. Light on the feetPoor quality! Lasts 2 months before it formed a hole in front of shoe

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These shoes are great - very comfortable and they look great too. As they are no laces, they slip on easily and no pressure points on the feet.  The soles are nice and high and they offer great support when walking.I am a UK 14 and they fit perfectly.Great buy.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These are so comfy I purchased another colour.They look much neater than on photo ..and I wear size 8 .Perfect for my daily 2 mile walk ...can wear them all day with bare feet .Look good with jeans .

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I would not myself class these as long walking or running trainers.  But l have worn them on short dog walks.  They are not appropriate for knee problems either.Having said that they look good but my opinion is that they are not good for walking long distances.  I will not be buying another pair.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Bought these shoes because i work in deli and on my feet all day cant wear socks with them because they are so tight and Afterwearing for an hour started hurting under my foot and twisted my ancle walking into work not good

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: love these. Tried them on at once. Really comfortable. Colour is great too. Only down side is , I wish they did a four and half. Not a huge problem though. They are that nice, I can cope with that no problem.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I am size 4.5 I bought size 4 and fitted perfectly. light weight. nice design. the only issue is sometimes my left footslips forward, therefore I think is no good to use them for hiking  but apart of everyday  it  is ok.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These shoes are really comfort and fitted as I expected. In the beginning, I was not sure if I had guessed with them but once I tried them, I felt comfort and relief especially in one of my foot with fasciitis plantar. I recommend this shoes all people who work, walk or travel.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: They're good looking and perfect for someone with narrow feet however not as comfortable as crocs. I bought the two for comparison and I must say the heel is not as soft and supportive - I'm on my feet for at least 10 hrs a day and don't skimp on comfortable shoes.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Prompt delivery,  l am pleased with the shoe and the fit was spot on. However I was not happy that it was in a plastic bag within another plastic bag. Although I would have purchased another pair in another colour, I am put off by the packaging.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Great lightweight shoe. Perfect for those people who do long 12 hour shifts. They really helped reduce my back pain from being on my feet for a long time. Can easily be put in the washing machine when needed too.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Received today and worn all day. Very light and comfortable. Plenty of support will be ideal for country walking as it has a good sole. Sizing true fit. A long time since I had such comfortable shoes.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I'm sure these shoes would have been lovely had I been able to get them on my feet I ordered a size 8 which my normal shoe size but it was impossible to even get my foot into the shoe very disappointing

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Excellent trainer. As a nurse with flat arches due to wearing flat shoes for over 30 years these have sorted out my posture and pain. Lightweight, comfortable very pleased with the product. Arrived early too.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: This is a really comfy pair of shoes,  i do 11 hr night shifts but they didnt pinch or rub, only fault is they are so difficult to get your foot in due to the tight elastic but once you master n pull your calf muscles,  these shoes are great.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: not so good...arived deffective  ( a small one but visible) and not so confortable if you work 10 hours shift with them . avoid for prolongued use on the same day as you will get painful feet

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These are really comfortable, I'm a support worker and we walk miles now I've got some decent footwear to do it in and I'll be ordering more. Love them thank you.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Excuse the detail but I am having a terrible problem with my feet. Hard skin and  bunions mean that for walking long distances I need really comfortable shoes. These trainers are brilliant. It is like walking on air. I might have to buy another pair in another colour...

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: A great pair of shoes, really comfortable.  I wore them in the rain and none slip too, also very stylish. I have ordered another pair in a different color and in a smaller size as first pair slightly big but good with thick socks.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Bought a pair last year and this year bought another 2 pairs. They are so comfortable and looks smart with my work uniform.My neighbour lived the look that she bought 2 pairs as well

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I walk 4miles a day then do a 10hours shift I have arthritis and these trainers well not much off a miracle for me comfort I can walk with ease do my job and walk back home a definite must buy and for the price wow amazing

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These are really good trainers to use in the gym. One thing I did have a bit of an issue with is I thought they were lace and they are not they are slip on. If you buy these I suggest you get a shoe horn.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I love the general design, flexibility and non-slip aspects. I picked it as it seemed to be able to give a strong insole support. However, I still use my own insoles since I actually do need them as well. I underestimated the size. I will keep the product, even if a little large ( I chose a half size larger), as I plan to use it during the winter too when I wear thick socks! Not sure if it is waterproof.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I found these womens trainers are perfect... Fit as expected. Light weight.. And good to walk in... Very breathable... And comfortable on the feet.... . And lovely colours...to choose from....I would recommend....

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I've had these shoes a couple of weeks now. I normally take a size 6 and this is what I order but I could of done with a size 5 as they are a bit big on my feet. I am a carer and I am on my feet for 12.5hrs a day, they are comfortable to wear but and this could just be my feet, I wouldn't say they were the most comfortable shoes I've ever worn

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: When ordering order a size smaller than you usual have i had 6.5 but was too big now got a 5.5 and they are perfectI have a collapsed arch and these are really helping me at workVery comfortable

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Had this product for a few days and already the insoles are playing up keep moving down to bottom while you walk nd they hurt your feet

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: After wearing these for 2 days I have cuts on both of the sides of my feet which is disappointing as they feel comfy but now I can't wear them anymore as it's to painful.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These shoes are really comfortable and pretty plus if you have a bad back or arthritis they are super easy to put on!Just pop your foot in and pull on like a sock, done. I can happily recommend them.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review:
100% recommend!
I bought these for work and they fit like a dream!
(however I did buy the purple ones too in the same size and they are slightly bigger 🤔)
I suffer from plantar fasciitis and these have definitely helped reduce the pain while walking.
Super comfortable, I wear them for 10 hours + at work and never feels like I have shoes on 👌

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I have bought these for my mother in law, she had previously seen them on Facebook.....and liked how flexible and lightweight they looked! She says they are very comfortable!

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I’m very pleased - not as soft as Sketchers but then they are not Sketchers or anywhere near the price. I’ve worn them non stop ! Great shoe for the money

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I ordered these for work but they were too big even after the 3rd try to get the right size. They are quite wide and I would not recommend if you have narrow feet.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I'm on my feet for 12 hours a day within a care home. I have tried a lot of types of shoes for comfort and these are by far the best. My feet are good for at least 7 hours

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Super shoes. Wear them almost every day. Ihave large size 9 awkward feet. It's a nightmare to find shoes. These are perfect. Still in perfect condition after almost daily wearing, yet I've ordered a 2nd pair already as I have never had such comfortable ones. Various colleagues are also ordering them. Thank you.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These trainers looked really good and they were the perfect colour that I was looking for to match a pair of leggings!  But unfortunately they were too small for me but I ordered a size bigger!

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I have suffered a great deal from plantar fasciitis and have been looking for walking shoes with arch-support without having to pay a lot, since I don't have that kind of money. These seem to be doing what I need.They arrived quickly - even during theese horrible coronatimes.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Looks smart, feels comfortable, and light weight. I have not worn it yet, but bought it for work purpose. Product as described as picture n came next day after ordering.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Was sceptical as I have wide feet and ankles. Was a bit of an effort to get on but when eventually did they feel pretty comfortable even if a little too big, an hoping that getting on will be easier over time.  Haven't walked in them yet so can't comment on that

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: I bought these because they were recommended I try them due to suffering with plantar fasciitis I've only tried them for a week and so far my plantar fasciitis is so much better already, but now after a few weeks I noticed the rubber sole had started peeling off now they are almost unwearable. Would not buy again

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: We're ok light, didn't get rid of plantar facieitas, if any thing they made it worse. Great fit, true to size, gave to my granddaughter for school

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These shoes are really comfy, as a big old unit I sometimes get aching feet, due to fasciitis and fallen arches. These shoes have been a revelation.

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: These are brilliant! They lost a star because the insole moves! (The company credited me instantly so I could get replacement insoles!).They help me walk more. The are really supportive.  No more pain in the heel!

Product: HKR Womens Trainers with Memory Foam Comfortable Slip on Work Walking Shoes
Review: Very comfortable, light weight shoes. Use them for work, i do walk a lot at work.Ordered a second pair from the same retailer but different style. Fingers crossed they will be just as good.(black, size uk3.5-eu36)

Product: 15 Strong Large Cardboard Storage Moving House Boxes with 66m Fragile Tape 47cm x 31.5cm x 30cm 44 Litres
Review: The advertised is 44 Litres, this is misleading as you can only fit 37.8 litres.The inside of the box is 28x30x45 which is 37.8 litres that is a 7.2 litres difference from 44 litres or a 15% difference.

Product: 15 Strong Large Cardboard Storage Moving House Boxes with 66m Fragile Tape 47cm x 31.5cm x 30cm 44 Litres
Review: I think it was my fault but I thought these boxes would be slightly bigger as I purchased large boxes but they're great all the same and very strong.The best thing was inside the small box that the Fragile tape came into, the seller thought of everything you would need when you're moving and put a Teabag inside. Such a lovely touch 😍

Product: 15 Strong Large Cardboard Storage Moving House Boxes with 66m Fragile Tape 47cm x 31.5cm x 30cm 44 Litres
Review:
Good set of boxes.

The provided tape was a major let down - very thin and easy to tear; (it became very annoying extremely quickly just trying to peel it off the roll in one piece)

The adhesion was also poor (kept unpeeling from box; a small piece also wouldn't keep the bottom folded over while you tape a full length piece on etc) so couldnt trust heavy boxes by the handles.

I think instead of wasting money on branded tape (the boxes are anyway?) providing tape that works would be nice?

Had a box set from a storage company prior and their tape was fine, as is cheap supermarket packing tape. They also tear easy but nowhere near as much as this one.

Edit: after packing, moving countries, unpacking, stacking and unstacking countless times, these boxes have held up well (even with their sketchy tape). Some of the boxes were loaded with near 30kg and yes, by the handles (trying to pull the boxes in the van by handles, however is a no-no).

While smaller than the boxes from storage company, held up better overall too.

Would buy again.

Product: 15 Strong Large Cardboard Storage Moving House Boxes with 66m Fragile Tape 47cm x 31.5cm x 30cm 44 Litres
Review:
Great boxes. They are sturdy and easy to assemble. You basically close the flaps and tape the bottom and the top when you’ve filled it.

What I think is great about these boxes from this company is that accompanying the box you get a Yorkshire tea bag ( nice touch) a black marker, a roll of sticky red and white tape that’s says fragile (another star) you also have some individual stickers and best of all each box had a series of squares with Space for You to write reminders of what is in each box and for the removal people a space to say which room the box needs to go in.

I am moving and think they are very useful. I’ve nearly gone through the pack and will need to purchase some more.

Great package and well worth the price.

I would recommend these boxes if you are moving.

If you found this review helpful please click below thank you

Product: 15 Strong Large Cardboard Storage Moving House Boxes with 66m Fragile Tape 47cm x 31.5cm x 30cm 44 Litres
Review: They certainly did the job for me! I used them for books, dishes and tech stuff meaning some boxes were heavier than others. I carried them down three flights of stairs - so much fun - the tape and boxes held well. I would order again! As a matter of fact I will keep them for the next move. Hopefully that won't be too soon...The size of the boxes worked well for me cause the bigger the box the more you want to put into it and then of course at some point it gets too heavy. Even the heavier boxes were fine for me to handle. Again yes from me.

Product: 15 Strong Large Cardboard Storage Moving House Boxes with 66m Fragile Tape 47cm x 31.5cm x 30cm 44 Litres
Review: I love these boxes.  Never thought I’d feel anything towards a box, but there you go!  Moving house (at some point in the future....) and I wanted smaller boxes I could fill and still lift!  These are great as you can fill them with books and still move them afterwards.  I also love the handles on the sides and have since ordered more slightly larger boxes for bigger stuff,  but these small ones are perfect.

Product: 15 Strong Large Cardboard Storage Moving House Boxes with 66m Fragile Tape 47cm x 31.5cm x 30cm 44 Litres
Review: High quality boxes. After reading comments about the big boxes becoming too heavy if overfilled and not easy to carry I opted for the Medium size. They are just perfect. You will receive 15 boxes in total and that's plenty of storage believe me. I went for aftermarket tape purely because of my fragile items inside. The originally supplied tape by Global Direct is great and it does say fragile. These are double walled boxes and they will last a very long time. Review:
These arrive we packed and protected. They are heavy when all together so ensure you can move them into your house.

It's nice to get all the accessories you need to pack and this kit is certainly loaded with

Fragile tape,
Marker pen,
Fragile stickers

And a Yorkshire teabag for when you need a break.

The boxes are sturdy and can certainly hold a decent amount of weight, they are a little smaller than I had expected but the measure as advertised and I still managed to box up my flat for moving.

Overall a decent price for what's included.

Product: 15 Strong Large Cardboard Storage Moving House Boxes with 66m Fragile Tape 47cm x 31.5cm x 30cm 44 Litres

I have many other boxes but they all have to be returned, to the Removal Company.
These DIRECT boxes I purchased off Amazon twice now, have a clear logo on the side; this means I can identify and keep the boxes I paid for.
I can return the others boxes to the Removal Company but I do not have to unpack these Direct boxes, until I am ready.
The Direct boxes come with a handy marking pen, 'Fragile' tape and a teabag!

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: Great boots in fact this is my second pair as my others wore out. I use them for dog walking, gardening, DIY so they get a lot of use. They are comfortable but a little on the generous size but as I put insoles to make them more comfy it is not a massive issue. For the price these are the best on the market, I have bought more expensive brands but they don't last as long and often split and leak.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: Simple pair of wellies. The size is, as you would expect, slightly larger than a shoe equivalent, all my wellies are like this. I get the shoe size and am happy as I can wear thermal socks on top of normal ones and have warm feet in the winter.These appear to be exactly the same quality as the previous pairs I have bought (I get through a pair every couple of years) and decent value. They are flexible and easy to get my feet in and out of.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: the product is good standard Dunlop and fits with a little room to spare as one would hope with wellies but the production or packing methods mean the boots emit an overwhelming rubber/chemical smell for about a week especially if kept near a  hot radiator.  Initially i was told to try 'cleaning them out' by the seller but after my further query the seller did offer to take them back .  However by the time I was able to do the return the smell had faded almost completely so i decided to keep the boots which are otherwise fine.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: Haven’t had the chance to test them out yet, but they’re really comfy, quite roomy and as others reviewers have mentioned, probably half a size bigger, but I like that so I’ll be able to wear thick socks with them in winter. Really pleased!

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review:
I wear size 12 wellies.
I ordered 12 they were hugely oversized and totally unwearable.
I ordered 11 and remarkably they were also far too big.
I now have £24 spent on these wellies that I can't wear nor return (as its costs £26 to do so).
Considering filling with soil as a garden planter.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: These wellies are comfortable for walking, good well made footbed and good grip for country walks.  Are they as sexy as the Hunter wellies or as twee as the Joules wellies?  No.  Do they look good in hot pants in the VIP area?  Hmmmm no.  However, what they are is green solid kick arse wellies which do everything they are supposed to.Delivery was super quick, they are well priced.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: Found these enormous, too wide at the top of the boot as well.Definitely should have gone for a size or two smaller.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: I've only had these boots for a few days and the weather being what it is atm, glorious, I've not been able to test them out.  They look okay and the soles are lovely and thick so I can walk over rugged areas and therefore I'm sure they are okay. Best to ask me to review them in a few months time when I may have been able to really put them to the test.  Having said that they feel strong, look robust so atm I'm happy to have boots, for working in, gardening and walking through muddy fields etc. They're functional boots and that is what I needed :)

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: Been through thick mud, sand, ponds, sharp brush over many hours and they still hold. Even regulary use to kick things in place while I'm working about. For the price, excellent quality. They will being to deteriote after a few years of regular use, but what do you expect for this price. I think they also look quite nice. If however, you need a fashionable pair of boots to walk your pedigree down a country lane or camp at glasto then I would suggest you get a pair of Hunters.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: These boots are too wide fitting. Far wider than my current boots which I am replacing, and I have a normal size foot. Also they are a bit floppy, i.e. not rigid enough. They don't stand up by themselves which is annoying when trying to put your feet into them.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review:
Really not sure what to say as I will have to return these.

The quality and size is fine. However, my leg calves are being squeezed and cutting off the circulation and it's actually very painful.

Not quite sure what has happened as I've not had this issue before.

Good size for those with no leg muscles.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: No nonsense wellies,delivered early I've lost count of how many pairs I've had over the years,I keep rotties so do about 8 miles a day in them,a pair usually lasts me about 2 years,these were bought to replace an identical pair.i don't think you can beat them for the price.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: These are good for gardening but I was disappointed in how heavy they are in ireland it rains to much and I'm in countryside I wanted a wellyboots I could walk in these are great for keeping rain of your feet but heavy than I thought. However good wellyboots despite the weight

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: Excellent wellies.... i think someone mentioned they are 'generous' in size and this is true... either a size smaller or thick socks should solve it but for pottering around the garden they are finewell recomendedian

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: Perfect. Brilliant great quality and fit. Totally waterproof.  Bought these for a family member but have previously ordered these in a smaller size for myself.  Happy with both purchases and mine have lasted really well and still waterproof.  Thank you.

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: Good price but terrible product. If your going to wear once a week for 5mins then they will probably be ok. For me they lasted 2 months then split contacted seller but your warranty is basically the returns period. You really do get what you pay for!

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: Bought for doing the garden and generally for jobs involving the power hose. Very happy with them, I had a more expensive pair made for trespass which weren't rubber, they lasted a year before perishing. Last Dunlop pair lasted 8 years before I wore them out, great value

Product: Dunlop Compass Flick Bell
Review: I returned this items caus it was too big, but I haven't got any conformation from the seller (I did one 10 days ago). Seller does not reply my emails.

Product: Women Men Fur Slippers Memory Foam Fluffy Slip-on House Suede Lined/Anti-Skid Sole, Indoor & Outdoor
Review: I've only had these for a few days but so far so good.They are very cosy and hug my feet nicely. They look lovely and seem good quality.They aren't as sqyishy5on the soles as some of the memory foam ones but I knew this from reviews and it isn't a problem for me, I still find them comfy.The sizing was worrying me due to so many reviews saying how big they are..... well I can say that the medium size... 5.5-6.5uk is spot on! I'm a UK 6 and they fit me perfectly with a little room in the length so that if I'd been a 6.5uk then they would still fit.I've given 4 stars because I can't yet comment on the durability of these and whether they'll hold their shape.  I'll try to update in a few months time.

Product: Women Men Fur Slippers Memory Foam Fluffy Slip-on House Suede Lined/Anti-Skid Sole, Indoor & Outdoor
Review: When these slippers first arrived I was delighted with them - very soft and warm and seemed good quality for the price. However, after 6 weeks of use, they went from being a snug fit to being way too loose.  My feet were sliding around in them (i don't think there is any memory foam as they're now completely flat) and I kept tripping over.  I now can't wear them as my feet feel completely unsupported and they started to come apart after I put them in the wash.  Only buy these slippers if you don't intend on using them that much and don't need arch support.  They are really fluffy and warm.

Product: Women Men Fur Slippers Memory Foam Fluffy Slip-on House Suede Lined/Anti-Skid Sole, Indoor & Outdoor
Review: I'd bought a pair for my niece and thought they were excellent quality looking at them. So decided to but myself a pair, (I'm on a  quest to find the perfect slippers) got the navy pair, they're lovely. My feet don't overheat in the fluffyness...  Only negative and it's a small one I find them wide. I'm a size 4 and bought the 3.5-5 size  and to me they're too big my feet move around alot in them. Not the perfect slipper for me but pretty close. I'll keep them till they wear out but don't think I'd get them again.

Product: Women Men Fur Slippers Memory Foam Fluffy Slip-on House Suede Lined/Anti-Skid Sole, Indoor & Outdoor
Review: The slippers were extremely cosy and comfy for the first couple of days. However, within a week they’re already less comfy, so I very much doubt that there’s any memory foam in them, which is very disappointing. Stitching on the sole is already starting to fray as well. Don’t know how hard wearing they will be at this rate of going. Won’t be buying again!

Product: Women Men Fur Slippers Memory Foam Fluffy Slip-on House Suede Lined/Anti-Skid Sole, Indoor & Outdoor
Review: This fits a little large however it still cosy and an absolute bargain for the price for it. I cannot live without these slippers. The memory foam makes it feel like you’re stepping on clouds, and the colour is super chic! I have had so many compliments from guests and even had some friends buying the exact same pair!I would recommend getting a size or a half size down due to it being wide fit, however they are amazing quality. They are like UGG slippers but for a bargain price! They are lasting really well!

Product: Women Men Fur Slippers Memory Foam Fluffy Slip-on House Suede Lined/Anti-Skid Sole, Indoor & Outdoor
Review: I ordered the UK size 7-8, and my heel was at the end of the sole with my toes pushed in tight at the front. My actual shoe size is a 7.5, but these are most definitely not suitable for a size 8. They are soft and comfortable, but there is no extra room if you like a looser fit. Hope my review gives you an accurate guide.

Product: Women Men Fur Slippers Memory Foam Fluffy Slip-on House Suede Lined/Anti-Skid Sole, Indoor & Outdoor
Review: Being a size 6 i chose the 5.5/6.6 and they fit perfect, they are so comfy and warm the sole is about 10mm thick and sturdy. They arrived early and were well packaged.  Very happy with them and would definitely recommend them to family & friends.

Product: 3/4 Orthotic Insole Support Helps Weak and Fallen Arches Also Plantar Fasciitis
Review: I have worn orthotic insoles for around 25 years and expected these to fulfil their role in replacing my old ones from another manufacturer. However, despite ordering my normal size I found the insoles to be slightly narrower than my old ones. I decided this was within tolerance to allow me to try them. The left insole does not seem much different to my old ones and I was hardly aware of it in my shoe, I would have expected to feel an improvement in the support compared to my old ones as they were new so was disappointed. As for the right insole it was very uncomfortable, there appears to be a lump under the outer part of my foot and too close to my heel. The arch support like the left was disappointing as I could feel no difference to the old one. Over all the material seems softer than I would have expected so its durability is in question. Though with the level of discomfort on my right foot it is unlikely I will persist in trying to wear them so will have to look for an alternative.

Product: 3/4 Orthotic Insole Support Helps Weak and Fallen Arches Also Plantar Fasciitis
Review: I brought theses on recommendation of my chiropractor. These are good and I have noticed a shift in the biomechanics of my body after using these for around a month. I have flat feet and have probation in my feet and these have aided in helping relieve pain I was experiencing. I hope these continue to improve my condition. I purchased the 3/4 rather than the full length as the full length were very uncomfortable and did not allow my feet to fit properly inside the shoe.

Product: 3/4 Orthotic Insole Support Helps Weak and Fallen Arches Also Plantar Fasciitis
Review: Such a great design. Fits well in the shoe with an extremely slim fit design. In some shoes it may look as though it’s too small or will move around a lot, but it isn’t the case. The arch is fairly solid, so provides perfect arch support. Some insoles are too flaccid and provide little support when weight is applied into the shoe, you don’t have this issue with these.

Product: 3/4 Orthotic Insole Support Helps Weak and Fallen Arches Also Plantar Fasciitis
Review: I bought these after hunting for insoles suitable for people with high arches. Having done an online self assessment through treadlabs.com (that says I have extra high arches requiring a £45 insole from the US), I went looking for less pricey insoles. These 3/4 Orthotic Insole Supports on Amazon are 1/5 of the price and do a reasonable job if all you are looking for is some extra support for high arches; however they still leave a gap between the arch support and my instep when I am standing.These are better than nothing in a period when it is difficult to access resources and products.

Product: 3/4 Orthotic Insole Support Helps Weak and Fallen Arches Also Plantar Fasciitis
Review: I was a bit suspicious, because they were so cheap. However, they are much, much, better than others I have used. They fit beautifully in my shoes, they are comfortable and today, when I changed shoes and forgot to put them in I was in pain as soon as I got to town. I've just ordered another pair.

Product: 3/4 Orthotic Insole Support Helps Weak and Fallen Arches Also Plantar Fasciitis
Review: The insoles are exactly as I expected. The xs size fit beautifully into my rather small shoes and leave plenty of room in the toe box (which was already quite small). The heel lift means that I feel my heel is coming out of the shoe somewhat so I don't think these will be suitable for all shoes. I haven't given them a full trial yet so not sure if they are going to help with my problems, but they feel like they give a lot of arch support.

Review: To me when my plantar fasciitis is sore i cannot wear these as they really are quite hard and you must pick a particular type of shoe to put them in or you have no room for your foot thus making shoe too tight

I have taken to wearing my shoes all the time in the house now too to get the full benefit of the corrections they are making.Excellent purchase, can't yet comment on how long they will last.

Product: Punched Pockets A4, 100 Poly Pockets
Review:
Shambles of a product. Turns up in a cardboard box, loose. So you can't easily thread into a ring binder. I'm here with 7x100 of them and have to thread them in batches of 3 or 4 so the holes line up. No idea if durable or sturdy. But would never buy again and would return if I didnt have to queue up at post office. Normally buy from elsewhere and comes in plastic packaging and holes line up an absolute treat. Won't be taking that for granted again, no sir-ee.
Never written any review anywhere before but the state of this motivated me to. Who knew I was so passionate about plastic wallets. Absolute shambles.

Product might be fine if you want to put documents in them and never file them an the way the product was designed to be used.

If you're reading this review before purchasing this administration nightmare then you're welcome as I've saved you hours of wasted time.
Stuff like this is everything that's wrong with capitalism.
Also they look like the cheapest, lowest quality version of this product I've ever seen. And I include the IRP-620's AND that time someone posted me an invoice in a resealable sandwich bag in that. Shambles.

Product: Skechers Women's Summits Trainers
Review: On average we walked 25- 30k steps a day whilst in Orlando.  My 2 pairs of Skechers at the time got me through 2 weeks, I came home, threw them in the cool wash and they served me another 15 months after that.  So replacing them was hard, mainly because I didn't like the other styles of Skechers out there.  These ones are my kind of style and fit to my feet like a glove (I am a 5 in some places and a 6 in others, I order 5 in Skechers).  Here's looking forward to another Orlando trip, and I shall be purchasing the same in a different colour.

Product: Skechers Women's Summits Trainers
Review: Always wear sketchers and this type. Nice shade of green but quite wide fitting and feel bulkier to wear than all my other sketcher trainers and so not getting worn as much as I'd hoped. Good price compared to shop prices.

Product: Skechers Women's Summits Trainers
Review: This is my 4th purchase of this style of summit trainers. I bought these to walk to work and to wear whilst on my feet at work. They are very comfortable and help to ease my heel pain. I do not need to add any extra heel support and wear with or without socks. I am a size 5 and they are a perfect fit.

Product: Skechers Women's Summits Trainers

Product: Skechers Women's Summits Trainers
Review: Bought these as a replacement to my well worn previous pair which had lasted a while but were on their last legs.  Good value for money and cheapest replacement I could find.  I find these trainers really comfortable and can walk quite a long way in them, the memory foam can be a bit bouncy when initially worn but they soon settle into a very comfortable fit for your foot!

Review: Excellent trainers, had sketchers before and these are to replace the old ones. So happy that I went on to order two more pairs for friends who’ve seen me wearing them and they are just as pleased  as me. I work with horses so I’m on my feet sometimes 14 hours a day and they are certainly the comfiest footwear I’ve ever had. Throw in washing machine and they’ll come up brand new.

Review: I love the comfort and fit of these clogs. They look good, are perfect for nipping out into the garden or to the kerb, and are so easy to wipe or rinse clean. I not sure how long they will last as they are made from quite lightweight expanded foam/plastic, but if they only last 6 months they're excellent value for the very reasonable rpice.

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: My old clogs were well past their sell-by date so decided to treat myself to a new pair of harden clogs; my requirements were that they should be lightweight, strong, washable and a good/comfortable fit.  After perusing what was on offer out there on the market, I plumped for a pair of dark blue, Lakeland Active Lorton Garden Clogs.  Ordering and delivery process was fine.  As soon as they arrived, the weather was nice and were unpacked, on my feet and out in the garden very quickly!  Just what I wanted and wished for so very, very pleased.

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: This is my 3rd  pair of these clogs.  My original green pair I now keep for outdoor wear and change at the back door for the new blue pair which I keep for indoor wear.  My  slippers are virtually redundant.  I love them.  Such a good fit and feel secure too even up a ladder (naughty I know). I am a UK size 10 and these are a 44. I could probably go a size bigger but experience shows that, with time, they 'give' a little and mould well to your feet.  Clogs are a great idea - no bending down to tie and untie shoelaces every time you want to change.  The Dutch invented them and we all know what clever clogs the Dutch are.

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: Only been wearing these for 2 days now and so dissatisfied. They are not suitable for gardening at all!Im either constantly having to pull out thorns which easily penetrate the sole, or having to unfold the inner sole which is so flimsy it just folds up under your foot. Only suitible for pottering around on a patio, at best!

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: I originally bought a size 5, my usual size, and this was too big and loose,. So I’d say they are slightly oversized. The quality is good, however .. So, I bought a second pair, thinking this was the solution. But sadly, these a a little too snug. So, i’m Clearly in between sizes, and this is a bit of an issue. I’m keeping both, as returns in Lockdown present some difficulties for us. I’ll adjust depending on socks in winter or barefoot in summer.

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: These were bought for my elderly father in attempt to stop him from going outside in his slippers then trailing muck through the house. They fit well and are easy for him to get on and off. He dud say they felt a bit rough inside but he had no socks on when he tried them on. My dad is a very poor walker but the slight lip at the heel of these clogs meant they stayed in place. Hopefully he’ll start wearing them...I may have to nag or hand him the carpet cleaner!

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: I got these just for small trips out to the garage or compost bin. They are very light but don’t feel cold. Perfect for quick trips out to the garden without having the hassle of wellie on and off.

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: Have been outside in them in horrible weather and my feel stayed warm and dry.  This first pair now live by my back door - I may well buy another pair for when I go out at the front.  The only problem I had was with the appalling carriers, who threw the parcel over the fence, where it was impaled on my grape vine in full view of anyone passing the house.  Had I been away, it might well have been stolen.

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: Lakeland Active Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs - just what the doctor ordered to keep my feet dry in the garden... ordered shoe size but they are slightly large  which is OK for the 30 seconds or so i wear them in the garden taking rubbish to the bin's . Definitely not OK for walking any distance.

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: Sorry to say these are not for me. They are not very comfortable nor very flexible and quite wide for a size 4 but there again, you get what you pay for.  I will be keeping them but only because my old ones have split and l can afford to buy a more comfortable pair. There was no problem with the supplier as the shoes came in record time.

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: Far too big, as others have said. Bit flimsy but OK. Had to spend money on insoles6

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs

I’ve had a pair of similar shoes for years but they were looking shabby.

What’s to lose nothing much
And they came like lightning!

Product: Lakeland Active Lorton Garden, Kitchen & Work Clogs
Review: Product arrived well packaged and in good order. These are lightweight clogs and do not have much grip so I would be careful about wearing them in wet and muddy weather. I don't think they would be up to much heavy work in the garden, ie digging but they are ideal for those days when you just want to potter about and do a bit of weeding. I made the mistake of paying heed to the answer to a question on Amazon regarding sizing. Another customer said they were small in size so make sure to buy a size bigger. I did. I bought a 7 instead of a 6. The clogs are too big so I would say order the size you normally wear.  They are broad fitting, which is great for me, but may be something to consider. I can wear the size 7s over my slipper socks so they won't be going to waste. I will be ordering another pair in the correct size for me. Overall I am very pleased with the product.

Review: I don't often write glowing reviews but this really is a gorgeous card.  It's not too large (18 x 13 cm, or approx 7 x 5 inches) and very well made, with lovely flower illustrations on the front.  It has two extra leaves inside, each with more flower decorations on, and enough room to write a message on the right-hand side one.  It can be sent in the UK, using a regular-sized stamp (not the larger, more expensive ones) and really is top quality.  I'm using it for an elderly lady and two cousins, all of whom are gardening fans.  I was so pleased with the single card I've received today that I've ordered the other two cards today, also.  Very satisfied with the item.

Product: Merrimen Roll of Quality Bubble Wrap - Small Bubbles (500mm x 100m)
Review:
Great roll of bubble wrap, perfect for moving your delicates.

Only criticism I have
The delivery driver left it out side in the rain , I live in a small block of flats and at the time I was restricted with illness it was only because my son visited and saw it outside he thought I bet that's for mum!

It could have been taken or blown away in the storm we had at the time, as I'm by the coast.

Product: Merrimen Roll of Quality Bubble Wrap - Small Bubbles (500mm x 100m)
Review:
The bubble wrap is priced according to its quality - low.

The upside is there is a lot of it, which was required as the wrap is thin resulting in multiple wrapping of items.

I used in a house move. If you're after good quality protection, avoid. If you're content with the price, be prepared to accept lower quality.

Product: Merrimen Roll of Quality Bubble Wrap - Small Bubbles (500mm x 100m)
Review: I had already written complaining about where the delivery had been left... but this is about the product. I bought this and similar from EBay. I have to say that I’m using them for moving house. Whilst both pop far too easily, this one is of slightly better quality whilst only being £1 more in cost. So if they can assure that it will at least be left at my door, I will buy it again!

Product: Merrimen Roll of Quality Bubble Wrap - Small Bubbles (500mm x 100m)
Review: Bought as we are moving house soon. Didn’t think this would be enough to wrap all our fragile items in but able to get a lot boxed.Great as you can just cut of size you need. Bought along with packing boxes. Will definitely buy again as I still have quite a few items to pack!

It's bubble wrap! Not a huge amount more to say except:

* It did what I wanted.
* It was a good price compared to the extortionate amount they wanted in my local post office
* It is a little thinner than some I have used but it is OK.

I am a happy bunny!

Product: 25 x Strong Large Grey Mailing Postal Bags 17 x24" Mailers
Review: 25 Strong Large mailing postal bags are bigger than I expected and great value for money. This are great, they are a lovely large size. I am very happy with these as they are big enough that I can fit a lot in. I managed to fit one item that shipped as a medium parcel so I was very happy, but they are also smooth enough that I could easily fit something smaller and just fold the bags over. I am very happy with these.

Product: 25 x Strong Large Grey Mailing Postal Bags 17 x24" Mailers
Review: We needed mailing bags fast and not too expensive and these plus Prime hit the nail on the head.They're HUGE, but versatile enough to go over UK post office small parcel shoe boxes and fold down to large letter size for clothing.Contrary to a lot of negative experiences, ours arrived with a faint aroma of eco-doom plastic - it's what that are - but certainly nothing like cigar smoke or so strong it seemed likely to contaminate the contents or need airing before use.Would definitely re-buy.

Product: 25 x Strong Large Grey Mailing Postal Bags 17 x24" Mailers
Review: I bought these large bags to post some large coats I'd sold on ebay. The coats, including a size large padded coat, fitted in the bags. The sticky seal seemed secure and the seams of the bag felt strong. The bags didn't smell as I've read elsewhere. They were delivered quickly. At the price I paid, I'd say they are extremely good value.

Product: 25 x Strong Large Grey Mailing Postal Bags 17 x24" Mailers
Review: I have purchased this set of mail bags on 3 occasions. They are strong and thick and large enough to get most things into that I end up selling on eBay or the odd return. Everything always seems to arrive in tact and it’s easy to stick or sellotape a label to as well.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: At first it was a bit scratchy, but became very comfortable overnight. The black, red, green Bond colours seem to penetrate through the sepia mist that hangs over me. The only drawback is that I can't keep the caseback as close to the pit of my forewrist as I would have liked, but that is an issue with Nato straps in general and this is my first. In terms of how much joy is purchased for the cost of this item, it really puts my wife into perspective, of whom I am considering replacing with a modest Nato strap collection.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: I have used the original metal bands on all my watches (Omega & Breitling) for years but my weight tends to go up and down these days and the band can be comfortable one month and unwearable a few months later, I then diet and they are fine again. I got fed up with this and was going to change to Leather straps until I stumbled across Nato straps. I didn't understand the appeal at first but decided to try one  and I'm glad I did. They are really adjustable and comfy, the range of colours means I can find a colour scheme to match any timepiece and honestly they look impressive once in place. There are two ways to wear these bands, that I know of, the traditional has the backle to the side of the watch face, that isn't for me, it is too bulky when wearing a suit and cufflinks, so I use the second method where the buckles fasten in the traditional place under the wrist. It's neater and there are plenty of tutorials on YT so you can find the way you prefer. I know it sounds daft to replace a stainless watch band that cost a lot of money with a canvass strap but they really do work and look good too. I'm getting a few of these from Sniper Bay as they can be changed in seconds to change the look to match what I am wearing. I can find no fault so far with these great Nato's from Sniper Bay. The spring pin tool is an added bonus but I'd prefer the choice as I now have 3 of them but it means I'll never be without one if I need one and you can always give one to a friend who doesn't have one. So far they are a 5 star product.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: I was seeking my first NATO strap for my Hamilton Khaki Field and didn't want to spent too much on one. I came across this one and it looked pretty good, it arrived and I was fairly pleased. It's very thin, comfortable and easy to attach and detach from the watch and is more than capable of being submerged in water. Although there is decent stitching around the watch, not glue like other poorly made straps, I did notice that after just a few days of wearing it, the end of the buckle had started fraying. So this may be an indication that it won't last that long. However, only time will tell and it of course depends on what you use the watch for and how often you wear it. Nonetheless, it's a solid strap with a range of different colours, but I did get the black.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: I have bought a second of these watch straps because I liked the first so much.The strap is easy to thread through the watch and is easy to clean (I put the strap through the washing machine with my other laundry, but  wrap the strap in a sock). Ease of cleaning is important, especially since I bought a pale blue/white strap. I have put 5 stars against "durability", although, in truth, I have not had this strap for very long.  However, the strap is strong and the watch fits securely on it.  I have also worn it every day.  So far there have been no problems at all, and no early signs of wear and tear.Another big attraction of these watch straps is the range of colours available.The seller has despatched the item very promptly.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: If they moved the decimal point in the price one place to the left, then perhaps that would ok. I've had other brands of nato strap - Timefactors, Watchgecko etc that put this strap well into the weeds. The TF straps are even £2 cheaper!!! The hundreds of positive reviews for this band are living on another planet. Or they are something else...MATERIAL:  stiff, thin, like the straps used to bind large boxes/crates of supermarket baked beans etc. I'm not joking.METAL PARTS:  cheap to the eye and the touch, flimsy feeling.STITCHING: ditto.OVERALL:  Phenomenally bad value for money. They are a watch strap to be fair, but not for that price.PRICE: Actually, on second thoughts, best move the decimal point two places.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review:
I needed a couple of replacement watch straps & almost went with a *much* cheaper version on eBay again that, from previous experience, I knew would be functional.

As there was an offer by buying 3 of them though, I thought I'd give them a shot - & they're clearly of a much higher quality, being noticeably thicker, & are far more expensive looking - even comparing the plain black one to a cheap (<50% the price) plain black one that I had already... …& the packaging was both smart/functional &, with no plastic, completely recyclable.

Otherwise, I personally I found the included tool for removing the pins to be a little too fiddly - & since I was ditching the old 2 piece straps then it was far quicker to just cut them off... Well, spending time getting the knack of something that I'm unlikely to need to do again for years is pointless - & if I ever needed to replace the pins then these single piece straps just get threaded through so wouldn't get in the way.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: I’ve not used a NATO strap before and thought I’d try one out on my Seiko Turtle.It was easy to fit and has really transformed how the watch looks. This strap is great quality and I’m considering getting some more in different colours (I went for the bond black/grey). It’s also super comfortable to wear.It doesn’t come with any instructions on fitting, but it’s simple enough to do if you’re familiar with popping the spring bars off of the lugs. It actually comes with a spring bar tool, which is nice. There’s information online re: the different ways you can thread a NATO, but it’s simple to work out.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: I decided that the 18mm Nylon NATO Watch Strap by Sniper Bay is a first-class product and a great addition to my Lorus field watch, the strap has a nice feel and do not carry any bulk to the watch despite having a double mourning point. Another nice point is that the buckle is on the side of the band so it doesn't catch on the surface when at the keyboard highly recommended.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: Simple and effective packaging, a perfectly good strap with quality metalware.It isn't as soft as some other strap types, but these are generally much more expensive due to the materials used.The price is good for the quality offered and it doesn't seem like marked up cheap tat.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: I fitted this to a marathon GSAR which is not a particularly big watch - however even on this the length of the top part of the strap with the clasp is far too short, meaning the watch fastens on the corner of your wrist bone rather than the underside of your arm. I don’t have particularly big wrists so I’d be surprised if most men don’t have this issue

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review:
It’s a well-made NATO strap; soft nylon, heated holes and edging, strong stitching (doubles) and solid buckles.

It comes with a spring bar removal tool, good for the job but I’d have liked a spare pin or two either instead of or in addition to.

It’s a brilliant strap and well-made. Don’t hesitate.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: This is a very nice and unusual strap as it comes with a sliding device which allows it (in theory) to be fitted easily onto the watch.  It was a bit of a fiddle (took me about a minute for each side), but then locked in.  My only worry is that the lugs are not very long and don't seem to fit very far into the watch so I don't know how strong they will be.Hopefully the will be OK. Only time will tell.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: I’d always stuck with the steel bracelets fitted to my watches as standard but, after getting a little fed up with damaging said bracelets at work, I decided to try out a couple of NATO straps. The truth is that I am now converted - they are very comfortable and hold my watches in position far better than the bracelets. They also look quite good as well - I tried to match them to the watches’ faces (sorry). Longevity is an unknown quantity so far but at this price, I have no complaints.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: Used to replace original watch band.  This one is stronger and nicer to look at than the original.  Only took a couple of minutes to fit.  Do like that it has plenty of holes so that adjustment can be made perfectly.  Altogether very impressed.  Thankyou.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: Very nice strap. Looks well when paired with a sports watch. Nylon strap is light and comfortable in different weather conditions. Easy to attach to a watch. Product was delivered promptly and well packaged. Price is reasonable. All in all the strap represents an economical way to change the look of a watch.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: Very well constructed with all edges heat sealed, feels like it will last years.  Strap is a little shorter than I would've like as there's only a very short strap end to fold back on itself through the retaining buckle (and I dont have particularly large wrists!). With a bit of fettling I was able to adapt it to fit an old Swatch watch and it looks great. Really happy with the product and postage/ delivery.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: What's not to like. A very well made and extremely comfortable nato. I have had several nato's from sniper Bay and they have all met my expectations. I would certainly recommend that anyone looking for a replacement strap look at these. The come in sizes from 18mm, 20mm and 24mm.
