Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: The watch strap was a replacement for the one on my work watch.  It can get a bit oily and dirty at work, and the NATO nylon strap is easily be removed for a clean up in the washing machine (usually zipped inside boiler suit pocket).

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: It's a great value NATO strap. The nylon looks and feels good, the hardware is good, it fits well. They do plenty of different colours and it arrived in a couple of days. If you like NATOs then there's no reason not to get one of these.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: Great watch strap so far for the price, very comfortable on a citizen eco drive. Haven't rated durability yet but it seems very good material and it's stitched glued and heat sealed. Great range of styles as well. The spring bar tool is appreciated as well.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: I'm quite pleased with the NATO strap - it seems reasonable quality and is certainly a good fit on my Duro's 22mm lugs.  I'd prefer it if it was less stiff but maybe it will soften over time.

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review: Ever since a gang of nasty pickpocket types spotted my Rolex Explorer II on the tube and tried to relieve me of it I've been very conscious of the risks of wearing expensive watches in a country where I have less legal rights than the criminal.  I have since found that this NATO type strap is the answer to dressing down an expensive watch.  Nobody ever looks twice at it any more, except me, but that's the kind of shallow person I am.  I bought several which was a good job as they are not as robust as I had expected; the nylon begins to fray after a while but for £12 they look the part and are a bit of a bargain...

Product: Sniper Bay Nato Strap Watch Strap – Nato Watch Straps for Men and Women with Military-Grade Nylon, Stainless Steel – 18mm, 20mm, 22mm, 24mm Wrist Strap Widths
Review:
This is a reasonable watch strap for the price you pay BUT the durability is poor!

I have been wearing my watch for only ONE day with this nato strap and already the punched holes are beginning to fray as is the end of the strap. Clearly the holes and end have not been glued or heat sealed properly. Also the strap itself is fairly long and as such you may find you have to fold the strap back on its self if you have thinner wrists (this happens with all nato strap and isn’t a fault with this make).

However the strap did arrive in good time with a well made lug spring removal tool. The strap is also super comfortable to wear and looks good on most dive watches (as with my Vostok Amphibia)

Overall you get what you pay for I guess.

Product: TOMS Men's Alpargata Loafer Flat
Review: I now own three pairs of these Toms slip-ons in black, white and brown, and have worn them for years.Numerous complaints can be found in reviews of Toms about them being a size, or half-a-size, too small. It's all nonsense, I'm pleased to report. On first slip-on they can be fractionally tight, but as with any shoe, it's a breaking-in process. After a few days they'll stretch to comfortably wrap around your size with no blisters. If you intentionally buy a larger size you'll end up overcompensating.Buy your size and enjoy.

Review: I swear these are the first toms this didn’t fit right out of the box. As most people have said- there’s something about the Black Toms. i bought these for a trip I was leaving for in two days. Instead of  of returning them I decided to watch a few YouTube videos on stretching canvas dealers. I decided to go with the steam method. I just stuffed the shoes with some face clothes and ran them over some steam to loosen the canvas. After maybe 5 min of 30 sec intervals. I immediately put the Toms on with a thicker sock to help stretch them more. I wore them around for maybe 2 hours while watching tv and occasional moving my feet around in them. After I restuffed the shoes with face clothes until my trip two days later and they were golden!

I'd run if there was a wild boar.. or probably a gorilla) These are my go-to-closed-toe-shoe for work/nights out/dog walks/pretty much anything that might require a closed toe. Product: 5 Pieces Watchmakers Jewelers Screwdrivers Set with 5 Replacement Tips
Review: I bought these as I have a Strapcode bracelet that has screw-links and needed a set of very small screwdrivers. These were fine. They Cost £6, they arrived a day before expected and I was able to size the bracelet without a problem. I was glad that there was a set of five screwdrivers as it gave me options to select the most appropriate size.

Product: 5 Pieces Watchmakers Jewelers Screwdrivers Set with 5 Replacement Tips
Review: Cheap rubbish, no watchmaker would be within a hundred miles of this quality. Tips soft, screw tightens for tips damaged. Look elsewhere for the real thing.

Product: 5 Pieces Watchmakers Jewelers Screwdrivers Set with 5 Replacement Tips
Review: There are no cross headed or Philips type bits...The delivery time was far to long...The visual look of this product, is nothing like the photoshop advertised picture, seen on amazon website...The overall quality is basic and mediocre at best...

Product: 5 Pieces Watchmakers Jewelers Screwdrivers Set with 5 Replacement Tips
Review: Wasn't sure from the pictures how small these screwdrivers were, as I really needed a very tiny, well made set of screwdrivers to undo very delicate screws in a very expensive watch. I wasn't disappointed, these screwdrivers are simply the highest quality, extremely small heads but handles ideal to hold, and the rotating top was just perfect. Come in a nice plastic wallet, with a cloth too. Can't recommend highly enough. Delivery was extremely fast too.

Product: 5 Pieces Watchmakers Jewelers Screwdrivers Set with 5 Replacement Tips
Review: I purchased these as a temporary measure to make a bracelet adjustment on a watch. They are cheap, and they aren't exactly the greatest quality but they do the job. If you are planning on using these frequently, then don't buy them - go for a Burgeon set. If it's to make a couple of small adjustments then these are more than capable for the job. Adjusting the bracelet was fine, but if I was to be working on more delicate parts, or internal components I would avoid using these.

Product: 5 Pieces Watchmakers Jewelers Screwdrivers Set with 5 Replacement Tips
Review: I'm really pleased with this screw driver set and wanted a 1mm screw driver to take out links in my new watch strap which has screw pins rather than the type you punch or press out. All the watchmaker screw drivers I owned were too big.

Product: 5 Pieces Watchmakers Jewelers Screwdrivers Set with 5 Replacement Tips
Review: I don't know if the batch that i received missed the hardning process of manufacture, but when i received this and tried to take out the links of my watch, the metal was not hard, sturdy and brittle like it's supposed to be after the process of hardening - but instead it bent when I turned it and developed rough edges, which could potentially have been very dangerous for scratching up my new watch!!! Would not recommend or buy again. Awaiting a response from manufacturers.

Product: VTech 193853 Kidizoom Smart Watch, Pink ,1.5 x 4.6 x 22.4 cm
Review:
Initially this looked well made kids watch. My 5 year old liked it too. However, this is not reliable at all. The touch screen stopped working just after 1 year (just outside the warranty period). My daughter rarely used it and always handled with care. It never came in contact with water or was never dropped to floor etc.

I hoped I could factory reset it to make touch screen work again as it seems to be a software problem. The worst thing is that one can not factory reset it without using touch screen. You can not do much using two side buttons. Even this can not be factory reset through computer.

I tried to contact VTech support and they simply refused to help due to expired warranty period. Avoid buying this.

Product: VTech 193853 Kidizoom Smart Watch, Pink ,1.5 x 4.6 x 22.4 cm
Review: Unfortunately not a great purchase. Plastic plug on side (charging point) would not stay in and eventually popped out altogether leaving a gaping hole which on a watch for a child is always going to be a recipe for disaster when washing hands etc. Returned due to this and wouldn’t repurchase. My 6yo wasn’t very impressed even though it was what she had asked for, too bulky and she didn’t find it easy to navigate.

Product: VTech 193853 Kidizoom Smart Watch, Pink ,1.5 x 4.6 x 22.4 cm
Review: I was a little uneasy after looking at the reviews. But so far there's been no issues for us with this watch. Spent a good bit of time with it myself and it's really a good product. Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review: Great little set. Had the back of my watch off in seconds. What I didn't realise though is that it takes a lot of work to get the back on again! Brute force didn't work so if it helps here's how I did it: I lined up the pins, put the watch face down on a towel on a table, then used the rounded end of a 4kg hand weight, gently pushing down while rocking the weight slightly. Got it at last!

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review: I recommend this product, it's great.  This Kit is perfect, I am faithful to my watches and when they ran out of battery I had a very bad time.  I didn't want to buy more watches but I had an idea.  Look for a set that had the instruments I needed for my watches because the covers are non-threaded and I bought this kit and I changed the battery of my watches myself.  With this toolkit it was really easy, bring everything as in the description.  Base to flatten the clock and not hurt yourself when using sharp tools. It's perfect for me. Thanks.

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review: Quite pleased when the kit arrived but disappointed to find that the adjustable tool for removing slotted watch backs is quite useless. I bought the set to remove the back of a Swiss Hanowa,which is not a large watch, with slots 35mm apart across the diameter of the watch back , but the widest the tool will open is 33mm. Not only that, but the adjustment of the third socket by twisting the tool handle jammed and now won't move at all. The other problem with this tool is securing the pins into the holes - they just fall out when the tool is held in the position necessary to remove the watch back - unless you are doing everything upside down lying on your back!The tool is a piece of poorly made Chinese junk and most certainly wouldn't be used by a professional as the advertising blurb describes. A pity, because other bits of the kit seem o.k. and come in a handy case, so I  won't be returning it because I bought it at an 'offer' price and the pin removal tools, spare pins, and other tools will be very useful.I've now ordered an Amazon's Choice Zacro adjustable case back opener which opens up to 60mm wide to complement this set. The total cost of this set plus the Zacro tool plus a couple of replacement batteries is still much less than the bill from a jewellers for replacing a watch battery, so I don't feel hard done by because one tool in the set is useless and I'll still award it 3 stars for value for money.

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review: Great little kit. It would have cost me closer to £100 to get two Citizen watch batteries/capacitors replaced. This kit, plus two new batteries from eBay cost me £55.All the bits worked. The twist back tool is a bit fiddly but worked with a bit of patience.Recommended.

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review: I purchased this kit after looking at a few in this price range, this kit appeared to have better quality parts. The strap pun removal tool is larger than the cheap metal ones in most kits and hold the strap better. The fine tweezers are good quality steel and not flimsy and will not bend. Just on a whole the kit is good quality.  I would recommend this kit to any watch enthusiast, or even if you only require one specific tool for a job, just buy the kit as it is great value

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review:
For the price I cannot fault this kit.
I had a new watch delivered and due to the Coronavirus lock-down there is no jewelers operating.
Ordered this kit which arrived in no time at all.
Nice kit with sturdy storage pouch and instructions inside.
I have never tampered with watches before but with this kit after 10 minutes I had removed the links from the new watch and adjusted to fit me perfectly.
Highly recommended, easily worth double what you pay for it.

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review: Pictures of the product state that the adjustable watch back remover, removes backs of up to 55mm. It only removes backs of around 35 to 40mm. After receiving the product I looked back at the photos and it was clear there are two different sized back removers photographed. The one provided and one of a larger back remover. Very misleading.

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review: I bought the kit to be able to fix my own watches rather than pay through the nose at Timpson’s. What a waste of money. The tool to remove the back of the watches doesn’t work at all. It doesn’t grip into the slots on the back of the watches. Some of the bolt-on screws don’t even grip to the tool; even if you turn the setup upside down it won’t work! What a waste of money. The other screwdriver like tools also bent too easily when I used them on a different clip-on watch back. Ended up using a knife to open!I guess I have to eat humble pie and go back to Timpson’s.

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review: I was told by a jeweller that it was going to cost me £68 to send on my watch away to get the battery changed it cost me the price of the kit for 6 quid for a 10 pack of batteries took me 10-minutes to do with this kitAlso as my bracelet was too to big for my wrist managed to take a link out with this kit as well which was going to cost me 25 quid so definitely worth the money

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review: Overall a good wallet of tools for entry level watch repair like changing batteries or removing links to correctly size watch strap.  Instructions are basic but useable.  The blue watch strap adjustment tool is rubbish, to flimsy and you can't adjust for strap thickness.  I used plastic spacers underneath the strap to raise inline with screw push pin.

Product: 147pc Watch Repair Kit Cadrim Repair Tools Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Battery Replacement Tool Kit Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set Carry Case
Review:
Very cheap metal, almost every tool snaped on first try and the ones that didnt snapped on the second, meaning i couldnt fix my watches correctly. So I binned every tool and now ive just got the case and im not too sure what i will use it for, i might store my broken watches in it. Honestly surprised it made it through transit for delivery.

This watch repair kit made me endure at least 48hrs of internal anger and frustration, which impacted my work ethic. The hatred almost consumed me. The thought of this purchase haunted me and chased me through my nightmares. I cannot recommend this repair kit unless you are willing to open your life up to a world of relentless disappointment.

Nice case though 👍

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review:
For an £8 watch you can’t really ask for more. It’s a watch I can wear to work, out camping, biking, washing the car or any other outdoor activity and not have to worry about it breaking. It’s pretty tough and has great water resistance too. It’ll certainly hold up to being rained on, quickly dunked in a bucket of you're washing your car or even a light swim.

It looks great on the wrist and isn’t too big either.

It has a small green light you can activate at the push of a button, admittedly it isn’t going to win any awards but it functions fine and allows you to read the watch in the dark which at this price is all you need!

The instruction manual mentions that it may deviate +/-30 seconds per month and I absolutely have found this to be the case. Even on the first day it had come out of sink with my other clocks/watches by about 2 or 3 seconds and that gap became larger over the next few weeks.

Overall for £8 if you don’t mind the watch being a few seconds out or re-adjusting it every few weeks then you cannot go wrong.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review:
Bought this as I'm an engineer and it's hand to have a stop watch on hand at all times.

I figured as it's so cheap I can wear it and not worry about it breaking. However I am very impressed with the quality and have had no issues the last 3 months.

It is very light weight and comfortable, I always forget I'm wearing it!

It is now my main watch and I'm very pleased with it. The alarm function is also very useful.

The instructions were easy to follow and set up.

Was delivered on time with prime and in a well packaged box.

Would recommend to anyone and everyone!

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review:
This watch is a work of art. Genuinely indestructible, durable battery and thin profile. This is likely the tenth I've claimed for a mind-blowing duration, a large portion of them lost. Got it this time for half a month skippering and it didn't leave my wrist for the whole excursion. Endure being crushed against things, jumping to 12 meters, continually being wet or salty, getting manhandled continually it despite everything looks all-around great. It's the embodiment of usefulness; structured not to look streak however just to work.

1. It is tough, and solid, I have had it now just about four years it despite everything looks and works like new.

2. It tells the date and time and has an alert and stopwatch work. At the point when watches have such a large number of highlights, I find that it convolutes the presentation which is an issue on the off chance that you simply need the date and time passed on to you rapidly, initially.

3. Different watches have highlights that I basically don't require - I don't fly around normally enough to profit by world time, so when I do I can without much of a stretch modify the time myself.

I needn't bother with the watch to be radio aligned, the watch keeps time quite well thus only occasionally do I have to alter it.

4. The watch is little which suits my thin wrist.

5. It is waterproof so except if you expect on swimming routinely with it, it is fine.

Get this watch!

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: I've owned a couple of these now, and I have never had one that managed to last long enough to need the battery changing. Typically less than a year. My opinion is that the only reason to buy one of these is because you've found one in a colour you like and you're looking for some fast fashion! In standard black it's so terrible it's nearly cool. But only nearly. Buy one if you like, it's dead cheap, and it's way better to look at your wrist to tell the time than to pull your phone out.But Casio make good, cheap watches, you just have to pay a little more to hit the sweet spot of value for money. This is too cheap for them to be able to do it. But after these kept failing on me, I bought a Casio AE-1200 WH. I have worn that daily for five years, and it's on its second battery. It also looks really nice, not just in an anti-aspiration hipster way, people have genuinely complimented it, which is fun because you can let them down by saying, "Thanks! It's a Casio." So I recommend you buy a Casio product, just not this Casio product.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Best watch I've ever had. It's actually the first one to use constantly and wear at all times. 100% water resistant I've showered with it and nothing happens to the watch. It's so easy to use and comfortable to wear, I can sleep with it too without being bothered. It also has a little light inside and its great for cycling and working in a classroom (phone-free environment). I think this is the best purchase for 2020 for me - my life has changed completely after buying this watch.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Just arrived and I can’t believe it. It is tiny.  Too small for an adult to wear. This is an “Amazon Choice” product. I expect Amazon. to use their judgement before giving this accolade. It clearly doesn’t mean very much and I suspect it is given without seeing the actual product. Next question is whether I can be bothered to return it? Might just put it straight in the bin.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Got this for my husband as a little gift for starting his new job. I know it sounds like a bit of a rubbish gift to buy him a £9 watch but he loves them. He's owned a few over the years and the strap of his last one broke a few months ago (the watch is still running without a hitch).  I had a look around and it worked out cheaper to just buy a new watch rather than get a new strap for it. So that's what I did.The Casio F-91W is legendary for its low cost and reliability and I can absolutely see why.  To the point that I'm considering one for myself(in neon, of course!), which is quite surprising since I'm partial to Swatch watches.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: You just can’t go wrong with these watches. I got this for work just needed something simple out on site with an alarm for the end of the day. Does the job well and quality is great remember them from back in the early 90s and it’s a trusted brand. Noticed the other day the strap fits my 6 year old sons wrists so I’m getting him the slightly nicer illumination one. Slightly jealous But this does the job I need it to.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: A great low-cost watch packed with features.  Possibly more power than the computer used for the Moon-lander?Once had an expensive watch that got shut in the channel of my car boot - took it off cause didn't want to get it dirty.  Now I use one of these when cleaning/repairing the car.  Cleans up fine afterwards.Main weakness is the strap that seems to break after about 2 years.  It's around the same cost for a new watch as it it is for a replacement watch.  Remove the broken strap from the old one and glued it the shelf above the workbench.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review:
This is a nice watch to wear; light, thin and conveniently small (it doesn't catch on the pockets of tight trousers).

However, if you need to use it in the dark and were expecting the light to make it useable, forget it. The light is pathetic, illuminating only the first digit with the second digit hard to see and the remainder of the digits unilluminated. This in complete darkness, so you can forget it in poor light.

If you don't need to see the time in poor lighting or pitch dark, this watch is worth buying, otherwise, get something else.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: I bout this cheap watch to use as a bedside timekeeper. The light to illuminate the face is very poor and does not illuminate the face enough to be read. In these days of inexpensive LED this is a design fault and a poor show from Casio. A real shame as I bought a very similar watch in HK years ago and the battery outlasted the watchstrap and the watchstrap lasted a long time. Apart from the light problem the watch is fine.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review:
Yes, there are of course better watches. I have watches that are more than 30 times the price of this F-91, in fact I have other Casio watches that are seven times the price....

However, this it the one that is the one that's on my wrist day in - day out. it's robust, accurate, reliable, water resistant and does everything you need a basic watch to do... and it does it all for less than £9!

Quick to set/programme, adequate backlight, easy to use timer function and looks inoffensive enough on your wrist. All for the price of two pints of beer.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Love Casio watches, simple functional and smart.  Bought this one as a back up in case the battery fails during lockdown and not able to get a fresh.  I'd love to see this model in other colours, but black goes with nearly everything.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Ah nostalgia, I only bought this for use as a stop watch on my Strava segments or to wear to one of those particularly fancy soirées one is invited to where making a good impression is a must!It’s great honestly, super fast 3 day delivery in the Uk, simplistic instruction guide that takes 2 seconds to figure out and a warranty to top it off!  Not bad for a little cheapy.Don’t hesitate, great little bit of kit and it makes a super Xmas or bday present for that special someone in your life too. 😂👍🏻👌🏻

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: This is a great every day watch, especially for the price. I had a Vivienne Westwood watch that was aesthetically pleasing but you knew you were wearing it. I had an Armani watch that was so "designer" you couldn't tell if it were 4 or 5 o'clock. This Casio fits nicely, you don't know you're wearing it, and it fits nicely in your pocket when it's convenient to take it off your wrist. And you can read the time at a glance. The torch ain't great but many watches don't even have them anyway so not a function to get down about.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Brilliant watch.  I've had the watch over 2 years now and it's never missed a beat. I work on a fish farm and recently dropped it into a cage out at sea. A month later it was retrieved from 20 metres down and it's still going like new. Small lightweight and very durable. Would definitely recommend

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Great watch at an excellent price. Debated getting an Apple Watch, and realised I just need a watch that did the simple job of giving the time and this does exactly that. Very easy to switch between 12 and 24hr formats. Only slight critique is the light could be a little more brighter. Can’t really complain when your paying the price above though.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: This is the best watch ever made by human beings! I am a luxury watches man. I have a Rolex and an Omega, but this became my favorite watch. Very light weight and very easy to use. I used to have this when I was a kid, so it also adds some good memories :)Highly advised of course!

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review:
So much has already been written about the legendary casio watch but I must show my appreciation for it also.

I'm a big fan of outdoors activities including caving and water sports. This watch has been a faithful companion through all of this.

This is now my third watch, my first died after it had been scraped across rock on many caving trips and then took diving. However, it did not die after these ordeals but rather fought on bravely for another two months before finally dying a warrior's death. My second watch I lost and after an appropriate time of mourning my loss, my third watch arrived this morning.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: I bought the Casio A168W-1 Electro Luminescence for myself before deciding to buy this watch (F91-W) as a gift for my kid (6yo). All I can say is that it's a carbon copy that's lighter, slimmer and doesn't rip the hair out my wrist like the A168W-1. However, the microlight in the F91-W is very weak, it barely illuminates the right side of the watch - it's so bad that my kid genuinely thinks I bought him a fake watch lol.So to summarise, if you intend to use the watch in the dark, then this digital watch ain't the right tool for the job.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: On the face of it this watch ticked all my boxes but I had to wait to buy it, being strapped for cash. Eventually the hour arrived when I could make the purchase and it had to be the Casio; there was no second choice. In terms of how big it is, I have different sized hands and this looks just right on my big hand. So far it’s been great but only time will tell how good it really is. Watch this space.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Not sure if my fault but the watch seems to be made for a child with very small face and the strap just fitting round my wrist.It says adult and I didn’t think to then check face size but hey hoy as just for gym and running will still wear and I can easily read what I need to

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: I purchased this when i was waiting a week or so for my new Smart Watch to arrive. Its TINY. i knew it was going to be small but the strap on this would be good for kids and thats about it. i can JUST do it up on the last hole. not really useful for my large adult male wrists.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Easy to set up, cheap price, nothing complicated, how refreshing! Bought to replace one I had for a year, the strap eventually broke. Only thing is light is really weedy and just lights dimly from side, but good enough for me to check time now and again when very dark. If you want a clear strong light, you will need the more expensive model, but this one cheap and cheerful, less than a tenner.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: I first bought this model of watch many years ago, now needing to have a watch whih I can wear while working in the garden, without fear of damaging it, I bought this one again.  It is sturdy lightweight and is accurate as well as waterproof, though I have not tested it in a swimming pool!

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: My husband has had the exact model for years now and has never had a problem with it, even the battery is long lasting, I have a lot of watches but this one is the most reliable out of all the fancy ones, and other digital ones, looks neat on too.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Use it at work so don't know if waterproof. But ideal for my purpose. Will buy again if this one breaks.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: This watch is awesome. Its a timeless classic, cheap and cheerful. It is perfect for casual wear and pairs nicely with Jeans and a t-shirt.The strap is comfortable and adjustable. It does not itch or irritate my skin like many other watches.As a healthcare worker it is great to have a nice simple watch, for a very reasonable price that I can clean and not worry about losing.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: It looks like a nice inexpensive watch and has lots of positive reviews.Unfortunately it really is very small and the  strap is far to short to be able to secure itself around many adults wrists.Have to return it sadly.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Works well, easy to put an and light weight. But screen is not too bright and can be hard to read due to the size, cannot complain due to the price, Overall a very good basic watch or simple watch for kids to learn to tell the time.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Bought as wanted a cheep watch and I go swimming it was a gamble but works amazing. It’s been in hot and cold chlorine water and works fantastic. Has an hour alarm, I set this up, which is really useful when I do night duty and a light to show the time clearly. For the price I’m overly impressed. Would buy again

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: An absolute classic watch. Cheap but iconic, you simply cannot go wrong with a Casio. Arrived from the seller in great condition, and would definitely recommend. So cheap that I think I might buy some as gifts for people

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: This watch is not too bad. Does the job. However, the small green LED light on my watch seems to only light up half the screen and not the other half so making it difficult to tell the time at night. I'm not sure if that's normal for these kinds of watches due to it's cheap price or if its faulty. Nevertheless, like I said it does the job.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: I bought this watch to replace a more expensive watch after it packed up six months after the guarantee. And the shop wouldn't repair it. Yeah I like this watch. It's perfect for what I bought it for. Back light useless.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review:
I decided to test the watch to its limits, so what did was;
Test 1: Put it inside a washing machine along with some clothes, it survived
Test 2: Then into the tumble dryer, it survived
Test 3: Then into a freezer at -18 degree C for a day, it survived
Test 4: Straight from the freezer put it into a pan of continuous boiling hot water on the hob for 5 minutes, water did get in because of the vast change in temperature from freezer. But I took the watch apart cleaned it, put it together and worked!!

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Ok this is great but it is a mans watch. My dad had one back in the day.This was a gift for my boyfriend and the strap is too short. We have had to give it to our 5 year old. Gutted.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: I have used the same basic Casio design for years because its functionally perfect and just replaced it when things broke down. However, this model I had to return because the stopwatch only goes up to 1 hour, which basically means its useless for my longer runs and other long-duration tasks. Also, its missing the button in the upper right corner for some reason (probably to save on production cost).In conclusion, lesson learned: always check stopwatch maximum duration.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Just buy it. Perfect work watch, if it claps out buy another. Just note this is a small watch and the strap is small too. I thought maybe I had bought a woman's watch but no, apparently it is made to look normal on a dainty wrist.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Bought this as I needed to tell the time whilst out surfing in the freezing North Sea. When I ordered this watch I didn't realise that this watch is only water resistant and not water proof. I've been surfing countless times with this watch on my arm underneath my wetsuit and its still going strong with no sign of water damage. For a watch so cheap I was expecting far less.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Been getting these basic casios for years. Solid workhorse of a little watch.. can't reccommend to anyone more highly. Cheap, longlife, multi-functional, low profile and relatively comfortable as I never realise I'm even wearing mine.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Digital Watch F-91W
Review: Honestly i was struggling so much trying to get women, no luck. Review: I got this to adjust the bracelets on several watches I recently bought, having tried another cheap tool that broke on first use.This one worked brilliantly and I had the job done in a couple of minutes. The base holds different width bracelets securely and the mallet and various sized punches are good quality. Saved me quite a few pounds not having to get a jeweller to do the job.

Product: Watch Repair Kit, Spring Bar Tool Kit with Watch Strap Link Pin Remover/Watch Band Holder/Dual Head Hammer/Watch Cotter Pins/Pin Punches, Watch Repair Strap Removal Kit Ideal for Watchmaker (BlueSet)
Review: This in all honesty is the best little gadget you need but never know you wanted - I bought a new smart watch that come with a metal strap and had no way of taking links out then a short Google search later I come across this item which was delivered next day, has everything you want to shorten straps, repair broken pins and to help you get them in and out of the watch easily. Product: Watch Repair Kit, Spring Bar Tool Kit with Watch Strap Link Pin Remover/Watch Band Holder/Dual Head Hammer/Watch Cotter Pins/Pin Punches, Watch Repair Strap Removal Kit Ideal for Watchmaker (BlueSet)
Review: Took a risk on this to adjust a steel Garmin watch bracelet, almost expected it to be poorly made and fail. How wrong I was, pleasingly, it worked perfectly. Surprisingly sturdy, the pin removal drivers were easily strong enough to do the job. The mini hammer feels nice and weighty. Not sure how long the nylon soft side will last with repeated use. It's well worth the purchase, reality is I'll only use it at most a few times, so no point wasting money on expensive tools used by professionals.  Don't worry, it won't disappoint.

Product: Watch Repair Kit, Spring Bar Tool Kit with Watch Strap Link Pin Remover/Watch Band Holder/Dual Head Hammer/Watch Cotter Pins/Pin Punches, Watch Repair Strap Removal Kit Ideal for Watchmaker (BlueSet)

I highly recommend this kit as it is a very good price and is an essential product.

Product: Watch Repair Kit, Spring Bar Tool Kit with Watch Strap Link Pin Remover/Watch Band Holder/Dual Head Hammer/Watch Cotter Pins/Pin Punches, Watch Repair Strap Removal Kit Ideal for Watchmaker (BlueSet)

Product: Cambridge Jotter, A5 Notebook, Wirebound, Lined, 200 Page, Pack of 3, green
Review:
I use this style of notebook every day for just about everything; I can't abide scraps of paper for notes (too easily lost) so I'm a noteblock avoider. I like to keep everything together but still need to be able to remove sheets when I need a loose sheet of paper.

I thought I'd give this brand a whirl as they're the cheapest on Amazon right now. I usually use Pukka. I'm not horrifically fussy over my notebooks but I do like to use a pretty decent smooth paper with a good thickness, and I want the perforations to work as they should when tearing out sheets. A thicker card style backing is also preferable so I'm not leaning on thin air whilst I write. The addition of holes makes no difference to me as I don't file away anything that I write. But I can see the usefulness for many.

So... This brand compared to my beloved Pukka:
- paper isn't as thick or as smooth. I like writing in this less than I do my Pukka pads.
- backing is seriously thick so you've got some solidity to writing in the absence of a surface to rest on. It's much thicker than a Pukka pad.
- the perforations are all spot on, pages tear out without issue.

And here's why I am only giving 3 stars:
There are no punched holes for putting pages in a file! This doesn't bother me in the least as I don't require punched holes but it will absolutely bother a lot of people especially those who are studying and need this. I triple checked the listing to make sure I hadn't dreamed up the hole punched feature. All three pads are the same so I can only assume that they've changed the features and Amazon have failed to notice or update the listing.

So if you need punched holes (life is too short to be doing it yourself), avoid this brand.

Product: Cambridge Jotter, A5 Notebook, Wirebound, Lined, 200 Page, Pack of 3, green
Review:
I bought these note books because they were cheap if i'm being honest. They seem good quaility for every day use and i have 1 sitting on my desk for everything from doodling while on the phone to making notes of recipes and mats needed in the game i constantly play, Black Desert, and anything else inbetween.

The perforations are a nice touch for rippin out the odd shopping list whatever, and i do not find the perforations weak nor are the pages just falling out.

Now the cons ...
The advert clearly shows the note books punched. And as some reveiwers have stated, their note books were as advertised. I had decided to take one pad and buy an expensive binder/cover for it and use it for more important stuff. I'm glad i never. These would have been useless for that purpose due to the lack of holes. Instead i will go with the more common 6 hole style with much more purchase option.

As a general desk jotter they are great, but lose one star because of confusing conflicting information about the style.

Product: H&S 155pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Removal Adjustment Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Pin Bar Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review:
Got this as a hobby starter as I have a lot of watches just laying around the house, I have had much fun taking apart and cleaning, repairing or in some instances irreparably damaging items however it has been a good fun pastime.

there are however some quality issue with a few of the pieces including the push bars which are about as strong a melted butter and the case back opener which cracked on first use.

for the beginner watch enthusiast you can do a lot worse that this kit.

Product: H&S 155pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Removal Adjustment Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Pin Bar Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review: I was quoted £80 to have my watch looked at, as it was operating sporadically. Lucky it was a skeleton watch, so I could see the internal parts stopping. As an engineer, I could take it apart, buying this set for half the quote.I was glad I did, after I removed the back, the watch restarted and ran happily. It turned out to be the second hand rubbing on the glass, causing it to stop. I removed the whole works, bent the hand sightly, cleaned the glass, and removed some bits of dirt, and put it all back together, using a back case press, (purchased at the the same time). It still runs perfect.Because I have saved money, I now pick up old cheap brand name watches and repair them too.

Product: H&S 155pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Removal Adjustment Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Pin Bar Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review: Not very good quality watch pins are bent and of poor quality case ratchet didn't fit 2 out of my 3 watch backs and not all the fittings are in threes for the ratchet so some are missing but on the case it did fit it would open it but would slip as you have to use an odd fitting

Product: Get Fit Womens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walk Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: Bought these for my sister as a gift for her birthday, however quite disappointed in that they are too small which I could not understand as when I ordered the size chosen was 42 in the ladies style, when they arrived it became apparent that they were far too small and a size 41, it was all a bit confusing as when ordering you can cross reference uk sizes with eu sizes, my sister granted has a wide foot so perhaps these trainers are designed for the slimmer footed female, just as a bit of a test she tried my mens size 42 size 8 uk and they fitted perfectly, her daughter will now make use and I have ordered another larger size for her and again in the ladies size, these are really good running / training shoes nice style & lightweight so fingers crossed second time.

Product: Get Fit Womens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walk Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: Bought these because of the bit of colour regarding sole, and have bought similar in past. Nice bright sole which makes a change from all black for me. So looks are okay not quite as nice as others I have bought as the shoes oooks long and the eyelets go up quite high, whereas I am used to the laces not being quite so many eyelets unless it’s a hi top trainer. Even though I have had for couple of weeks or so, the inner sole has come away and was rubbing my feet as I was out and about so have made them sore. It may not happen to others but thought I would 100% transparent.

Product: Get Fit Womens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walk Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review:
This shoe isn't bad for the price. For me the benefits are they look quite stylish, they are made of manmade materials and the price.

I did need to walk them in. They are not like the more pricey well known brands where a similar style of shoe feels comfy straight away. However after a few days of building up my walking in them they have become more comfortable.

I wouldn't recommend them for sport, though walking to work, walking the dog etc I've had no issues.

They arrived quickly, and not in plastic... thank you.

Product: Get Fit Womens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walk Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review:

Product: Get Fit Womens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walk Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: Great lightweight pair of trainers. Got them for my daughter who is already on her fourth pair of shoes this school year, 3 weeks in (that doesn't sound long but it's half her shoe's life expectancy) and they are still in great condition. The sole and inside are holding together, the heel is still firmly attached (that's almost a miracle), she's says they are comfortable and they dry out really quickly even when they're soaked. They're half the price of the last pair of school shoes and it looks like they'll last twice as long. I'll defiantly buy again - especially since school hasn't noticed they're trainers not shoes!!

Product: Get Fit Womens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walk Gym Shoes Sport Run
Review: Absolutely atrocious.😵 I have had these for just over a month. I walk regularly on gravel roads, and now the external and internal soles have holes through them where little stones come in. These are not for for purpose but it seems impossible to get in touch with the company for a refund. If I could give it a minus star I would! ☹️

Product: Get Fit Womens Mesh Running Trainers Athletic Walk Gym Shoes Sport Run

Review: This is a grand little watch, it's twice the size of my nurses watch and a good bit heavier but that's exactly what I wanted for my go-bag. It clips onto zip pull or strap easily and really has quite a good glow in low light. It seems sturdy enough to take a few knocks but haven't tested how water resistant it might be. It also seems to be keeping time accurately when compared with the other little watch. Overall I'm happy with the purchase.

Product: Clip on Carabiner Luminous Face FOB Watch Digital for Doctors Nurses Paramedics Chefs Sport Unisex Men Women

Product: Clip on Carabiner Luminous Face FOB Watch Digital for Doctors Nurses Paramedics Chefs Sport Unisex Men Women
Review: I have had many fob watches over the years for attaching to my rucksack when out walking as I do not like wearing a watch on those occasions.This is definitely the best one I have had to date. It is extremely robust, the numerals are nice & clear & it is ideal for clipping to my rucksack for easy access.It is worth paying a little more for something that is much more up for the job! Don't waste your time, (pardon the pun), on cheap, plastic imitations that disintegrate within a very short 'time span'.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: I've a vast watch collection and I'm so used to sizing straps I was not expecting to throw this in the bin(it's new home) I got an Archer instead The pin pusher broke and the pin holding the clasp to the strap snapped and the pins are a pain to remove due to the thick paint(I thought for the price it was DLC with screws  silly Me. I'll never buy anything from the maker again it may be solid links etc but if it's held together with bendy rubbish then it's not worth it. Chain is a weak as... And it certainly applies to this POSThese are My views from the 100plus collection of watches I have and the dozens of straps I swap out. I've seen better ones for half the price. The  stamped tin folding clasp should have set the alarms off.. Don't buy!. Go root in my bin 😂

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
I have a Fossil watch that has for a few years had a chunky black silicon strap. Functional but not good-looking. So one day I decided to look for a metal watchstrap. The shops were close in the UK at the time, so I looked on Amazon and found this. The reviews seemed okay, so what the hey? At this price?

The strap is satisfyingly heavy, easy to fit onto the watch because it has the newer hinge bar with the little projection, and it changes the look of the Fossil completely, presenting it on my wrist far more clearly than the silicon strap. The watch face itself looks brighter, cleaner and sharper. Seriously, this strap is AWESOME!

One thing. I removed a couple of links so it fitted my wrist, and let's say that it was a learning experience. I got confused and wound up removing the wrong links from the wrong place. I'm clumsy and don't work with small bits of physical stuff for a living or a hobby. And I did not take the time to look the strap over to familiarise myself with what goes where, and which way round is 'up' for the strap. If you behave like a sensible person, instead of rushing into it, fitting the strap is easy. The fact I could sort out my own mess speaks highly for the strap and the tools they supply.

It is worth the effort. Your chances of finding a strap this good at this price in a high street shop are about zero. Even now the shops are open.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
Overall this strap is great, works well and easy to use (Put on and take off when required).

I bought this strap to replace a magnetic aftermarket one I have had a few years, which has deteriorated as the small metal mesh band was starting to fray and hence catching on clothing, and ending up ruining sleeves. The magnetic strap was very useful, easy to use and put on to the watch, and lightweight. It was super quick to put the watch on your wrist and adjust it to be comfortable. But the magnetic clasp would slip and result in becoming too loose, which was the only drawback.

As the old one had got to a stage that it needed to be replaced, this new strap is a great replacement. Its a little heavier, but is supper easy to put on to my wrist, and looks good on my black smart watch. feels strong and robust, so should last long. I was a little worried that it will catch on my hair, but has not at all.

The strap comes with a handy tool to remove links when required. But when I used it, on one side, it works fine, but on the other side, it did not work. It resulted in me spending £9 at Timpson's to get this adjusted to my size, as the included tool broke. So the strap has turned out to be a little more expensive than expected as the tool to adjust the strap was very cheap and single use only.

Overall, the strap is great, looks and works great, shame the included tool (to adjust the length) is not up to quality of the strap.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
For the price it seems churlish to complain about anything but I knocked a star off because of two things.
The link adjustment tool pin broke very rapidly and I had to purchase another tool. (which was also rubbish).
The bracelet lacks any micro adjustment so I had the option of crazy tight or looser than I would like.
On a positive note it looks very nice and the folding clasp and locking mechanism works quite well.
I suppose the true test will be in a years time but that will be plenty of time to assess whether I get on with a steel bracelet and if so I will know whether investing in the OEM bracelet for my watch is worthwhile as it costs a fortune.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
With the watch active you can only get aluminium band if you purchase 4G version. This was a great cheaper replacement for me. Works well. And still going strong.

There are 2 improvements I would of liked from this:
1. Some sort of stopper preventing the band pins from falling off. When I had the Huawei watch they came with metal band which had the pins enclosed onto the bands so it never could be taken off or fall out.
2. The clip is abit stuff but doesnt hinder the performance of the watch band.

Other then that this came with tools to change the band size. Extra pins and manual ins nicely packed box.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: I bought two of the Fullmosa straps for my Garmin Vivoactive. This metal one, like the leather one I also bought, is a really good quality item for the price, and it comes with spare bars and a clever tool to let you resize the strap yourself. All that is great. The problem is that - again, like the leather strap -  the bars aren't stable enough, which means the strap pings off very easily. In this metal one, it's very easy for the bar to fly across the room, which makes it easy to lose especially if you're out and about. This would be a five star product if it was just more secure, but unfortunately this one issue makes the whole thing disappointing.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
As you can tell from my 4-star rating, I'm quite pleased with it.

I only minus one huge star for 2 reasons.

1. It's a bit thin and flimsy. If it were thicker and more sturdy I would give 5/5 stars and 10/10 stars.

..... Maybe that depends on what bands you've already experienced as well as what band your watch requires. If I had something like a Skagen watch (known for lighter and more low profile watches) then this band would probably be perfect.

2. There's a large gap between the case of my watch and the straight edge of the bracelet. (I knew this would happen going into this purchase)

All in all, I do not regret this purchase one bit.
Keep in mind, ANY black watch band is going to scratch and scuff so the black coating can and will eventually 'rub off'... That's not specific to this watch band so nobody should be removing stars for that known issue.

Any further star-minusing was quickly thwarted by the inclusion of the link removal tool and the spring bar removal tool. I was considering buying new ones and now I don't need any. Awesome!

If you have a huge or medium watch and tend to prefer large hefty bands/bracelets... This MIGHT NOT be for you.

P. S. I actually find it quite amusing that some people are stating this is a "high quality" band or "the best metal band I've ever had"... It's not that good... by a long shot. It's just cool for the price...

The reviews stating it feels cheap or flimsy and lightweight are more accurate. However, only compared to the hefty thick bands to which I've become accustomed.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
HIGHLY RECOMMEND!: This is the best quality stainless steel replacement bracelet I have ever seen, especially in this very affordable price range, and it includes a free link removal tool also!

The links are smooth and so comfortable (and does not catch hair on my wrist). As soon as you hold the bracelet in your hand, you can immediately feel the quality of the steel links.

The link removal tool comes with clear instructions and is easy to use. It also includes extra link pins and lug spring pins.

I was so impressed with this Fullmosa bracelet, a few days later, I bought another Fullmosa bracelet for one of my other watches.

Thank you, Fullmosa!!

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
The band itself is fine, but the accessories are garbage. I bought this to replace and old band that I used a punch and hammer to pop pins out of. This band came with proper adjust tools, so I was looking forward to that making it easier to adjust. Wrong.

First, there is the plastic screw tool. This snapped in half after removing 2 pins of the 4 total I needed to remove. Next there was the metal one. This snapped in half after 1 pin removed. So, back to the punch and hammer and scratching thse sides. These tools are either worthless or this bands pins are made of titanium.

Next, time to install the band on my watch. I really liked the easy install push pins. Wrong. They suck. Apparantly the spring force is not enough and the band pops off my watch constantly with these. Luckily I had some pivot pins from my old, broken band. Installed those, no problems. If you don't have spare pivot pins, though, this band is unusable.

The band itself is good and I have used it for a couple days fine now, I won't be returning it, but the install process was awful.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: Love, love, love. It's given my Guess watch new life. I was replacing my watch straps all the time as they would start looking shabby and make my watch look OLD. I've spent so much on bands over the years. One day in the store I was complaining about how often I was replacing the bands and the guy asked if I used lotion...and therein lies the problem. He advise the leather was soaking in the lotions, oils etc. I didn't want to not wear my watch as my baby had given it to me for either birthday or mother's day gift. Now with this band, problem solved and my Guess watch is looking like new.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
5 month update:
Still not impressed with the finish. It comes off extremely easily but it's got real weight and is worth the $20 something I paid for it. Another note is that if gets sweaty and gross easily. I just installed a new leather band to replace this one.

This band is great across the board except for durability. I had worn it two days when I started to see wear on the underside links.

I work a desk job and the band rubbing on the desk was enough to wear off the paint. I had a previous steel band at the same price point that also had this happen but it took significantly longer.

Great band, I would buy again without hesitation but it's something to be aware of.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
I ordered the 22mm strap for my Garmin Instinct watch. It fit well, unfortunately, I had to return it because after adjusting the strap, the watch was either too loose or too tight for me.

The strap looked great, and I think it complimented my watch very well

Removing the links was simple enough, it came with a tool which was very useful

However, when using the quick-fit pins to attach to the watch, that was when it was tricky. It felt like when I got one side of the pin to one side of the watch lug, and tried to put the other side into the other lug, there was no pin. It was difficult to get the pins in the lugs. But after some playing around, it worked. However, due to the fact that it was very difficult to get in, I felt like it wasn't very secure because it seemed like there wasn't enough "pin" on each side of the lugs.

However, I would've still used it, but because of the fit, I had to return it

Review:

Everything else goes downhill from there.
Trying to remove links, the pin in the screw rod broke almost instantly.
The instructions say the package includes a storage tube and 2 spare pins - none of those were there. So to replace the pin on the screw rod was not possible. I've also tried other methods to remove link pins and it is not possible - the pins are stuck in the links.

Lastly, the metal feels cheap. The brushed silver just does not feel great.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: It's light and comfortable.  Because it's metal you can use it for everything from fine dining (attractive) to jogging (rinseable).  I used to switch between my leather and my silicone but this is a one size fits all solution.The link remover tool is fun to use too.  You feel like a jeweller for a minute.Also you can wipe it with disinfectant without degrading the material, a plus just right now.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: Put this on a Garmin Vivomove Style and it looks like a million bucks. The colour is nicely matched and most people think it came with the watch. Easy to put on and remove . Link adjustment was a tad difficult one pin would not budge but eventually got it. I didn't take a star for that as the final look is so good.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: This review was edited 9 months after purchase. The bracelet is solid in construction but not as substantial as more expensive options - you get what you pay for and it is worth it in my opinion. The bracelet rattles a bit with movement if that is something that really gets to you. I personally wish there were more removable links so I could get a better fit. Be sure that you remove the pins from the correct side, which are labelled by an arrow, otherwise you will end up with a stuck pin that the included tools may or may not be able to resolve for you.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: I have another Fullmosa band (leather quick release) that I really like for my watch (Garmin VivomoveHR) and I was really looking forward to this SS version. Unfortunately this band disconnects VERY easily and my watch is constantly falling to the floor. I'm lucky it has not been dented or damaged yet. It appears that the quick release pins are just a fraction of a mm shorter than the pins in the leather version which causes them to pop out very easily. It's a shame, because it looks good and seems to be of reasonable quality otherwise. Would not buy again.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: Still debating whether to keep or return. Haven’t used it yet but compared to the watch, the band is heavy. Also, while the workmanship is good, the gap between the band and the watch appears to be more and appears to be a slight misfit. Still contemplating.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: Very good value for the money, fits great on my Withings Steel HR.  Secure, comfy.Adjustment (wrist size) was not easy but is a one-time thing !  (tools included).

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: After less than a week of wearing it regularly, the bottom of it has already got the paint wearing off.  I really like this band. Its comfy, fits nicely and looks great with my watch. But the paint is already wearing off and showing an ugly copper color that doesn't go with my watch at all.  I'm not impressed since I spent $22 on it.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review: After 20 years of abuse my original leather strap disintegrated, to be replaced by a fabulous black metal band that matched my watch gold and black casing. The Fullmosa was easy to adjust to my wrist and looks amazing, so much so that people asked if I had purchased a new watch!! Yes, it looks that good!

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
I purchased this band to replace the OEM band on a 5.11 watch with 24mm pins. The original band was made of a rubber like neoprene—thick, strong, and caught on sleeves like cockleburs on a wool sweater.

I don’t have any issues with the links, wearability, or construction of the band itself. It doesn’t poke or pull hair. But it arrives fully assembled for the largest wrist, meaning most people will have to adjust it. It comes with a small, screw-driven pin tool and a jig to hold the band while you are removing pins.

I removed two links successfully, with some effort, with the provided pin tool. Of course, you have to keep testing the fit. When attempting to remove the third pin, the threaded pin tool stripped its threads. The pin tool’s base is made of plastic, and some of the pins move less easily than others. I’ve worked on dozens of watches, fishing reels, sewing machines, and other tools, and I don’t recall many “new” pins that moved as reluctantly as these.

Well, you say, if the threaded thingy stripped, just use the metal part of the pin tool. Well, without some other means of supporting the pin, the metal pin started bending as soon as pressure was applied. And, like a bent nail, it was never going to operate in a straight fashion again.

I was eventually able to remove the correct number of pins to fit my wrist with marginal success. Removing four links fit but tightly—as soon as I became active, my wrist swelled enough where the band makes an imprint. However, at three links removed the band was too loose, and there is no way to customize the fit.

As a result, although the band itself appears sturdy and serviceable, I will probably be replacing it soon and can not recommend it to others.

Product: Fullmosa Smart Watch Strap 16mm 18mm 19mm 20mm 22mm 24mm, Metal Straps for Mens & Women, Compatbile for Samsung, Casio, Huawei, Fossil, Withings Smart Watch
Review:
Band came with minor scuffing on the underside of the bracelet where the clasp is. No biggie, nothing a little scour pad couldn't correct for the brush finish.

My biggest issue with this band is that it is NOT 22mm. The box was clearly marked 22mm. It's just a skosh bigger. It didn't fit on any of my 22mm watches, none. It was cheap enough and knowing if I returned it for another I'd probably experience the same issue, I took my Dremel to it and shaved down the link that houses the spring bars. Now it fits all of my 22mm watches.

All in all, it's just an OK band. I wouldn't recommend nor would I buy another. A case of you get what you pay for.

Product: Mens Watches Chronograph Stainless Steel Waterproof Date Analog Quartz Watch Business Casual Fashion Wrist Watches for Men
Review: I like rolex's but im a middle class 16 year old who obviously cant afford one. I wanted a fake but they are all a couple hundred so i resulted to this. Right first of all it looks amazing on your wrist, like a two toned submariner would. Get a bit closer and its still stunning. Analysing it closely, its not rolex level, the face does look a bit generic but i mean its 30 quid, it should be around 200. Get it if you want a beauty of a watch.

Product: Mens Watches Chronograph Stainless Steel Waterproof Date Analog Quartz Watch Business Casual Fashion Wrist Watches for Men
Review:
I can only feel sorry for anyone who actually paid the RRP of £230 for this peice of scrap, I know I was taking a risk in thinking maybe just maybe this really was once worth £230, I fell for it, should have know better, I feel ripped off paying £25, if I had paid £230 I'd be crying!

Firstly the weight of this thing amazed me, it's a wrist watch not a grandfather clock, I could strap stone henge or a sundial to my wrist that weighs less, and no doubt would work just as well maybe more so, this isn't something I would feel comfortable wearing, it weighs a tonne at least!

The comments suggest the size of the strap would fit the Incredible Hulk, you'd need to be him to carry this on your arm, for like just 1 hour, if it worked well enough to tell you what an hour was!

I didn't even get around to removing half the strap it seems everyone else had to suffer with, or pay a jeweler to remove and I'm glad I don't have to as it seems the cheap tool provided either doesen't fit, or just bends/snaps instantly, lots of reveiws state this.

None of the stopwatch functions worked as they should, the top start button does nothing at all, you feel as if you just need to push it in harder maybe, still nothing just a painful dent in my finger, there is ZERO tactile feedback in any of these spring loaded buttons, nothing at all, they are loose, wobble side to side, press in and seem to connect with nothing at all, no slight click, no feel, may as well just be a dead show button.

The bottom button spins one of the dial around, sometimes, I thought maybe the outside face dial needed to be set in order for this to work as it seems to start for a short time then stop, even IF this is the case it only worked 2 out of 5 times I tried using the same methods. It's IMPOSSIBLE to read any of the instructions without first placing them under a high power microscope, or use a telescope, possible one like Hubble in space, with the instructions placed directly onto the lens.. again this button has zero feedback loose and wobbles from side to side.

The external dial wobbles up and down, is loose and has too much movment to even suggest fine workmanship, i'd guess after turning it around a few times it'd fall off, or free spin. If this is the case for the biggest component, then I can only imagine what the inside movements are like!

I also tested the 'glow in the dark' feature, there isn't one, although the claim 'just charge it up with light' suggests so, you'd probably need to place it on the surface of the sun just to get it to glow dimmly for like 3 seconds!

This is a cheap copy of a Citizen style mens watch in NO WAY is it 'military' 'fashion' or 'waterproof' it suggests maybe if some rain lands on it you'd be ok, but warns again immersion for longer than a few minutes, and NOT to be used diving, swimming.

At best and as sorry as I am for saying so, this is a 'made in China' cheap costume jewelery type item, mass produced seemingly untested, and TBH I'd feel ripped off if I paid more than £3 for it!

It looks nice though!

That's about the only good thing!

Product: Mens Watches Chronograph Stainless Steel Waterproof Date Analog Quartz Watch Business Casual Fashion Wrist Watches for Men
Review: This watch was bought for me as a Christmas present. It arrives in a felt pouch as opposed to a box probably for shipping purposes so that it can be popped through the letter box. So what do you get for £30.00? A stunning looking watch very similar in appearance to very expesive Swiss Diver watches. Ignore the RRP. For that sort of money I would at least expect a screw on back, screw down crown and an automatic movement. Having said that this watch is amazing value for money. All the sub dials are fully working as are the buttons so you are getting a lot of watch for the money. According to the supplier it is made in China using an imported Japanese movement with a 3 year battery life. The make of movement is not listed but as the japanese invented the quartz movement it should be pretty reliable. They also provide a tool for removing links but this was not too successful as it broke in use. Fortunately I have had an interest in Horology for a few years and had my own tools with which to make the necessary adjustment. My advice would be to take it to a friendly local watch maker to get it adjusted if you are not too confident in adjusting it yourself. Treat it as a very smart dress watch not as something you would wear on a building site! I have seen some dreadful reviews regarding this watch on Amazon but if they are correct then they certainly have not purchased the watch that I am wearing.

Product: 112 PCS Watch Repair Kit, Eventronic Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set with Carrying Case
Review:
I'm a Weirdo! For some reason I emit a strange field that totally wrecks watches. I even managed to make an expensive Tag run backwards just by wearing it. Consequently over the years I have spent so much on watch repairs I finally gave up and decided to have a go myself

I am genuinely surprised and this little kit has so far managed to repair three watches including a very expensive Fossil. I am seriously impressed and think it's humble price is money well spent as it has already paid for itself twice over compared to the high street charges for just swapping a battery or strap

My only complaints are that what few instructions supplied need a magnifying glass to read and that the clamp to hold a watch body in place has little padding. If it wasn't for these minor issues I'd give it full marks, Especially as it comes with a small bag of strap pins - the things everyone loses and also comes in a padded nylon case that unusually has a zip that actually works

I like this and genuinely recommend it but it has to come with a health warning. Repairing watches needs a steady hand, good eyesight and lots, really lots of patience. Please don't blame anyone if you use it to chisel open a family heirloom as there are some tools in this kit I haven't figured out yet. This from someone who used to hand solder circuit boards

Product: 112 PCS Watch Repair Kit, Eventronic Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set with Carrying Case
Review: I have a vast collection of watches, and always begrudge having to spend a fortune when it's time to take them in for  new batteries! Normally between £5 and £10 dependent on the watch, plus the waiting time, and similar if any links need removing! Never even thought of attempting a battery change or link extraction until now but this is the perfect piece of kit! Coupled with buying a batch of assorted watch batteries, these tools helped me to change 7 batteries, remove links from 3 of my stepsons watches, and now surprise surprise the wife wants hers doing to! Only thing missing I guys would be some small pliers, but most of us have those hanging around, and don't feel it's work marking down for! Great value and quality :)

Product: 112 PCS Watch Repair Kit, Eventronic Professional Spring Bar Tool Set Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set with Carrying Case
Review: Honestly, it’s everything you need to maintain your watch. I can’t fault this kit at all. It’s a great value for money and easy to use not to mention it’s excellent build quality. It’s a bargain for the price. Perhaps my only gripe with it is that it’s quite compact ( usually not a problem ) but it’s often very frustrating to locate the respective places for the instruments if you are in a hurry so you often end up shoving things in and closing the zip. Apart from that I can’t find any other fault. It’s 5/5 from me anyway since the shortcomings are mostly due to my frantic and impatient nature.

Review: More than delighted with this handy little pin-on watch.  Light weight, yet strong - the numbers are large enough without the watch being too large (lovely and clear to read).  Just what I needed with all the hand washing/hand gel usage needed in this brave new world we sadly find ourselves in.  I work in an Opticians, and though on Reception (with a PC & clock) - it is excellent for when I am not sitting at my desk.  It fits firmly in its rubber casing, yet is easy to remove to set the time.  Also keeps excellent time, with a lovely soft ticking noise (barely there - not annoying), which I find quite soothing to hear.  A very good purchase, and will buy again.  (I bought the blue - may buy some other colours to go with my various outfits).
