Product: Ravel Unisex Easy Read Watch with Big Numbers
Review: I bought this watch because i badly needed a new one  - My old watch needed a new battery, but I was unable to open it to replace the battery - I expected this cheap watch to last at least a month or two, until I could purchase a better one.Unfortunately when I received my new watch, the prone that goes through the hole into the buckle (keeps the strap on the wrist) wasn't long enough to keep in the hole. Therefore the watch kept falling off my wrist. By day two I couldn't find the watch.Waste of my money!

Product: Ravel Unisex Easy Read Watch with Big Numbers
Review: Do not buy! It’s cheap and shoddily made. I bought this at the end of November as a present for my hard of sight mother in law, thinking that the face would be big. It’s not.My mistake. Rather than send it back, I thought I’d keep it for when my watch battery died. That day has come and I started to use the watch today by pulling out the plastic around the dial. Most of the dial pulled out when I tried to set the time which made me somewhat suspicious about how long it would work for. It worked for about 10 minutes then it gave up. Complete waste of money. I have had a different ravel watch that was much better quality. This is poor quality, cheap rubbish. Save your money. I don’t expect much from a cheap watch but I do expect it to work for longer than 10 minutes.

Product: Ravel Unisex Easy Read Watch with Big Numbers
Review:
A neat watch face with numerals that are large and easy to read but not ungainly.
This watch fits a very slim wrist perfectly yet there is plenty of strap to fit a larger wrist.
The watch face remains central on the wrist even when the strap is tightened to the last hole.
Keeps good time.
Excellent value for money.

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review:
I had one of these about 23 years ago at primary school. I decided to scrap my Fitbit that bombards me with notifications and needs charging every week for an old school Casio once again! I got it in yellow and love it. The design is exactly as it was when I was a kid. It's super easy to use and the screen is really clear in and out of sunlight. It's also super slim so you don't catch it on things as much as the thicker smart watches do.
Over all, if you're looking for nostalgia, style or just a reliable cheap watch, this is the one!
Super pleased after all these years they are still making them!

Also the delivery came on time and undamaged, thank you!

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: This watch is great - keeps the time perfectly, affordable, durable, lightweight, east-to-read screen, and of course- awesome color! I like that it isn't bulky at all, it's very low-profile so never caught on anything.The Casio F-91W has been my watch of choice for the pas 15 years, it typically lasts about 5 years, before the strap starts to look a bit scruffy, and then I replace it. For the price, I think it's pretty great, and I highly recommend it for anyone who's looking for a simple, yet high quality and resilient digital watch!

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: I got this watch for my daughter as a present because her favrioute colour is yellow and her best friend had the same one so they have matching ones. 😄😄😄It is water resistant but take it of before the bath just in case my daughter has forgot to take her watch of many times before getting in the shower and it still works!!! I would recomend this watch 😁😁😁😁😄😄😄😃😃😃😀😀😀

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: There appears to be a manufacturing defect in these watches as my wife has broken two in succession, both times in the side of the main casing., rendering the watch totally useless.  It is difficult to contact Casio and Amazon doesn't appear to have a function in their order section to honour their obligation under the UK Sale of Goods Act either.  Seriously unimpressed with a watch that broke apart after a months use.  If anyone from Casio or Amazon reads this I'd appreciate some proactive support (and I'll update the review if I do).

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: The classic Casio- given as an everyday to wife. She remains in raptures over it - tells date and all that, and once time is set it goes on painlessly for ever. May seem elementary facts to most but this is a better and more useful timekeeper than previous gold analogue. She also has the pink one Casio!

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: Saw a work mate wearing this watch and had to get one of my own! The colour is great and on trend, timer function is fab, and it's so comfy I forget I'm wearing it.Unfortunately I've had it a few months and the strap colour is starting to go a bit 'off' at the edges, like a greenish colour, and it seems to be an issue with the plastic itself, not dirt that can be washed away. Next time I'll go for the black version!

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: A simple thin digital watch with stop watch and light up in the dark is all i wanted. You will not believe how difficult to find one nowadays. All far too much funtions and need regular charging. Hopefully the digital accuracy of Casio will not let me down. A bit disappointed that the watch is just a bit darker dirty yellow than what i can see from the photo.

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: Very serviceable.  Comfortable and secure on wrist, easy to take on and off. Has a lot of features I don't need: I actually want just a clear accurate display of the time and it gives that.  I haven't tested Timer function or Water resistance so Didn't give a star rating for them.

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review:
Had my last watch for a year and a bit, lasted me very well, even when worn in showers or in the river. Water resistance suffers after a period of rough use, but it was still mostly functioning for a week after water got into it. Had to get a replacement as soon as I could, I'd be lost without one now!

The LED isn't the best, but if it's dark enough to need it you can generally make out the time with it.

Overall a very solid and reliable watch with a slim profile so it doesn't get in the way like a bulkier watch might. Lightwieght and comfy, no real downsides

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: Love it, use it to track my times as a simple stopwatch. Decided as I use Strava for all my runs I had no need for a fancy expensive Garmin device. Keep my phone in zipped running leggings so this is handy to check my  time (and pace- but by working out in head). Love the retro style, it’s simplicity & reliability.

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: I was the first of my colleges to buy it, because our uniform is black and green, very light but the most useful thing for me is the night light.

Product: Casio F-91WC Collection Men Watch
Review: Very pleased with the watch (Casio has never let me down) But also, my son who is 7, was fiddling with the latch and it just snapped. Product: CASIO F91W-1 Casual Sport Watch
Review:
I bought this renowned watch for its iconic status. Many reviews have already been done on the quality and functionality of the watch, so I'm instead going to add the following interesting facts:

1. Most folk say this watch was released in 1991, but in fact it was released in Japan in 1989. This makes it the longest manufactured digital-watch in history.

2. Casio state that these watches continue to sell around 3 million of these watches worldwide EVERY SINGLE YEAR making it the best selling digital-watch in history.

3. The watch was worn by Barack Obama AND Osama Bin Laden....more or less simultaneously!

4. Due to its construction and availability, the Casio f91w was adopted by terrorists for use as timers in Improvised Explosive Devices. The CIA considered possession of the watch as an identifier for their 'terrorist watch list'. At one point, it is alleged that over 30% of inmates at Guantanamo Bay had been found in possession of either a F-91w or a variation carrying the same module.

5. With a good battery and the watch kept at body-temperature, accuracy over time is said to be more accurate than mechanical/analogue designs....including Rolex!

6. This model has been displayed in the London School of Art, due to its iconic design.

7. Purists refer to this watch as the 'happy meal watch' due to the fact that, wherever you are in the world, the watch generally retails at the same price as a Macdonald's meal.

Some people are worried about the 'Water Resist' standard? Well the following is the official standard (ISO 2281) which the watch is able to exceed:

Resistance when immersed in water at a depth of 10 cm.

Immersion of the watch in 10 cm of water for 1 hour.

Immersion of the watch in 10 cm of water with a force of 5 N perpendicular to the pusher buttons for 10 minutes.

The watch shall be placed on a heated plate at a temperature between 40 °C and 45 °C until the watch has reached the temperature of the heated plate (in practice, a heating time of 10 minutes to 20 minutes, depending on the type of watch, will be sufficient). A drop of water, at a temperature between 18 °C and 25 °C shall be placed on the glass of the watch. After about 1 minute, the glass shall be wiped with a dry rag. Any watch which has condensation on the interior surface of the glass shall be eliminated.

Immersion of the watch in 10 cm of water at the following temperatures for 5 minutes each, 40 °C, 20 °C and 40 °C again, with the transition between temperatures not to exceed 1 minute. No evidence of water intrusion or condensation is allowed.

Immersion of the watch in a suitable pressure vessel and subjecting it within 1 minute to the rated pressure for 10 minutes, or to 2 bar in case where no additional indication is given. Then the overpressure is reduced to the ambient pressure within 1 minute. No evidence of water intrusion or condensation is allowed.

Exposing the watch to an overpressure of 2 bar. The watch shall show no air-flow exceeding 50 μg/min.

(No magnetic or shock resistance properties are required.
No negative pressure test is required.
No strap attachment test is required.
No corrosion test is required)

So there you have it: The Casio f91w. Probably the most astute £10 purchase you’ll ever make

Product: Casio Collection Men's Watch AE-1200WH
Review:
I'll clear one thing up straight away; Mine came with a box, manual, and warranty card.

As for the watch, I bought the silver version. I can not more highly recommend this watch, it is truly amazing.
The band is very nice and comfortable with easily changeable links to get to your wrist size, and can be swapped for something of your choice.
The width for the links/ band are 22mm outter, 18mm inner.

The watch itself is a great throwback to the 80s with a wonderful nostalgic feeling to it.
As for the functionality, it is amazing. It comes with, if I remember correctly, 31 main time zones, with a separate function on your 'Main' display for 4 cities of your choice.

The alarm feature is wonderful and isn't at all too quiet, I found it to be the perfect volume. With 5 alarms, it is great if you travel a lot as you can set your alarm along with the city you're going to, or add one for medications, etc.

Stopwatch and timer work as you would except.

Has a mute feature which mutes the beeps of the watch, but not the alarms etc, very handy.

The display is nice, and I haven't received a single scratch on it yet. Viewing the watch is fine, though in direct sunlight, and as mentioned in the manual, it can be hard to read directly overhead, so tilting slightly works fine.

The LED lights are a good brightness, perfect to see once it is dark, and has a timer setting of 1.5s to 3s, which can be adjusted to your liking.

The world map is also nice, showing and changing as you change cities on the watch to match that particuliar area's timezone, NYC, Paris, Sydney, etc.

There is also a little digital analogue clock in the left corner, which if worn on the right hand, is a great little feature that pokes out of the side of your shirt so you can still see the time without being too obvious.

The only downside I have is that I wish the world map had been coloured so it is easier to see which timezone you're in, in the daylight. Shows up perfectly fine at night and with the LED light.

5/5 for this item, and for the price, you really can't go wrong, it is an amazing nostalgic throwback, and it fits comfortably on the wrist.

Product: Casio Collection Men's Watch AE-1200WH
Review: As a man with an attraction to watches I found myself needing to add one to my collection.It needed to be sturdy and waterproof for outdoor activities and sports, but bot overly chunky like a G Shock. It needed to be waterproof, and ideally not have a strap likely to scratch or sty wet. I also didn’t want anything flashy, but smart looking. After much time spent reading reviews and researching i settled on this Casio, and having owned a couple of different casios knew the abuse they can take. Very pleased with this model, does exactly what it says, looks decent enough to be worn anywhere, but still handle anything you put it through, and functions like a Casio. For the price, you can’t go wrong

Product: Casio Collection Men's Watch AE-1200WH
Review: This watch has the looks. It is a great timekeeper and quite easy to set up if you take your time, Afraid the instructions are very small which can be off putting, but  not difficult. The bracelet is nice and solid and looks classyand although it is far too big for my wrist , (or most people) there are some good clear instructions for removinglinks on the web. I removed 3 links very quickly this way and the watch is now a perfect fit. FANTASTIC WATCH FOR THIS PRICE.  go for it.

Product: Casio Collection Men's Watch AE-1200WH
Review: The watch is well made and consists of good build materials and finish. The digital module is extremely accurate and never needs adjustment. The watch comes with an operating manual which is actually very complicated, it took a while to work out how to set and use all the features. The digital display is reasonable but I would prefer larger digits to make it easier to read at a glance. The backlight is very good and works well in the dark. Overall I am very pleased with this watch which now a classic casio watch for collectors, the price is a little on the expensive side as these watches can be found cheaper.

Product: Casio Collection Men's Watch AE-1200WH
Review: Bought this watch as it had the alarm functions I needed and was cheap (my last Casio cost 5 times as much and only lasted a couple of years before all the buttons failed).In fairness, during the 3 years or so I used the watch all functions worked just as they should and crucially the buttons don't appear to be anywhere near failing.  HOWEVER, and I know it's a cheap watch but I just can't get past the fact that, the watch glass (plastic) is so vulnerable to scratching that they seem to just appear (as if caused by just wearing long sleeves)???  I've never had this issue with another watch (and there's been a lot of them) so I'm putting it down to the soft plastic used in the face.  If it wasn't for this I wouldn't have bought a replacement with an expensive sapphire crystal face (which as you'd hope hasn't scratched in the last year or so).

Product: Casio Collection Men's Watch AE-1200WH
Review: I bought mine in black with the resin strap before travelling in 2016. The world time function was genuinely useful (once you figure out how to set it up) and personally think this design looks a lot less tacky and garish than some other world time designs. If I'm being picky, I do wish it was mineral crystal instead of scratch prone plastic but can't complain at the price. Some of the front wording can be removed with rubbing alcohol, see my picture.I still wear it as a beater and take it on holiday, every time it's a memory of my travels and even though it costs less than £25, it is probably more precious to me than my more expensive analogue watches.

Product: Casio Collection Men's Watch AE-1200WH
Review: I bought this because my other Casio watches had plastic straps which kept on breaking. I had not realised that fitting the stainless steel strap on this watch needed an expert; also the date is too small to read quickly. I have now gone back to the old casio straps and put this in the drawer.

Product: Casio Collection Men's Watch AE-1200WH
Review: I doubt this is a real Casio or their quality dropped down completely. The glass got scratched after few days, and it cracked few weeks later. Bear in mind that I don't do any DIY or other work which could expose this watch to such a damage. I actually noticed the damage while driving a car and I'm sure it wasn't cracked before I set of. Our theory as a joke was that I drove well too fast. Besides that, it was the most beautiful electronic watch money can buy for sure.

Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review:
I bought this wrist watch because I wanted something elegant to wear after the work time: I need to say that this watch does his job very well!

This watch has been presented in a black box with the logo, the box opens and closes with a magnet; an easy and quick way to open a box.

Overall, this wrist watch is very good since the center of it is made of iron; a very strong material and the stripes are made of skin; comfortable and attractive.

Together with the watch, we can find a little instruction booklet for some support.
If for some reason the watch is damaged, there is an ‘’insurance’’ card that informs you how to obtain the same product not damaged.

Additionally, if the watch gets dirty, in the box is contained a little cloth to wipe it.
In my opinion this is a fantastic product.

Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review: I bought this watch as a gift to my other half, he really likes it and says it fits really well due to the quality of the leather. Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review:
The bad: the gold on black that I bought looks great in the picture but in the real world is quite hard to read; the contrast is not great except at certain angles and the hands are very thin, with cutouts, making them eaven harder to find against the very busy background. Looks great but not so good to actually read the time. Oh - and the luminous paint doesn't work; I can't see it at all in the dark.

That said it's a great watch for the price and I suspect that had I chosen a silver version the visibility would have been much better. The build quality and attention to detail is outstanding, as is the quality of the leather strap; it looks and feels like a much - MUCH - more expensive watch. It's also accurate :-)

Bottom line: if you want a cheap watch that doesn't look like one just buy one of these. The silver version(s) are probably much easier to read than the black/gold one I bought... but it does look really nice on the wrist.

Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review: The battery in my old Accurist watch ran out when due to the coronovirus all the shops were closed. Obsessively I checked my empty wrist for a few days (no idea why as time seems to matter a little less at the moment) and the time is on my mobile phone, my computer and I just have to say "Alexa what time is it"  to know. Nonetheless I am of an age where if I wish to know the time; I look at my watch. I have been doing so for so long that this habit  is now unlikely to change. So I sent for this watch. I choose this one for two reasons, a leather strap (would not need to find a shop to adjust the metal bracelet on a strap when all the shops are shut) and the fact that it looks good.It does, look good, it is easy to read and seems to keep good time. What more can you ask for from a watch?

Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review: A stylish and classy looking watch! Beautifully made for such a great price- a real bargain! The watch came also with it's own box which is fantastic! The watch is definitely made with high quality materials. I would definitely recommend this product!

Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review: I needed something for everyday wear whilst my main watch was being repaired. It's a lovely looking watch and keeps good time although it feels very light and cheap.  Ive had some compliments from friends who have noticed it. Comes in a nice box but I dont tend to keep boxes. The loop came off the strap after a day and the little bottons on the side that start/stop and reset the face dials dont work. I'm happy enough with it though for £20.

Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review:
Nice watch, seems to hold time too. Also comfortable with a soft leather strap. Two little things though....

When adjusting the time, the arms flop everywhere and getting an accurate time is harder than it should be. Sometimes, As soon as you let go of the adjuster you can lose or gain 2 minutes. Annoying.

Second, the strap clasp is steel coloured on my rose gold coloured watch with brown strap... i mean.... seriously, why ? It sticks out like a sore thumb. At least make it rose gold colour too so it matches.

Apart from those two things im quite happy

Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review: I am a bit of a perfectionist when it comes to watches and after trawling through several screens and reading copious amounts of reviews I decided to go for this LIGE watch....and I wasn't disappointed. The style seems to be not too dissimilar with other branded watches but at a fraction of the price. The black face/dial combined with a dark brown leather strap looks and feels comfy to wear and at the moment keeps perfect time. The luminous sweep hands don't display much luminosity  but that is a minor quibble. The ability to use it as a stopwatch function is also handy but not something I would personally use, nevertheless the additional dials just add to the look. Overall it's a good quality watch for a very good price.

Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review: I was pleasantly surprised by the finishes of this watch. I bought it out of curiosity after reading the reviews. The watch is presented with a beautiful blue dial, the bezel is fixed in an intense blue slightly iridescent, the case is gold color uniform and deep and not at all tacky, the chronograph works perfectly and the keys are very precise, just a small press to start, lock and reset everything. The strap is made of soft leather, it looks like Nabuk, beige with gold buckle. In conclusion for less than 50€a great timepiece precise is a month that I wear it and still does not sgarra the minute, certainly of important proportions but not excessive, in practice the watch hardly does not goes unnoticed.

Product: LIGE Mens Watches Fashion Waterproof Sports Chronograph Analogue Quartz Stainless Steel Black Dial Leather Bracelet Wristwatch
Review: I had previously bought several Lige watches,all of which I have been extremely pleased with,if I was to offer any criticism it would be that some of the metal straps have temperamental catches which open at random.My latest purchase has a leather strap which is extremely comfortable.I have at least 10 Lige watches,and I love them all.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: I ordered this because my husband broke the strap on his watch and due to the lockdown could not replace it.  This was a reasonable priced and looked easy to use.  I say looked because when it arrived, from China, the instruction leaflet was in Chinese and English, but in exceptionally small print which did cause a few problems.  Having said that, I managed to get the date and time sorted out, he won’t use the rest of the options anyway.  The really excellent news was that the strap was big enough to go round his wrist, I normally have to get extra long fitted for him.  Cheered him up during trying times.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: I'm suspicious that the calender display does NOT automatically handle dates properly, e.g. The software does not appear to follow "30 days hath September, April, June and November all the rest have 31 except for February".  I had to manually adjust the calender because I noted an error in the displayed date when I compared it to another device, and I am confident that it was set correctly before the end of the previous month. Also the date function does not automatically work out what day of the week any particular date might be.. That had to be manually set as well.  The plastic watch face has been easily scratched by sharp things in contact with it during wear. On the plus side, the digital display is large enough for me to read without my glasses, and the stop watch function allows me to easily measure elapsed time which was my main motive for buying this watch.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: Very big and very accurate. Casing is made of bad plastic and/or design, 2 months on the plastic ring sourrounding the watch face began to crack and detach in 3 places. Used superglue to repair.6 month the battery need changing I changed it and assembled it properly then it started to leak, checked all the seals are ok and inserted properly still it leaked. I will stick to Casio next time

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: For the price, this is a great watch. I just need something to show the time in nice big numbers and an alarm function and this does the job perfectly. Yes, the alarm could be a bit louder and sound for longer, but it’s still acceptable. A bit tricky to work out the settings when reading from the instructions - I found it easier to just work it out from trial and error on the watch itself.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: I bought this because it has a big clear display that is easy to read, if you need reading glasses you will probably be just fine reading this without needing them. No nonsense, simple - does what it says on the tin - it tells the time.  Stopwatch and alarm are there also if you think you might ever need that. Easy to use. Easy to push buttons. Robust and looks ok.  What more do you want ?

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: Great watch for the price ( but to set it up is a nightmare, I've only got the stop watch working, given up with the rest of the functions = instructions are very basic.So I've got a stopwatch for £9.95 not bad & great delivery & packaging.It says water resistant not waterproof = huge difference !!  Try it if you like but I would be very surprised if you could swim or shower with it on. But @ a tenner it's a risk.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: This is my second review for this little watch. I have had it now for a few weeks and the timekeeping is very impressive - still accurate to within a second. I would recommend this for anyone whose eyesight is in any way diminished - the readout is big and beautiful. The day and date are displayed clearly as well as the seconds and at the end of a month it automatically reverts to the 1st - no manual adjustment needed.If you want to know the time, day or date (reliably) then seek no further - brilliant value for money.N.B. I have no connection with the manufacturer / wholesaler or Amazon - this is a genuine review.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: Back-light is not very bright but bright enough to see it clearly at night time. The manual could be clearer it's easy to figure out the most basic of functions like setting time, date and how to use the timer. Still not sure how the split timer works. It's sturdy and contrary to some reviews it's water proof. I've had showers wearing it.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: I had this for less than 24 hours and already there's a scratch.I thought it was a bit of dirt at first then when I used my nails to try scrape it off I just ended up adding more scratches to it! I'm immediately returning this for another watch I found that has scratch resistant glass.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: Fantastic, easy to read ( I have a problem telling the time with some watches as the numbers are too small ) watch. Very comfortable and stylish, good value product.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: The watch has a big display and is therefore easy to read, also in the dark.But there are two issues with this watch.1) it adds 10 minutes to the time on a regular basis, and then takes it off again after a minute or two.2) the seconds sometimes count past 59 seconds and have been witnessed displaying 78 seconds. Therefore the stop watch is unreliable.

Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: Got the same watch again .Used it for over a year and was in the sea most weeks with a wetsuit pulling on the strap and never had a problem. Easy to see the time because of big numbers,so If your eyes are not too good its great. Hope this one lasts like the last one. Great value.

Review: This watch exceeded my expectations with the modest price tag. It has taken a good beating as I wear it for work and gets covered in dust, gets soaked and takes a beating in general. Product: Mens Sports Digital Watches - Outdoor Waterproof Sport Watch with Alarm/Timer, Big Face Military Wrist Watches with LED Backlight for Running Men - Black by VDSOW
Review: Great watch. Simple, strong and robust. Also has a stopwatch and alarm and can be lit up for a few seconds to see the time when it's dark at night by pressing the light button. The back is easy to remove if you ever need to replace the battery(just 4 miniature screws) display is very big and easy to see and also shows the date at the top. Also water resistant as well. Can't fault this watch in any way.

Review:
For the price I'm happy. Great customer support from wifort for me. Asked a question and got answered the next day. Back to the watch. It comes with some cons, ofcourse. The countdown timer can only be set to full minutes and hours. I would like seconds accuracy for sprinting intervalls and such.

The bracelet is either a bit tight or a bit loose for me. I'm just inbetween two sizes. Not a big deal though. I'm nitpicking here.

The bracelet is "squeeking" when I correct the watch or press the buttons since it's wide enough to touch the sides of the connecting place with the pin.

Ok. Some of these things is just nitpicking but worth telling. I'm very pleased with the screen. Huge clear numbers which was what I was after.

It looks good imo.

Easy to press buttons. I miss the beeps though when I'm in countdown timer mode. It beeps from everything else. Maybe a tiny bug? It doesn't matter that much though.

Backlight is cool. Whole screen turns green. A bit distorsion of the numbers though in medium dark but in real dark it gets very clear and looks great.

Feels good that it's really waterproof for this price too. So, overall pleased. I feel I will wear this as a casual everyday watch and when I'm out running. 👍

Product: 2 x 20mm Black Rubber PVC Watch Strap Keeper Retaining Hoop Loop Ring Retainer Holder

Product: 2 x 20mm Black Rubber PVC Watch Strap Keeper Retaining Hoop Loop Ring Retainer Holder
Review: Bought this out of necessity to save buying an entire new strap for my watch (Garmin Forerunner 645) after the original retaining loop broke after 11 months. The original loop was perfect - it was unobtrusive and it locked into place. Obviously this doesn't lock into place, but then it isn't designed to. However this loop is taller, chunkier and more supple than the one it's replacing, meaning it stands out more, and not in a good way. At least it doesn't irritate my skin, and the width is spot on. 3 stars for now, but subject to go up or down depending on how long it lasts!EDIT: The first retaining loop lasted around 18 months before breaking. I feel this is pretty good for a watch which I wear all the time so upping the review to 4 stars. After the first loop broke, I used a paper clip bent into a rectangle and covered in tape for around 3 months whilst I hunted down the second loop. This worked surprisingly well, but I'm happy to have recently found the other loop in the pack - let's see how long this one lasts!

Product: 2 x 20mm Black Rubber PVC Watch Strap Keeper Retaining Hoop Loop Ring Retainer Holder

So the strap holder on my Casio watch broke, and I ordered these 20mm ones to replace them.

My only issue was, I made the mistake of measuring the broken one to know which size to go for, wheras I should have measured the size of the watch strap. Because of this, the holder I ordered is a bit too big, but it's not a big deal.

Otherwise perfect, and saved me the money of buying a new strap or watch.

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review:
This is a lovely, simple watch from Casio and a nice alternative to their vintage model. This has the advantage of a strong, teal coloured backlight that fills the entire display evenly. It shows the time, date, has a stopwatch and is water resistant to 50 metres.

I travelled up north and left my watch at home so ordered this because I kept staring at a bare wrist! I'm so happy with it, it may become my primary watch (and my other two are an expensive Casio and a Mondaine).

It's worth noting that this is a small watch, and some may find it too delicate. The strap is narrow and the face shallow, which suits me perfectly but may not be prominent enough for some.

I'm very happy and highly recommend this watch! It does what it says on the tin and is the price of a couple of coffees (at the time of writing). What's not to like?

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review: I had these in my very early years, around single to double figures. Didn’t realise they still made them and they are soooo cheap! Where else can you be taken back by 40 or so years to a much simpler, friendlier, uncomplicated time for a few quid. And it’s a great watch! Amazing, buy one, buy two, be a 70’s/80’s kid again, worth its weight in gold.

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review: I brought this watch to use whilst at work. I love the retro design, the time and date are both displayed in a clear manner. The illuminator is bright (the only downside is you do have to keep your finger on the illuminator button, otherwise it goes off right away) shame it didn't stay on for about five seconds after pressing it, but it's probably a battery saving feature... Overall,  you cant go wrong with this watch for the price.

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review:
Originally got the F-91W retro Casio which was great but the light was very limited. This Electro Illuminator edition improves on the OG in every way. The light is great, and it looks awesome. I wear it in all weathers while cycling and keep it on in the bath. 50 metre water resistance is more than enough. The alarm and stop watch are easy to use, too.

I think the watch strap might be its weakest feature- very basic plasticy feeling, which is okay, but is easily changable. I intend to replace mine soon with one of the custom soft material watch straps available on Amazon.

Good job, Casio. 90's charm in 2020.

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review: A fantastic tool watch for people with smaller wrists. Might look a bit silly on larger sized people. Basically a nicer looking F91w, which is a legendary watch.Used mine for timing runs, and syncing time code on tv shoot, so can definitely say it is a great tool to have. So cheap that it doesn't matter if it gets banged around, but can take a little bit of a beating and getting wet. If you don't want to get the cash out for a G shock, or maybe just don't need something that rugged, this is a great option.

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review: I've been buying this watch over the past 30 to 40 years.  There used to be a little plastic tag stopping the battery from engaging, thereby giving you a fully charged battery..  You pulled out the tag and the watch came to life.  Now, the watch is already running when you open the box, and the question is: for how long has it been running?  A month?  A year?  5 years?  Who knows.  I'd love to know why it no longer comes with the little plastic tag ??

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review: This is my second identical watch and they are great. Keeps accurate time and has a brilliant stop watch facility for any sport related activity. First one lasted a long time until the plastic strap fractured and a new watch almost cost the price of replacing the strap at a local repair shop. My constant companion.

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review: I empty/fill and test hot tubs every day so I wanted a reliable watch that could survive the water and chlorine and was easy to read the date and time on.This was cheap, looks cool and retro and it performs well.I have small wrists so most modern watches look stupid bulky on me but this is perfect.

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review: I love it, my other Casio is still ticking despite it being more than 5 years on me. This watch hopefully lasts the same. I changed the straps into Nato one, and it looks so much better. Also love the green light this one has instead of the pale orange from my other Casio. I will try swimming with this on September and hopefully nothing wrong happens with it. I trust Casio.

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review: Having had this watch for over 2 years now, I can confidently say it will keep on going forever! Super tough, lightweight and functional! Would highly recommend! Also good for work use to as Can be strapped around a belt loop or on a land yard without being to heavy!

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant

It also offers a feature to alarm every hour, day and night - I have no idea when that would be useful so I have never used that feature.The time piece itself is very well made and has never gone wrong.  The only downside is the straps are plastic and they break- which is the end of the watch as they cannot be replaced (or it's cheaper to buy a new watch).

Product: Casio Classic Men's Watch in Resin/Stainless Steel with Daily Alarm and Automatic Calendar - Water Resistant
Review:
Awesome little watch. I got this as a 'I'm doing things I don't want other watches to get scratched or broken by' watch. Not so much a daily beater but not a work horse watch either. And it's turned into one of my favourite watches to wear. Feels as light as a F91W, which I have as a watch that I really don't care about if anything happens to, except it's too small for my wrist size (approx 7.5-8 inches). This feels and looks much better, however, like the F91W I do have to wear it on the wrist bone or closer to the wrist 3 holes from the end. (All preference to be fair).
The light is so much better on this watch though. So for an extra £6-7, if you need a light and you're looking at the F91 series, don't bother. Go with this watch instead.
The stopwatch is basic and does what it says on the tin.
Nice addition of the month in numbers to this one, which the F91W doesn't have (at least my cheap £9 one), day/date as standard.
Basic alarm/daily alarm, don't expect it to wake you up unless you're an extremely light sleeper (some heavy sleepers might wake up to it, I guess, take my opinion with a pinch of salt on this). Okay to good as a reminder alarm if you're awake though and not around a lot of decibels.
Cannot comment on whether it would hold up to a bit of destruction or throwing it around as I genuinely try to look after my watches and don't fancy breaking it by a brick wall full speed throw test.. I assume it would be okay for the most part for small drops and maybe some larger drops. But it wouldnt surprise me if you dropped it from a 10th floor if it still worked though, it is Casio after all, they do create G-Shock watches, and it is it a digital after all.

I'm into automatics or complications but somehow the Casio charm has rubbed off on me with this watch and now I'm looking at adding a DW5600 to the collection (rather budget collection I must say but I'm more about the appreciation of the craft than a connoisseur).
I'm even thinking about buying another one for if it ever fails or breaks, in (hopefully) decades to come.

Arrived with the tag and all paperwork, purchased from Amazon directly.

Definitely recommended for anyone, from someone needing a watch who just needs the time, a light, month/day/date or basic stopwatch - to a watch enthusiast.

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: I love this range, but this particular set is so lovely, I have bleached wavy hair and it moisturises and leaves it in such fab condition. As soon as you apply the conditioner, the lugs and tangles melt away 🥰

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review:
Update: moving from 4 to 5 stars, my hair will air dry really straight after using this, the more I use this the more impressed I am.
In my 40s, I'm too busy to spend much time on my hair, i have very thick hair, with a bit of a curl and prone to frizziness.
This is a fantastic product that makes my hair look wonderful!!
Original review: Wow this is like a moisture bomb! Used together with the conditioner my hair is really soft and they tame any frizz too! I prefer to wash and allow to dry naturally if possible
with these products my hair dries pretty straight, I add a spray in conditioner, brush and air dry, results are pretty dam straight and mad frizz free, enough to go out with my hair down and look like I tried more than I actually did!! I am very pleased with these, would buy again without hesitation!
My only small issue with this product is that the bottles are identical and you have to stop and find if it's the shampoo or conditioner in the text on the front, it would be better to have 'shampoo' text clearer rather than as part of a block of text on the front so it's easier to grab the right bottle when your washing your hair instead of having to start reading them first!
To sum up, I can allow my hair to air dry and its pretty dam presentable at the end, looks like I've made an effort, while actually making none ;) , no extra hassle so big thumbs up here!
Well worth a go! Go for it!!

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review:
Never have written a review for Amazon, but thought it was important to share for anyone considering.

I had been using this product for a while and noticed my hair starting falling out. It was subtle at first, but as I continued usage with it my hair began falling out in chunks.

Found a forum online where women have experienced similar issues. I switched my shampoo a couple days ago and have already notice way less hair loss.

I don’t know what they put in there but DO NOT BUY. Unless you wanna go bald!!

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: This has exceeded my expectations by far! My hair is normally very dry and not in the best condition due to years of colouring but this first time using it, made my hair soft with a beautiful shine! No weight to it and feels so clean and fresh! The smell is different to most shampoos but none the less not a horrible smell as iv seen others comment. I have very long hair which is normally very tangled after washing but using this has definately decreased the amount of knots. Overall i dont think ill ever go back to other shampoos and conditioners. This is a must buy!

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review:
Well, firstly I want to start by saying this is one of the best set I’ve ever used.
My hair has gone through the trauma of being dyed for years. And whenever I wash it it feels dry even though I use every defence product known to man.
Both of these leave my hair silky smooth and not frizzy. I have fine hair as it is, luckily it’s naturally straight. But I wouldn’t be without this now. Also great if you have extensions in too.
It’s such a cheap price, if you’re reading reviews and contemplating buying them, don’t hesistatr you won’t be disappointed.
The smell is fresh and soft too, cannot daily this product at all.
Amazing and totally recommend.

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: My hair is very high maintenance (like the rest of me!) being bright red, thick and pretty long. I'm a massive fan of Olaplex No 3 for once a week treatment and will use it along side vegan hair dyes like manic panic.First time using Bed Head shampoo and conditioner and it's fantastic. I generally only use Redken for around £55 for the shampoo and conditioner that I have to buy from a hairdressers that stock it. But not anymore!! Decided against it and grabbed a bargain of both of these bottles (being as they're both huge) and were £12 for both in the sale. I thought, with such a huge saving I may as well subscribe every month which I did. This stuff works as well as much more expensive products my hair is used to. Its EXACTLY the same as Redkin for 1/5th of the current sale price!!!! One of the best bargains Ive had on Amazon and now I've subscribed to it every 4 weeks, I'll never run out of it again now. Yay!When this double pack gets below £15, its a unbelievable on price that can't be beaten. Just try it!!!!!!

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: Okay - so I’m devastated for this to be my first review on a product. The first usage was amazing. The shampoo is so moisturising that my over-processed dry hair didn’t tangle or feel extremely dry after washing out the shampoo. And the conditioner is really hydrating yet really really light and gentle. It doesn’t leave residue or feel greasy or heavy on your hair at all. I don’t wash my hair often, only once a week or so. After the second wash using it a week ago I experienced a lot more hair fallout in the shower and everyday since when I’ve brushed my hair dry, so much comes out on to the brush! And my scalp is so sore with hard chunks of dry skin which I’ve never experienced in my life! So maybe it’s just the product reacting to my own scalp. But what it does for the hair otherwise is brilliant.

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: Ordered a couple of times, both times had a bit of a leakage problem, once it came with a pump, the other time it didn’t. Not fussed though as I know how much I should be using on my own hair, and so should every adult lol. This made my hair feel, look, and smell amazing, and I noticed my hair actually grew after using this constantly for about 6 months, it lasts a long time as the bottles are big and i don’t use ridiculous amounts of it, I shower everyday but wash my hair every 3 days and this shampoo and conditioner is just amazing ☺️

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: The shampoo and conditioner left my hair incredibly dry and brittle having said that I donated them to someone with straight hair and they worked wonders. I have wavey 2c with 3a curls and it did not work with personally and my mum gave them a whirl (3C) curls and it dried her hair out also. So if you have straight hair go ahead and try out, if you have wavey/curly hair and plan on keeping those curls perhaps keep looking... The smell is pretty fresh

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: I have swayed for weeks about buying this but I’m glad I did. I have ruined my hair with bleaching. It’s dry and horrible and nothing seems to make it look nice but one wash with this shampoo and conditioner and I already notice a difference. It’s softer and shinier. My only gripe is the smell. It’s not unpleasant I’m just not a fan of fruity smells, it’s almost peachy sweet and a little sickly.

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: I buy bras head regularly but this one was disgusting. The shampoo smelled completely fine but the conditioner smells like it’s been left in a warehouse for the last 20 years.Used it once on my hair and threw it in the bin. It made my hair feel rough and stiff which had never been the case with and bed head I have used before.Won’t be buying again.

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: As a new mum suffering with post partum dry, brittle hair and hair loss, this shampoo and conditioner has really helped bring my hair back to life. My ends were looking half dead, my scalp lifeless and greasy, but then I began using bed head to rescue my hair and I am not disappointed. I feel for the amount of product you get for the price too is just amazing! I will continue to order this shampoo and conditioner as it also smells amazing. I ordered it for my mum too I was that impressed!

Product: Bed Head by Tigi Urban Antidotes Recovery Moisture Shampoo and Conditioner Set, 2 x 750ml
Review: I’ve only used this once so can’t comment on whether or not it does your hair any goodBut I love how big they are, how cheap they are, the smell is nice I wouldn’t say fruity or if it is then very mild, not over powering. The conditioner is really thick too which I like means you don’t have to use a shit ton. Will definitely be buying again.

Product: Dettol Antibacterial Laundry Cleanser Additive, Fresh Cotton, Multipack of 4 x 1.5 Litre (Packaging May Vary)
Review: I am 84 years old, and ever since I was a child I have known Dettol. Growing up with 2 boisterous brothers we had our share of knocks and bruises: my mother (Dad's in the War.) always took away the pain; with Dettol! the magic potion. I used it with my own three children, I use it now, Happy to use it in the Wash! It gives a certain reassurance, it is still taking care of me.

Product: Dettol Antibacterial Laundry Cleanser Additive, Fresh Cotton, Multipack of 4 x 1.5 Litre (Packaging May Vary)
Review:
I made the fatal error of leaving washing in a washing machine then going on holiday for a week.

No matter how many times I boil washed then used machine cleaner, I could not get the smell out of the machine and subsequently any clothes washed in it.

Out of desperation I used this product, magically my machine now has no mould smell and my clothes smell fresh and clean. Not only do they smell fresh, they smell fantastic and so now I use this with every wash.

Would, highly, highly recommend this, both if you have a damp smelling machine, your clothes start to smell a bit stale after washing, or you just love smelling nice.

Product: Dettol Antibacterial Laundry Cleanser Additive, Fresh Cotton, Multipack of 4 x 1.5 Litre (Packaging May Vary)
Review: I have been using this Dettol antibacterial laundry product for years and put a cupful in with every wash, irrespective of whether I’m washing whites, bedding or my work uniform.  You can use it in the washing machine or soak heavily soiled/contaminated items in a stronger solution.  Every household should use it!

Product: Dettol Antibacterial Laundry Cleanser Additive, Fresh Cotton, Multipack of 4 x 1.5 Litre (Packaging May Vary)
Review: I like this product. The fact it is antibacterial makes me keep buying it again and again. I have young children and I find very convenient just to pour some Detol laundry cleanser in the washing machine and I can rest assured that it kills bacteria and viruses . Of course this not visible but I trust this brand as it is with good reputation and tested. The scent itself is very nice and delicate but I can not detect it after washing and drying clothes. I feel my laundry fresh. I think it is good value for money and definitely worth it buying it.

Product: Dettol Antibacterial Laundry Cleanser Additive, Fresh Cotton, Multipack of 4 x 1.5 Litre (Packaging May Vary)
Review: This is a really good product, I purchased it in January for under £11.00, it is now over £64.00 !! This company is cashing in on the Coronavirus, it’s an absolute disgrace, they should be ashamed of themselves, DO NOT BUY

Product: Dettol Antibacterial Laundry Cleanser Additive, Fresh Cotton, Multipack of 4 x 1.5 Litre (Packaging May Vary)
Review: I use this stuff so that I can launder at lower temperature/faster cycles, but remove bacteria from the endless laundry - boys' football kit/socks, swimming gear,  dog's blankets etc.  I cannot prove that it works, but the laundry is fresh and I have peace of mind that even at 30 degrees, it's allegedly bacteria-free.  Certainly seems sweet-smelling!  Arrived well packed in a box with separators inside.

Product: Dettol Antibacterial Laundry Cleanser Additive, Fresh Cotton, Multipack of 4 x 1.5 Litre (Packaging May Vary)

Product: Dettol Antibacterial Laundry Cleanser Additive, Fresh Cotton, Multipack of 4 x 1.5 Litre (Packaging May Vary)
Review: Not sure why I bought four bottles of this — it's absolutely awful. On the plus side, it probably kills bacteria. But at what cost? When I use it to wash sportswear we have to dry it inside and that horrible chemical raspberry smell floats into every nook and cranny of the house. You can feel it in the back of your throat and in your chest. Heaven knows what it's doing to your skin. It's also very watery, presumably so it feels like you're getting more for your money, but this is also going to be bumping up its environmental impact — as well as those chemicals entering the watercourse. Definitely won't be buying any more!

Product: Dettol Antibacterial Laundry Cleanser Additive, Fresh Cotton, Multipack of 4 x 1.5 Litre (Packaging May Vary)
Review:
Ah, the good old days of washing clothes at 60C knowing they’re clean are well and truly gone, unless of course you like your jumpers etc coming out of the machine the size of a facecloth and fitting your child’s barbie or action man perfectly.
So here I am, more and more of my clothes state 30C, even my new underwear! So along with this and an increasing scummy mould problem in the door seal and detergent drawer, believe me, I even took ‘professional’ advice and bought sachets of which I was promised work, hard to find but they’re so worth it and religiously used them as advised. But the problem was just getting worse as the years went by.
So I thought to myself what to do next? Ah, go on amazon and scour the reviews. As much as it galls me to buy not only washing detergent but a cleanser too where a good old 60C wash used to do the trick for the clothes AND the machine, I succumbed and bought the dettol cleanser. All I can say is...
WOW, it actually works!
Firstly to tackle the machine issues I used a bottle of dettol machine cleaner, well I was so pleasantly surprised with this and a few weeks down the line there’s still no mould growing back. Secondly I add only 1 capful of the cleanser in with the softener, and yes, this too works & doesn’t take away from the softness of ones clothes.
After reading other reviews and advice from dettol, the liquid is to be used ONLY in the softener drawer as putting it in the detergent drawer will diminish the action of the cleanser, can’t fit 2 capfuls in AND the softener? Hence why I only put one cap in with softener.
Genuinely, I’m gobsmacked! The machine cleaner has given my machine a new lease of life and I no longer dread having to clean scum from the door seal or spending ages scrubbing the detergent drawer and it’s casing most weeks.
Although I’m still rather cross at not being able to do a hot wash like the old days, as although it says that it’s to save money on electricity and the environment, I still believe that a hot wash is more environmentally friendly than buying even more detergent to battle the ‘low temp mould issues’ which itself needs a factory, more chemicals, thousands of litres of water to dilute it, and more plastic manufacturing in which to store the cleanser, not to mention the fuel and traffic congestion to get said cleanser to the shops etc.
Sure I don’t have to buy it, but then I’m fighting mould issues, fusty smelling clothing and a smelly machine..... it’s only 6 years old, plumbed in the kitchen so shouldn’t have these issues, it’s all down to temp.
So for that reason only, I’ve reluctantly converted to the dettol cleanser, and I’m in no way disappointed, it’s smashing and I believe it’s also helping to keep the machine mould threat at bay as when I wipe round the door seal and check the detergent drawer there’s absolutely NO mould and the washing smells naturally fresh, there’s no distinct ‘in yer face’ detergent smell, only that of your softener.
All that said, I highly recommend this cleanser and used with the dettol machine cleaner I no longer have mould and frousty smells emanating from my machine, so a huge thumbs up from me. 👍🏻

Product: NIVEA Soft (500ml), A Moisturising Cream for Face, Body and Hands with Vitamin E and Jojoba Oil, Hand Cream Moisturises Deeply, All-Purpose Day Cream (Packaging May Vary)
Review: I Was completely blown away when I received this product not only because of the tub size but how much it cost. I paid this amount for a smaller size for my daughters Christmas, out of the shops. I was a bit skeptic about buying this because I've known Nivea to be quite thick on the face, but I bought it anyway. After applying it, it makes my face soft as a babys bum 😂 my face has a very lovely glow and it smells amazing. It also doesn't have that thick feel too it anymore. The delivery was a day early. Yes I would recommend this product not only for the amount you get, or for the price but because it makes your face feel amazing

Product: NIVEA Soft (500ml), A Moisturising Cream for Face, Body and Hands with Vitamin E and Jojoba Oil, Hand Cream Moisturises Deeply, All-Purpose Day Cream (Packaging May Vary)
Review: I was amazed to find this at such a competitive price and it arrived the next day.  I've used this for years having occasionally tried alternatives but always returning to this.  It's a shame you cannot order more than one tub.  I wanted a couple so as to have one tub upstairs and one downstairs and had to order one tub one two consecutive days. Perhaps Amazon would reconsider and allow two per order which would save them the packing and delivery costs of two separate orders.

Product: NIVEA Soft (500ml), A Moisturising Cream for Face, Body and Hands with Vitamin E and Jojoba Oil, Hand Cream Moisturises Deeply, All-Purpose Day Cream (Packaging May Vary)
Review: Has a lovely scent, very light but fresh, such a lovely texture and my skin has been insanely soft since starting using it (and I've tried a lot of different moisturisers). The pot it comes in is huge and it's extremely good value for money. I use it twice a day on my face, under my makeup and then before bed, as well as all over my body as it's just lovely. Will definitely be buying again. Could not recommend this any more highly.

Product: NIVEA Soft (500ml), A Moisturising Cream for Face, Body and Hands with Vitamin E and Jojoba Oil, Hand Cream Moisturises Deeply, All-Purpose Day Cream (Packaging May Vary)
Review: This cream goes into my skin and absorbs very well without any weird residue. I have oily skin that is really sensitive and creams such as cerave or cetaphil give me a rash and break me out but this is my favourite cream that leaves my skin feeling and looking smooth. A tub of it lasts for ages, it's very affordable, and can be used both on your body and face.

Product: NIVEA Soft (500ml), A Moisturising Cream for Face, Body and Hands with Vitamin E and Jojoba Oil, Hand Cream Moisturises Deeply, All-Purpose Day Cream (Packaging May Vary)
