Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Awful! Purchased after reading reviews that it had no strange aftertaste. How wrong are all those reviews! Horrible cooling aftertaste. Peanut butter cookies are ruined and now I’m stuck with a big bag of it. Disappointed.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: about this product.  I have tried Stevia as a sugar alternative but found it left a nasty aftertaste.  I was dubious about buying this product but am glad that I did.  I took the plunge after having read that Tom Kerridge used it when trying to lose weight and that he cooks with it in his recipes.  I do not normally use sugar in tea or coffee but I do use sugar/sweetener when cooking with tomatoes and some asian dishes.  I have found it a good substitute for sugar but a word of warning do not over do it. When first using, start off with a little until you find the desired quantity for the amount of taste you need.  Best to err on the side of just under sweet and not go full out for an OTT sweetness.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review:
We have been using this as sugar substitution for years. Really happy with it. In fact we tried several other options and always ended up back with this. We use it like for like to sugar - i.e. if I was to use a tbs of sugar for something I just use a tbs of this. Honestly if some ppl think that a sweetener will be same tastes as sugar they are lying to themselves.
1kg last long as well and we are a family of 3. I would also definitely recommend this for a great sugar substitute for someone on diet and looking to loose weight.

My wife after giving birth to our son, she has now lost about 30kgs so far and still going - of course she was eating well and does exercise, however if she did not care about swapping small things like sugar she would not have achieved her goals. Letting go of bad sugar and salt are a start of healthy lifestyle. This product is definitely recommended.

P.S there a lot of fake reviews - I can confirm that ours is genuine and we did not get gifts or pay to write the above :)

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review:
I bought this as a potential alternative for aspartame based sweetener and was also interested in the fact it was zero calories and did not affect blood sugar levels.

However, I have found the product isn't anywhere near as sweet as other sugar substitutes so more is needed which will result in more expense in the long run. Also, I don't feel it is good for use in cold dishes. For breakfast, I tend to have porridge oats mixed with yogurt and sweetener - when I used Erythritol, it didn't dissolve properly so I was left with an unpleasant gritty texture to my meal. It dissolves properly in my tea so I have concluded it is better for hot dishes or for baking.

I can't see me buying this again in a hurry. A shame because it sounded so promising. Perhaps if the product could be ground down finer as to dissolve more easily, I could be persuaded.

3 out of 5 overall from me.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I normally buy Finish Xylitol but owing to price increase thought I would try Erythritol as it seemed to work out a bit cheaper. How wrong I was!1 the amount you have to use in comparison to Xylitol negates the lower price- I was truly surprised how little sweetness it has.2 Taste - I really didn’t like the flavour at all. Very syntheticNeedless to say I am very disappointed and feel I’ve wasted my money.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Honestly i love the concept of erythitol in theory. A sugar substitute that doesn't cause insulin response (in me anyway) and is a great basically 0 calorie substitute that tastes better than stevia and is better in drinks than ones like sucralose etc not damaging unlike the reported effects of aspartame and all that (possibly. Don't know if those are definitively proven yet) BUT in practice i just cannot go a day with having this AND solid craps. It just liquifies my insides which is so unfortunate because this has been my go to sweetner for a while it just doesn't do me well. Looks like it's time to venture into xylitol for me

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I thought this would taste like Natvia, which is a great product based mostly on erythritol, but would be better value.  I used the NKD in some  some home-made lemonade.  It hardly works at all, in fact it was so ineffective that I ended up tasting a spoonful of it to see if there was any sweetness at all.  There was hardly any. Using large quantities of erythritol can give you a nasty stomach ache, so I ended up adding sugar!  I'm going back to Natvia - it looks more expensive but you do get sweetness for your money.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Good quality sweetener , has a slight cooling taste , you don’t need a lot to make things sweet. Lasts a long time, great for my keto diet whenever I have a sweet craving I make chocolate brownies.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I have been trying all sorts of sugar substitutes since being on Keto diet. This is certainly the best one. No chemical taste or reaction on my throat. I even managed to make meringues with it!! Tip on that is to buy the powdered one, or this one blitzed up in your liquidiser (which I did). Another tip is that it's very sweet so you don't need much of it, and certainly a lot less than normal cane sugar.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Ok well in these crazy times there is a shortage of everything. So as I have recently weaned myself off of refined sugar and I could not get hold of any raw honey, thought I would try this. I made some muffins, which looked great, but then I tried one. A taste difficult to describe, but a bit life getting some medicine stuff in your mouth when trying to swallow. Also noticed the muffins dried up extremely quickly, in a matter of hours, not days. So alas I won't be using this again, just not for me & will stick to natural raw honey.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I have been using this in baking and sauces and have found it works very well. No after taste so far ( I used it in apple sauce and a carrot cake).I do not use sweetener in anything else but from reviews it seems that it is not suitable in drinks and leaves an after taste. My next try will be Stevia , but only if I could get granulated one , using similar amount to sugar in baking. For me psychologically does not work to add a tablespoon of sweetener instead of cup and half of sugar!

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I thought I’d try this sweetener as a change from my usual Splenda sachets and simply because I was getting fed up with some sachets being full, others part full (more part empty) or completely empty.  I only use sweetener products for coffee and I only drink espressos because I like the taste of a strong and even bitter start to the day.This product is granulated so it isn’t just a case of throwing the sweetener into the bottom of the cup, but that’s fine, with the amount needed being very similar to the amount of sugar. But this product is not good with espressos (maybe other hot drinks too?), the taste is very specific -not good - and gives a very bitter or sour taste that is almost metallic, just like you’ve absorbed some of your blood after cutting your finger. The metallic taste hangs around for ages, Although I guess that’s just because coffee hangs around too.I’ve gone back to sugar until my order of Splenda arrives.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: This product is a very nice one! It smells really inviting. I love it. Don’t be tempted to use too much as too much of everything is not recommended in my own opinion. I have not tried to use too much though. I am trying to stay away from sugar and had to be good to myself and not to be tempted to use much. I use very little of this and I am satisfied. It’s far better than nothing. You should not expect it to taste like sugar. It tastes really good and very very mild sweetness. Doesn’t taste like sweeter either.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: The size and price of the product is great,however,i have to put loads to tea/coffee/food etc. to actually taste the sweetness. As i said that-that was my first ever time i tried Erythritol so maybe it should taste like that as i’ve always used stevia which is just stronger in my opinion.It’s great for someone who likes a delicate sweet flavour :) So all in all not bad

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review:
Great stuff, don't be confused by the carb count as it doesn't mean anything. The carbs in this don't get absorbed.

So it really is perfect for dieting. To be honest even when I'm not on a diet I'll be using this stuff instead, no aftertaste imo, just tastes like sugar, you do need to use more than you would for sugar though.

I wish it was cheaper but for some reason we have to pay more for trying to better ourselves, doesn't make sense so this loses a star.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review:
Loved it. Perfect. And lots of it for the price. Thought I would need to mix with Stevia to remove any aftertaste ( some brands you do, as they both cancel out each others aftertastes) but for this one I didn't have to. There is no aftertaste as far as I can see. It's so good I can't believe I'm "allowed" to have it on keto.

My favourite is frozen raspberries in a cup, add 10% greek yoghurt, add cream, add this erithritol, add ground cinnamon, and mash it all up with a spoon and then eat it.

Best dessert ever!!

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I have to be honest I haven't tried this with baking yet... However, I've used it in my tea and coffee and I can't taste anything?? Then i added some more because it does state on the packaging that it's not as sweet as sugar and again I can't taste anything.  My dad went to try some just out of curiosity and even he said he couldn't taste anything?? It was just like having no sugar in his tea... plus, for me I seem to get a bitter aftertaste in my mouth...I'm going to try it in some baking before I think of disposing of it as it's not cheap...

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Personally I’m not convinced. I’m on a keto diet and currently fasting for three days which l have done many times before and three spoonfuls of this in a coffee threw me out of ketosis for about 36 hours. I don’t know much about this sugar substitute but had heard good things from others on similar diets so thought I’d give it a try. It tastes good and I’m sure if your are on a standard diet it’s great but personally l wouldn’t recommend it for keto diet.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: My first impression was that this was huge ! Didn't realise how large it was. I have come to loathe artificial sweeteners so just wanted to try it out. This is THE BEST artificial sweetener ! I am quite astonished. It is less sweet than sugar but it looks like it and tastes like it. It comes in crystals that look very much like sugar and so far I couldn't detect aftertaste. I've been experimenting with gelatin deserts and this is great.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I didn’t realise that this doesn’t dissolve like sugar.  My fault perhaps, but it’s sold as a sugar replacement so it didn’t cross my mind.  I made some lemon curd.  I ground the powder finer as per the recipe.  The end result was inedible in my opinion.  It was grainy, and didn’t taste very nice at all.  A nasty aftertaste too.  Won’t be buying again.  I’ve given this to someone else to try - apparently the aftertaste varies between people, so they may well get on with it better.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I've tried it multiple times and this has worked really well. It's almost as sweet as sugar cause you need to use more but no bitter aftertaste and it's really good with baking. I read people commented on eating too much gave them headaches or stomach ache and could tell you one day I ate 2 small desserts made with this and my belly was feeling funny. I don't how why that could be so keep that in mind, it might be different for different people though. Love that is has 0 calories.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Although the texture of this product resembled that of a sugar, I needed to use double the amount to achieve desired sweetness, therefore making it an expensive substitute. Also the packing of the product was faulty as the grip-seal was loose when I opened it.  But despite all this, I will be buying it again, as 0 calories and 0 carbs means I can stuff my face guilt free.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review:
This is a great sugar alternative, one of the best in fact, to break addiction.
Not only it is not digested - so close to zero GI and calories - but also there is no aftertaste, it works well in baking and looks the part too.

To add to all that, other than potentially laxative if eaten in large amounts (we're talking 100+ grams here), there are no negative effects.

I use to usexylitol

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: This was recommended by a nutritionist as the best sweetener because it isn't carcinogenic and doesn't cause flatulence.  I do find it bitter though.  Given the choice of putting it in coffee or having coffee without sugar, I go for the latter although the only way I actually enjoy coffee is when it is sweet.If you want it for baking, please disregard my comments as I haven't tested it in baking.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I only discovered erythritol fairly recently but wish I had known about it before. It is by far the best sweetener I have found - easy to use, no bitter aftertaste and very versatile. I use it straight on cereals etc and also use it in cooking and baking with great results. Although a fairly generic product, this particular brand is really nice and well packaged in a resealable bag. I have tried their other erythritol products too and they are just as good.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Best sweetener out there, with the added benefit of being 100% digestible - this means that whereas I suffer with stomach cramps, discomfort, and flatulence (seriously, those Slimming World bars resulted in way too much crop-dusting of my office block!), erythritol comes with no nasty surprises.Yes, there is a slight aftertaste, but nowhere nearly as bad as other options on the market.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review:
Great item, and in my opinion one of the best sugar substitutes out there taste-wise: though perhaps use modestly, and check reviews/articles for how some people have unwanted side effects (good article on Erythritol on Wikipedia).

Unfortunately one of the three packages that I've recently ordered on a monthly subscription basis was leaking.

In all fairness I should say that I've ordered this item previously from the seller on a one off basis three times previously and have never encountered this as an issue before.

Not sure if this is a coincidence, or, logistically, something to do with how different kinds of orders are fulfilled. So, got to say on this occasion, I'm not feeling "fulfilled", and would probably cancel the subscription if it's a recurring issue!

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Great fast delivery and packaged well. Sweetener tastes really good and doesn't have that gross bitter taste. It does have a similar ''cooling'' taste that Xylitol does.I am type 1 diabetic on a low carb diet to improve sugars and maintain a healthy weight and this sweetener is really nice mixed with cocoa powder. Be careful of the warnings though, I've had some stomach pain/bloating the last day or so, but I probably just ate too much of it because I have a sweet tooth. It could also be coincidence. No poops for me tho, only bloating and butt toots.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Like most things, trying to strike the right balance when using this to bake something easy like peanut butter cookies is getting the amount of sugar to use - or in this product. Although the package says to use a little more, you actually need to add another 10-15g to get the right consistency for baking.There is a horrible after taste when used in tea.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I have been using this product a while now and like the taste.  As a diabetic I stopped using sugar which raised my blood glucose levels but having a sweet tooth I had to find an alternative.  I use erythritol because it doesn't raise my blood glucose levels.  I also find it more effective as a sweetner when I add liquid stevia with it.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review:
I can't drink tea or coffee without having 2 teaspoons of sugar in and considering I'm trying to shift the final 1.5 stone to reach my goal weight, I figured cutting sugar and minimising on carbs was a start.
As the title suggests, it's not sugar, but for someone who is an avid tea drinker, 2.5 teaspoons of this in a nice strong brew isnt actually that bad!
I'd definitely say it's something i can get used to.
I've not yet tried it in baking but I cant see it being bad, the product is the same texture as granulated sugar so I'd imagine would act the same way.

Pros:
• no bad after taste
• not far off the taste of sugar in a good brew
•good price and packaging

Con:
• Weird smell (but you cant smell it once its mixed in to something!)

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I don't usually make an effort to review a product, but I had to drop a review here.  Currently on a quest to find the perfect sugar substitute- PCOS has made me incredibly sensitive to sugar, but I also crave it like crazy.  So far I've hated all substitutes I've tried, but this one *actually* tastes like sugar- a weaker version of sugar, but still sugar.  No gross aftertaste like stevia, just a slightly cooling effect in the mouth if you eat it by itself.Am currently enjoying a cup of tea with this stuff- being Asian AND British, tea is life, and it tastes exactly like a sweet cup of tea should.I'll definitely be forking out for this on the regular :D

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Tried this yesterday for the 1st time as being sugar sweetner that had no after taste and this was recommended by all the online comments which were very accurate and helpful with no after taste, tastes like sugar with ZERO calories and ideal for baking etc if you are watching your weight etc

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Really unhappy with purchase, this stuff is horrible. Not very sweet and numbs/cools the mouth. Rubbish in baking, wasted other ingredients as inedible :(

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I bought this specifically to do a Tom Kerridge recipe - I’d never heard of it before reading his book.  It worked just as Tom said it would and produced an incredibly good low-carb soda bread, which toasted well.I’m currently experimenting at using it in some of my other home-bakes, and so far it has worked quite well.  Nothing has been a total disaster, although some recipes have obviously got to have the sweetening quantities adjusted slightly.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Not used in baking yet but after i started keto and was cold turkey from sugar in my coffee. I bought this  as I was craving a lil sweetness and when it came and put in my coffee it was amazing. It really hit the spot!No after taste in my drink at all. I cant wait to try it in a baking recipe and will update when i do

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: It's a good sugar replacement but there is a cooling sensation which might out some of you off. Both times I've ordered, the side of the bag had burst a little, leaving us with grainy shelves. The plastic is almost too brittle. It's not a disaster but something the manufacturer should work on.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: If you have a sweet tooth and are trying to lose weight this is pretty much a must have, I know some people say there's an awful taste but for me it tastes great I mix it with warm almond milk for a very low calorie sweet drink, a little pricey but overall I will be buying again. Only thing I'm uncertain of is the claim that that it has zero calories, it's hard to believe there is absolutely no calories in the whole bag but after a quick bit of googling apparently it's true, which makes it a very good tool for weight loss in my opinion

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: This stuff bakes and tastes exactly like sugar. I've been using it in everything from cheesecakes to tea to cookies and there is no bitter aftertaste at all unlike some of the other sweeteners on the market. The only thing is that it's quite expensive but I suppose you get the quality you pay for. Would buy again.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Used this to make an almond “sponge” cake. Found the cake was a little more crumbly than normal although tasted great but then I used it to make flourless choc chip cookies. Oh my goodness these were amazing and I’m not a big cookie fan. Scoffed the lot in 2 days. WOW

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Not what I was expecting there's no taste at all you are better of with out it

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: This is the best sugar substitute by far - No after taste or bitter kick, can be used in cooking and has no calories . expensive - yes , but it is worth it as its such a healthier substitute if you have a sweet tooth and need that sweetness in your tea , coffee and cakes . Very pleased with this find and will continue to purchase . Try the whole range ( brown and icing sugar)

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: You need to use 4x as much of this as you would use Stevia. Very weak and taste like plastic

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Not sweet at all and it’s suppose to be good in baking it has no sweetness ruined my cookies and the price is a bit steep for something that doesn’t do a thing!!!

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I bought this after seeing its positive reviews,  but I do regret my decision now.  Although the price is good comparing to the quantity you get, there is no real value in it as you need loads of it to get any sweet taste. I put loads and could not break the bitterness in a cup of coffee! How can I use it for baking then? It also smells funny. You can tell it is not natural. I do not recommend it at all.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I love a lot the erythritol and I buy it frequently. I use it not only for my coffee/tea but also to make cakes, biscuits etc.I would like to suggest you don't use too much of this sugar especially when you make a cake for example, because the taste can be stronger and you may not like it.I highly recommend it because it's very healthy instead of to use a normal sugar.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I always struggled to cut down the innate of suger and bought this thinking that it will help me cut down calories.  A small amount does not make much difference but you cannot use it in a large amount. the flavour is not the best.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Been on a low carb diet and using recipes by Tom Kerridge who uses erythritol so chose this product based on reviews. Really like that it gives you comparison to sugar ratio to use in recipes. Made a few things with it and am very impressed. Would definitely recommend and would buy it again.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: a couple of teaspoons makes me dizzy not sure whyalso used it to bake muffins which taste good but also make me dizzyflavour is knda odd but it gives a good sweetness. will continue to use but in small doses and not baking

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: It's excellent replacement of sugar and much cheaper than Stevia. The taste is slightly different indeed, however, considering that it is 0 calories, the low price and the fact that it is used mostly for cooking, it's bot such a big deal. As the description say, it is slightly less sweet than sugar

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Haven't bake with erythritol yet but put into my coffee and teas . The powder is very fine and it taste like a sugar ( very close to it, you will feel the difference though, it is more pleasant, there is no after taste or anything) + "0" on glycemic index.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Use wherever you use granulated sugar, eggy bread  cakes, tea, coffee and hot chocolate. It's really good. No sour after taste like stevia or saccharine and no super cooling like sorbitol or xylitol. It's just sweet.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Haven’t used this yet, but I hear good things. I don’t expect it to taste like sugar when it’s not the same but I’m excited it’s a natural equivalent.I’ll be using in cakes than anything else and will feedback with cupcakes flavour once tried...

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Bakes like sugar and taste like sugar??? WHATEVER! Tastes awful and ruined the taste of my cake. It tasted like acid.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Great quality. But the bag doesn’t seal securely and my mum spilt a lot. So definitely put in something more secure. Definitely need to use more. Add a touch of salt to bring out flavour in dishes. Great in tea. Used in sweet dessert too.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Brilliant for the Keto diet. I make delicious Keto desserts with this and the powdered variety! I couldn’t be without it and wouldn’t have been able to keep going on Keto for 10 months without having home made Keto treats!

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I bought this erythirol when I decided to do keto diet. I used it to cook cake and cookies with almond flour and coconut oil. The taste was the same as the normal sugar and it is cooked as normal.The only difference is it is 0 calorie !

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: best sugar alternative I ever tried, taste like sugar and you can use it in your shakes and baking, best thing is that my wife use it in her daily coffee. my kids love it and now they can use it in their daily routine.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: You would need to add many teaspoonful to feel the sweetie taste. I have tried different products and they usually taste so sugary with using half a teaspoonful.  I just bought that one because i thought it would be a good deal for that price.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Works out a lot cheaper than buying small bags of truvia in the supermarket. Need to use slightly more than ordinary granulated...I used 50:50 in marmalade making and still set fine although didn't make as much marmalade.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Taste like sugar. Its great for cooking, baking, teas, coffees and pudding.great for diabetes and people on diets as it doesn't rise sugar in your blood as regular cane sugar does.Highty recommend this product although price could be a little lower ;)

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Used it in place of sugar to bake a Keto chocolate cake. As a diabetic it's difficult to describe the level of joy being able to eat  chocolate cake, that tasted like a chocolate cake  without feeling unwell.  I've used a few sugar substitutes before but this is easily the best, no aftertaste and granular consistency like real sugar. I would recommend this product and this seller, who dispatched promptly and with good comms. I will be back at some point to buy more.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Helped with my one meal a day diet and does not have the horrible after taste of sweeteners so was really happy with the purchase, would recomend to anyone looking for a sugar or sweetnerer substitute.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Nicest alternative to sugar I've had, and I have tried quite a few, no nasty aftertaste, can be used in cookingGood on your breakfast, great in coffee or tea. Also doesn't contain aspartamine

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I have tried so many sugar replacements and just don't like the taste. I felt this was another expensive experiment to try yet another sugar replacement but I was not disappointed. In fact I have just put in for my second order. Yes it's expensive in comparison but if you are watching your intake you won't be gulping this back.... have used in recipes too. I never leave reviews but this is such a find I felt it was deserved. No horrible after taste, great in my morning coffee....Well done the creators.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I really hoped this was good based on the reviews but really disappointed! Leaves a strange after taste specially when I used in a cake. My cake was ruined, which tastes good with normal sugar. I have used a different brand Erythritol before and it was better than this. I will need to find that one again now!

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Love this range! I have used it in coffee and cooking, works really well with both. Has a "lighter" taste than sugar and doesn't leave your mouth feeling "heavy". Very versatile and fits in perfectly with keto plans.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I absolutely love this product,it's super sweet and super healthy,I'm dego staying with u guys for ordering more as soon as I need more ,love the fresh packaging and the taste is just No1! Thank you for making it for us keto people 💙💙💙💙💙

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: The product is great as sugar substitute, has a mild bitterness if used in paired weight as the sugar, therefore I learned to always use less than the normal amount of sugar. Also, this product do not melt like tagatese but definitely has its strong features of 0 carbs- if you look for this aspect particularly.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: One of the better sweeteners, found brilliant and tastes like sugar when used in or food such as cereal, however when used in hot drinks such as tea/coffee slight aftertaste but not in your face as much as normal sweeteners.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Disappointed,Having to use much more than normal sugar to achieve similar desired sweetness with  breakfast cereals and morning coffee etc thus means no cheaper than using the real thing.So, having given it a try,will be returning to my favorite T and L in due course .

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Helps pcos cravings and diabetes glad I found it and it doesnt mess with hormones like other sugar alternativesA cooling taste afterwards. I dont mind and when ur adding it to cake drinks etc it's not so bad.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: It’s great for baking and use in teas or coffee , mixes very well and a better taste than the grain Erythritol but only problem is you need double the amount for sweetness than the grain Erythritol

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Really good. You just need to use a bit more than you'd do with sugar, but it's worth it. Great value for money as in shops you'll pay about £5 for 300 grams on similar products

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I didn't really notice any difference in the taste until the last bake I made for a chocolate cake. It had a strange after taste, like a bitter, spicy taste at the back of your throat which ruined the cake. Although it's cheaper than Xylitol, I'm not sure it's worth it.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Great for my Keto diet and love the fact it tastes virtually like sugar but with no aftertaste 👍😀 been using this brand for over 2 years in cooking, baking and drinks 🙏⭐️

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: The best low calorie sweetener I’ve come across by far - tastes just like sugar, with no aftertaste at all unlike stevia which I find absolutely disgusting. It’s the same as xylitol but without the calories. There is a slight cooling sensation if you taste it by itself but this is not noticeable if in hot drinks / on cereal / fruit / etc. No digestive issues either. Highly recommend.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Was previously buying xylitol but got a puppy and wasn't going to risk using it. This is very similar with no taste just sweet. Will buy again. Can't stand sweetners with an after taste.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Not sweet enough. Poor quality or it is not 100% pure product. Need to use 2x more than from other brands whats not good at all! Very dissapointed. Added to coffee, cappuccino and the same amount as used with different brand and was not sweet at all, ruined the taste od coffee. Waste of money! Disgusting taste.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: My family is happy with this, but I don’t like the taste of this, ver artificial and a bad aftertasteI’ll keep using coconut sugar which is the least “bad” of the standard sugars

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I would have rated it higher if there wasn’t a hole in the packet. A lot of the “sugar” had covered the bottom corners and it was such a mess to open. Value for money would’ve been worth it if some of the product hadn’t have gone wasted.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Our family follow the keto diet and this is very keto friendly, so we use it a lot in both cooking and making hot drinks..it dissolves well and is a fantastic replacement for sugar!

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Doesn't taste that bad! I mean it doesn't taste like sugar but what do you expect!? Is not sugar! I bought this to bake otherwise I prefer to use agave syrup as the taste is much better!

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: I’m following the keto diet and brought this product as it’s one of the only sugars that is recommended for keto ..I use it to make cakes and cookies ..after all who wants a life without a cookie ?

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Love this sweetener. I use it in tea and coffee all the time. I have used in baking too, but it has a slightly 'cool' sensation so is best used with flavours that work well with that such as mint and citrus. The best bit is that this sweetener passes through the body without causing a laxative or gassy affect like some other polyols do!

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Great product. Taste good, you have to use more but it's worth it. Doesn't upset my stomach like Xyitol does either. Great speedy delivery that has never let me down.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: My husband is diabetic, this stuff has no after taste, works well in cakes etc as well as drinks and doesn't mess with his blood sugar.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: It doesnt taste like sugar and has a really funky smell that really puts you off. I'm considering just throwing it away.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Real taste is not normal . It taste stingy kind of . No good .

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: To be honest this product is terrible . It’s smells so bad n taste so bad . It gives you Luke a chemical burning sensation when you eat it with cereal . Went straight to my bin

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Tastes just like sugar. May need just over a teaspoon to get that 1 tsp flavour. Does not leave an aftertaste like sweeteners.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement
Review: Item came the next day! I would recommend it. Using this product to bake if my dad wants something sweet. Goos for cooking and baking for people who are diabetic.

Product: 100% Natural Erythritol 1 Kg (2.2 lb) Granulated ZERO Calorie Sugar Replacement

Review:
If you are on Keto, this is fantastic. Its none GMO for a start , whcih alraedy puts it ahead of some of the competition. It has the amazing ability to make you forget you are even on keto, finally i was able to make real sweet tasting deserts.

It has a very similar texture to sugar, and i find i dont have to add too much to really give a meal that sweet taste i want. Ive used it for all sorts form waffles, to sponge cakes to fudge. And ive recently started experimenting with my currys, and have made an unreal passanda with this.

I see people say that its not as sweet as sugar, but i disagree. It is really sweet, and definitly ads enough to make you forget that you miss that sweetness in your baking.

Product: COSRX Advanced Snail 96 Mucin Essence 100ml | Snail Mucin 96% Skin Repair Serum | Lightweight Facial Moisturiser with Snail Mucus | Korean Skin Care, Cruelty Free, Paraben Free, Alcohol Free
Review:
Ok, so I have tried everything in the past, but nothing comes close to this for reducing/preventing acne and also fading hyperpigmentation marks. Btw I have brown asian skin. I saw a huge difference difference within the first day and now in week 2 my skin is glowing!! I am not claiming marks will go away overnight, but you will see a difference very quickly (obviously depending on how bad your skin is). You have to be consistent and patient if you want marks to fade. Another thing I noticed, since using this gel any new spot that is forming, instead of becoming a full blown pimple, it stays small and goes away within a day or two and leaves no mark.

I use 3 pumps on my face twice daily after washing face with cool water (not ice cold!). This gel feels so cool and soothing on the skin kind of like aloe vera gel. No fragarance or any nasty chemicals in this which I love.

I don't use this with any other moisturiser as I feel that will dilute the goodness of this product and make it less effective, however, I may need to do that in the winter if my skin starts drying up! So far during the summer this product is good enough on it's own as a moisturiser. If you are using a moisturiser with this, make sure it's oil free otherwise you may end up causing spots despite using this great product.

Good to use underneath foundation as on my skin it has a primer like finish, but could just be that I am using a 'compatible' foundation that looks great with this underneath. Product: COSRX Advanced Snail 96 Mucin Essence 100ml | Snail Mucin 96% Skin Repair Serum | Lightweight Facial Moisturiser with Snail Mucus | Korean Skin Care, Cruelty Free, Paraben Free, Alcohol Free
Review: I've tried this product a couple of times, and after the 2nd I was sure this is what was causing my breakouts. I'm so disappointed because I really wanted to love this. While it does help with hydration, it also caused an inflammatory reaction - at least for me. I've used other snail products and have gotten the same result. I guess I'm one of those sensitive skinned people who can't handle snail mucin. There is no smell to speak of, it is a hint sticky and viscous to apply. I considered using it with my lotion on my body, but I'm at a point in my life where if the product just isn't working for me, I'm not going to go out of my way to use it up. Better to toss or return than to hang onto it and hope things will get better. Right?

Product: COSRX Advanced Snail 96 Mucin Essence 100ml | Snail Mucin 96% Skin Repair Serum | Lightweight Facial Moisturiser with Snail Mucus | Korean Skin Care, Cruelty Free, Paraben Free, Alcohol Free
Review: This has changed my skin. Seriously. The snail mucin is anti-aging and soothing. I can tell a difference in my skin when I don’t use it. It decreases wrinkles, helps decrease hyperpigmentation, and increases cell turn over. Granted that isn’t why I purchased it. I thought it was just an Essense to use as apart of 7 skins. And technically it is. But it’s a game changer. And who needs Tret when you can get the same results with a natural product like this. That doesn’t have the side effects that Tret does.If I could slather my body in this daily I would lol. Be careful. Some people do have an allergic response to snail. So use it with caution. Personally I’m very sensitive so I’m not able to use it every day as it will cause my allergies to act up. However I’m trying to build up my tolerance. Seriously try it.

Product: COSRX Advanced Snail 96 Mucin Essence 100ml | Snail Mucin 96% Skin Repair Serum | Lightweight Facial Moisturiser with Snail Mucus | Korean Skin Care, Cruelty Free, Paraben Free, Alcohol Free
Review: If you are looking to add snail to your skincare routine this is your best bet. Don’t go for other pricier products with 15 plus ingredients as they are sure to dilute the snail secretions effectiveness and agrevate your skin with other random ingredients. When it comes to snail, more snail is better. This product is a winner with 96 percent snail, and only a handful of other ingredients in very low concentrations. My dehydrated, oily, combo, acne prone skin loves this stuff. It’s none aggravating, authentic and effective at delivering increased hydration, and smoothness to my skin. You will notice a difference! This is my secret weapon for keeping my pores clear, and smooth. I’ve heard people say pores can’t shrink, but there’s something special about this product or snail itself that has that poor shrinking effect, when i look in the mirror I see it.

Product: COSRX Advanced Snail 96 Mucin Essence 100ml | Snail Mucin 96% Skin Repair Serum | Lightweight Facial Moisturiser with Snail Mucus | Korean Skin Care, Cruelty Free, Paraben Free, Alcohol Free
Review: I bought this a few years ago and have tried different essences since then. This essence is one of my favorites, especially in the colder months when my skin gets drier. This essence has no scent (which my sensitive skin is thankful for).I like to use it in the night time and layer a cream moisturizer on top to seal the moisture. Although, there are times where I feel like the serum is moisturizing enough to hold on its own. I have experimented and tried to see how my skin would feel in the morning without using the essence and there is definitely a difference. My skin feels softer when I wake up, and that moisturized glow stays a bit longer.

Product: COSRX Advanced Snail 96 Mucin Essence 100ml | Snail Mucin 96% Skin Repair Serum | Lightweight Facial Moisturiser with Snail Mucus | Korean Skin Care, Cruelty Free, Paraben Free, Alcohol Free
Review: I have worked in the skincare industry for over twelve years and have tried everything under the sun. If you’re lucky, you usually see results within a few months. This product however is absolutely amazing. I’ve never seen these kinds of results so quickly. I will say that it is best used with a good cleanser, toner, exfoliator and moisturizer. I use it after I tone. It really helps with pores, fine lines and redness. I highly recommend it!!!

Product: COSRX Advanced Snail 96 Mucin Essence 100ml | Snail Mucin 96% Skin Repair Serum | Lightweight Facial Moisturiser with Snail Mucus | Korean Skin Care, Cruelty Free, Paraben Free, Alcohol Free

Product: Timex Kid's Analog 28 mm Elastic Fabric Strap Watch
Review:
I've been tricked to buy this piece of plastic by false specifications on Amazon, stating it has back-light but it doesn't.
Description says it has elastic fabric strap but its not elastic enough for my little girl.
Water resistance "30m" has nothing to do with diving at 30 metres (just another lie) and for kids something like this means it'll last to next rainy day.
I can't return this watch since my 4yr put her hands on it but I'd really love to. It is sad how well known, trustworthy brand turned cheapo. Had some sentiment about Timex.
It's simply disappointment.

Product: H&S 147pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Pin Removal Adjustment Tool Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Bar Pins Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review:
After taking 2 watches to have batteries replaced and being told it would cost upwards of £45 as one would have to be sent away as the screws holding the backplate were tiny, so could not been done in the shop - I decided to see if there was a cheaper option available.

After looking at a few different watch repair/servicing kits and watching some reviews, I decided on this one - at around £15 - I didn't really expect much, but how wrong I was.

The items are of a very decent quality, and so far I have used all of them whilst changing batteries and straps on both mine and family members watches...…..including both of the ones mentioned previously (the screws were small on the one to be honest - but there are screwdrivers included that dealt with that task with ease).

The watch clamp,openers and vice are a godsend, no more finicking about when trying to open a case -you can make sure it is held firmly in place while working on it and this greatly reduces the risk of damage and losing any pieces.....although the clamp is one of the smaller ones available apparently, so will not fit larger watches (I think its up to around 30mm?).

All of the items come in a handy case, with room to keep your watches inside while you wait for your batteries and straps to arrive - so I have found anyway.

I would recommend this item to anyone who is looking for a decent watch kit that has all of the bits and pieces needed to perform basic servicing, its worked for me so far.....and no need to ever be charged £20+ for something I can buy for £1 and do myself in 5 minutes in future.

Product: H&S 147pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Pin Removal Adjustment Tool Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Bar Pins Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review:
It wasn't long to cost me over £30 to replace the battery in my Seiko watch. Doing a bit of research showed I could buy the battery itself for £3.99 but the watch needed a special tool to remove the back. Doing further research came up with this toolkkt. So for approximately £20 I was able to do the job myself and can now save money changing batteries and adjusting straps on this and other watches in the future.

The toolkit itself is well put together. The tools appear to be reasonably well made. They're probably not the best you can buy but for the price they are excellent. There are lots of useful components so it seems pretty comprehensive. The inclusion on a large selection of strap springs is very useful.

My only criticisms are that the adjustable watch back removal tool that I needed for my Seiko is a little fiddly to use. It took me a number of attempts but I finally got there. You just nee to be a bit tenacious and try the different pins that are supplied. The other slight grumble is the wing nut for tightening the watch vice is very sharp and can cut into your fingers when turning. The vice itself is fine and is very useful. I will have to see if I can find a better made wing nut. The supplied one is one of those cheap hollow ones. I think if the manufacturer could replace this it would improve the overall quality of the toolkit.

But other than these very slight issues I would thoroughly recommend this kit. It has lots of good components and is generally well made and nicely presented.

Product: H&S 147pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Pin Removal Adjustment Tool Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Bar Pins Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review: Have used it to change a training watch battery and the associated heart monitor chest strap.  The tools in the kit allowed me to do this very easily using the adjustable watch back opener and the lever to lift the watch back, so it has almost for itself just allowing me to do this.  I can’t comment on the tools I did not use. As far as I can see the kit is reasonably robust and should last me quite a few years.  The holding straps in the ‘leather’ case don’t always fit some of the tools particularly well but for £14. 99 I think the whole kit is great and a really good buy.

Product: H&S 147pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Pin Removal Adjustment Tool Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Bar Pins Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review: Not worth buying, brought this for christmas due to me knowing we had alot of watches to be giving away as present and i had a few as a gift, but when i went to use it the main strap adjuster( the big clear one) was bent and also the three pin pusher( three silver small screwdriver looking things) two was bent and the 3rd keeps coming out so i tried to tighten it on the side and the screw has no head, but the other three has.

Product: H&S 147pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Pin Removal Adjustment Tool Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Bar Pins Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review:
Decent little toolkit for a good price. Nice storage case too. Covers most bases for the amateur watch enthusiast.

If you’re a strap fiend like I am and are constantly swapping straps on watches my only advice would be to invest in a better, higher quality spring bar tool as the forks on the tool in this kit wear down very quickly - but that’s the same with all cheaper spring bar tools so it’s not really a knock against this kit. No substitute for the Bergeon tool if you’re constantly swapping straps.

Other than that, good value for money and will save many unnecessary trips to local jewellers/fast fix to do small jobs that anyone can do at home.

Product: H&S 147pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Pin Removal Adjustment Tool Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Bar Pins Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review: Rubbish, a case of style over substance. The most used items being the 'presion' screw drivers, are so rough it's a joke. A three are bent, the blades are so badly groundhow they could claim to be an accurate size is beyond me. Also, one of them, the one I needed to use, the shaft spins in the hasle so you cannot get untighten or tighten anything. Don't get me started on the tweezers! Don't be fooled, or like me, try and cut corners, buy a quality set not this. I kept the case and threw the tools away.

Product: H&S 147pcs Watch Repair Tool Kit Strap Link Pin Removal Adjustment Tool Kit Back Case Remover Opener Removal Tool Spring Bar Pins Watchmaker Tools Kit
Review: I bought this as a present for my fiancé who has recently developed an interest in watch movements. About a week before his birthday he bought himself a different brand so I was thinking it was a waste but he tells me there are more tools in this; the other one didn't have pliers, for example. He was also impressed by the case quality; it looks really expensive and is sturdy. Product: Timex Easy Reader 35 mm Men's Black Leather Strap Date Window Quartz Watch
Review: I like the easy-read face on this watch, but it could be better:The date function is ridiculous to set - you have to keep winding the watch hands around multiple times until the date changes to the one you want. The date window is also too small for an easy-read watch.I have a Lorus easy-read ladies watch, which is almost identical to this one, which has two stops on the knob - the first stop allows you to change the date, and the second stop changes the time.  I did try the men's version of that watch first but it was too large, so I had to swap it for this one. (I was looking for a men's watch as I find the ladies watches too small for me).The Lorus watch is also a lot quieter than this one, as the second hand doesn't tick so loudly as this one does.  The only thing the Lorus watch doesn't do is light up.  So if you don't mind a larger watch than this one then I recommend you buy the Lorus watch instead.  The price is almost the same.After all the years that Timex have been making watches I would have thought they would have come up with a better way to change the date by now.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: Although these are fun to play with they are extremely dangerous. When I read the prioduct details it said numerous times that they were for 6 months and over. They are not!! The manufacturer's recommended age is 12 months and over and even then you must be extremely careful with them. Because of the shape of the egg tops, if a child gets one in his/her mouth they cannot remove it or spit it out and it's also difficult for a parent to remove from the child's mouth if it's facing inwards!! Very dangerous!!

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: Today my 6 month old managed to get the entire egg lid of one of these in his mouth, in a way which made it really difficult to remove. (Picture putting an egg or ball in your mouth past your lips snd gums, as far back as it can go) Fortunately I was with him and got it out before he panicked and either started crying or trying to close his mouth. NOT SAFE FOR SMALL CHILDREN even though these say they're from 6 months+. Anyone with a baby knows they put everything in their mouths, I stupudly trusted that a big name like Tomy would have rigorously tested their products for such an obvious safety risk. I learnt the scary and hard way that they don't.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: Little one instantly loved this (15 months ).  Very colourful and like the cheeping noise they make when you press them.  Wasn’t aware each one has a different shape on the base so only fits in its own shape space , this is great although she doesn’t quite understand this part yet but will eventually.  Love that the faces on the shells are colour coded to each chick yet fit all the others anyway as again when she’s old enough to match colours and shapes this you will mean she can play even more games with it. Really greatHad to take a few stars off for durability and sturdiness as arrived very beaten up and the hinge on the box is really white already upon arrival an not sure how long before the two parts of the lid have fully snapped off , will keep an eye whilst played with as I imagine this will be sharp.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: I bought this for my first granddaughter seven years ago and decided to buy another for my newest grandchild as this toy has so much play value. As a former early-years teacher, I can guarantee that this set is an important tool for development in most areas of learning. It works on so many levels, colour-matching, shape-matching, counting, cause and effect - it really promotes fine motor control and knowledge and understanding of the world around them. This toy will be useful for many years as it eventually can be used as part of kitchen or shop play. I would highly recommend this toy to all parents of little children - you really can't beat it when it comes to play value, durability and value for money. If toys are to be limited for any reason, this really is a "must-have".

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: Very disappointed this arrived without outer packaging, instead there was a 6inch address label stuck on the toy box itself, which cannot be removed without ripping the box, making this terrible for a gift option. I bought this for a friend's baby, but it looks awful for a gift as the label completely covers the image of what the toy is. They could have at least stuck the label on the back. The toy itself is great as my daughter has one. Just avoid if planning to gift it.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: I was excited to receive these as they had such great reviews. I was sadly a little disappointed. My LG loves things that make noise which is the main reason I bought them. But they don't really. They all make the one same noise which is plastic rubbing plastic and quite quiet. She doesn't even notice the noise.I do like the bright colours and the shape elements though so I will keep them for when she is older enough to appreciate those aspects.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review:
These are great. I don't know why, but kids love these eggy things.
Only thing to watch out for - and by no means bad points - is that it's a bit time consuming to put them away - especially if you have OCD.
You have to get each eggy in it's correct compartment - they fit in a shape, so only go in one orientation.
Then, you have to precariously place the eggy shell tops on. And if you're like me, you can't just put the yellow top on the orange egg oh no. Got to be the same colours. So that takes a little more time. And then if you accidentally nudge them, they're off again lol.
But seriously, I like these. Well made, no fiddly parts, the squeak is simple (mechanical) so nothing to go wrong. But top marks on the egg box - its solid and the latch is pretty good. Those eggies are going nowhere after you close it.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: Bought as a gift on the recommendations of toddler-owners that their little humans loved this. It's an odd little toy really but apparently a joy to mix and match the colours, shapes, faces, fitting them back in the box and make them squeak. It went across to some friends in Morocco for their little 1 year old boy who took to it immediately and has already had hours and hours of delight entertaining himself, rather to the bewilderment of all the adults. Really solid too so should last him a long while as long as he doesn't actually succeed in licking the faces off.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: For all the hype, I wasn’t that impressed. My one year old expressed some interest but wasn’t too into these (stacking cups win every time). They also seem a bit fiddly (a lot of work picking them up and putting back into the box), design is a little basic and I was expecting more from the sound “feature” - they all make the same faint squeak. I’m sure they will get used! But I expected something more thoughtful I guess.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: Video Player is loading.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: The sound? Yeah non existent. It’s an extremely faint squeak. In fact the the clacking of the plastic is louder making the squeak non existent. It says it’s for kids that are 6m+. I’d have said 18m+. As the screws and holes in the bottom of each egg is very distracting for younger kids. Oh and the egg tray ain’t easy to open for a three year old. Let alone 1-2yr olds.The positives are it seems durable. But the colours painted on the egg shell won’t last long.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review:
Baby likes the toy, and the clever thing is that as baby develops there are things to learn along the way, shapes and colours.

I don't like the grating squeek they make, and after only a little use they often get stuck in the down position. They are also not easy to press to squeek for little hands.

Not expensive, but I would rather pay a little more and get a product that is a bit better designed.

Would I still buy them knowing what I know? I think I would.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old
Review: Sturdy toy in brill colours. My baby still doesn't understand very well what to do but loves smashing the eggs... And even my 5 years old plays with it! He uses the eggs pretending he's cooking!Keep both busy for long time, so perfect!

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old

My daughter hasn't managed to match the shapes yet, but that's a further way to play in the future.

Product: TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs, Educational Shape Sorter, Toddler & Kids Toy, Suitable For 6 Months & 1, 2 & 3 Year Old

Review: It's a really good toy. I bought it on sale so it was worth my money. The toy itself is really sturdy. Each egg has different shapes on the bottom so it keeps the young children busy and educates them.  The only con that I can find with this product is that I wish that the little chick would make more or louder sound when they are pressed. Other then that it is a quite nice toy.

Review: Excellent little toy, the chicks squeak when pushed into the egg shell they're sat in and all the pieces are durable and fun colours with different little faces on the egg shell tops and chicks themselves. The hinge on the egg box probably won't last long but it snaps closed at the front so shouldn't be an issue. One thing to note for parents is you will get sick of trying to find them and put them back together after the first 20 times! It doesn't hold attention for long but the older one likes you to guess which colour the chick is in the egg.

Product: RSVOM Mens Digital Watch - 50M Waterproof Men Sports Watches, Black Big Face LED Military Wrist Watch with Alarm/Countdown Timer/Dual Time/Stopwatch/12/24H Format for Man
Review: Bought this to time myself swimming. The instructions which came with the watch were poor and I have not been able to set the date or time or alarm etc. So pretty hopeless from that point of view. Instructions had all the right words but not necessarily in the right order. However I did manage to get it into stopwatch mode which is what I wanted. Although it was a bit vague, I thought the advert claimed it would be OK for swimming however information on the box said specifically not for swimming. However given it was so cheap decided to give it a go and it has survived the first swim.

Product: RSVOM Mens Digital Watch - 50M Waterproof Men Sports Watches, Black Big Face LED Military Wrist Watch with Alarm/Countdown Timer/Dual Time/Stopwatch/12/24H Format for Man
Review: Can't vouch for the battery as have only had it for 4 weeks. Bought as a daily wear for work. Large enough, black and smart enough looking for most occasions.I didn't want a watch that lit up the time like an advert. I wanted something more subtle. Some might say it's not easy to read in dark conditions, which it's not, but that's what the light is for. Very comfortable strap and light weight.

Product: RSVOM Mens Digital Watch - 50M Waterproof Men Sports Watches, Black Big Face LED Military Wrist Watch with Alarm/Countdown Timer/Dual Time/Stopwatch/12/24H Format for Man
Review: On initial looks this watch looks like a Sunnto or similar style, yes it is only £10 but it is fairly difficult to read unless you position just right. The days look like hieroglyphics, Mon looks like INON, the rest are not much better. Even though I have only had for a few days, I am not convinced this is keeping time well, arguably the most important reason for a watch, it seems to run a bit quick. Only plus, the wide strap is more comfortable than I thought it would be.

Product: RSVOM Mens Digital Watch - 50M Waterproof Men Sports Watches, Black Big Face LED Military Wrist Watch with Alarm/Countdown Timer/Dual Time/Stopwatch/12/24H Format for Man
Review: Looks OK, it's good value but the display is poor, it illuminates off you press a button but only for a short duration. The rest of the time the screen is difficult to read. Set up is a bit painful but doable but am illegible display is kind of a deal breaker...

Product: RSVOM Mens Digital Watch - 50M Waterproof Men Sports Watches, Black Big Face LED Military Wrist Watch with Alarm/Countdown Timer/Dual Time/Stopwatch/12/24H Format for Man

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review: I am very used to wearing an analogue watch. My previous one broke down so I needed something quick, that would not leave a dent in my wallet. This watch is great, very light weight but seems well built and great quality for a very low price at the same time. It is very clear to read, and comfortable to wear. Cannot say how water resistant it is but I bathe my kids wearing it and it seems perfectly fine (although I'm wet all over :-D ). Have been using it a couple of weeks now and have absolutely no complaints.Comes in a nice plastic packaging with Casio tag.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review:
Fully deserving of 5 stars. This beats all of the poseur minimalist watches by actually being a simple, clean, robust watch. Beautiful design, reliable engineering and like a feather on the wrist, from a quartz watchmaker with heritage. All for less than £8! Not pretentious, ostentatious or crass, it just works. I can wear this over my £4K Speedmaster without worrying about it, and still look cool.

In many ways better than watches 500-600 times it’s price. Future classic.

Great job Casio, thumbs up.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review: Its never a watch for a man as advertised its much too small. It would fit a young lad. I am not big boned by any stretch of the imagination but this looks tiny on me. I haven't tried to scratch it or put it in water so ive not given any stars there. Its cheap and not as discribed by the seller but you only get what you pay for.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review: Second of these I have had. It was cheaper to buy a new one online than to get the battery changed at a jewellers. Reliable and stands up to housework and gardening and sweaty sports. Probably not a good idea to submerge in water but resists heavy splashing and doesn't get condensation. Easy to read numeric face (analogue). Easy to set time with knob on side. Strap is resin but can be replaced with any suitably-sized strap.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review:
Inexpensive, sylish but non pretentious, easy to read, quartz precision, water resist.

It has a very lean and slim case, so it makes it appear a bit small, but the dial is clear, readable, and well sized.

It tucks in inside shirts and gloves very easy due to its size.

It is a watch of reliable quality that sits outside of the "envy market".

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review:
This is the ultimate watch money can buy. It's simplistic in its design, yet not trying overtly hard to be minimalistic like many fashion watches do.

The resin strap is very soft and in comparison to my DW9052 it wears better but is less robust. It looks very good as the watch strap blends in well with the watch.

The watch wears well and is on the smaller side. It's very understated and has little presence on the wrist, however I do not view that as a downside. In fact, due to its slim profile and simple appearance it works well with casual attire and for more formal occasions.

However, due to the plastic covering the dial it's very easy to scratch. For example if you somehow nudge your keys against this watch it will probably show a scuff mark. But it is possible to polish it with toothpaste (not grainy paste, but smooth) to elimante smaller marks. Also, as you can tell from the picture, the plastic isn't domed. Still isn't a deal breaker at this price range.

In short, if you're looking for an easy to read, cheap, lightweight watch that works well during most occasions where you want to be able to tell the time but not be too "flamboyant", this is a perfect watch.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review: It is a basic watch, which is what I wanted as a temporary replacement. The screen, however cracked within a day or so of purchase. I haven't returned it, as I need it until the replacement parts for the strap of my usual watch arrive.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review: Casio doesn’t need my review but I’m doing one anyways because I’m truly amazed at the quality of this watch. I bought it 2 years ago for £5 and it is still going strong. The classic look and durability are something that I have not seen in a product in a while. It is the best. I love this watch, I dress it up or down. I have small hands but the watch doesn’t look awkward at all.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review: Although I've given this watch a 3-star rating, the watch itself is probably good value. However, the strap was too short for my wrist and probably won't fit any wrist over 7 inches in circumference.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24
Review: This is a great little watch and at the price cannot be beat. The watch face is clear and crisp without any unnecessary clutter. The strap too is surprisingly thin and my only fear is its longevity; though I must say, at this price, if the strap fails I'd buy the same watch again! I am very pleased with my purchase.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24

Failures are limited to either the strap or the resin strap retainer, which eventually break, but you'll get a good few years out of each one.

Product: Casio Collection Unisex Watch MQ-24

What's not to like?Recently I forgot I'd left it in the pocket of my shorts. As a result it went through a wash cycle in our washing machine. Two hours later it emerged unscathed: still working, and still showing the correct time. Amazing!

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: The watch itself looks nice, but that's where the positives end. In the space of 30 mins, the watch restarted a couple of times, froze while scrolling through apps, buttons became unresponsive and then all activated at once and to top it off google pay was deactivated and when i tried to activate it, it said my region was not supported (I knowthe UK is supported and use google pay on my phone for nearly all purchases). The whole user experience was unsatisfactory. I don't know if the fault lies with the hardware or software, but i suspect a bit of both.The search for an android wear smart watch that functions adequately and looks the part goes on. I switched from iOS a couple of years back and had an apple watch ... it's the only part of the apple ecosystem that I miss.Avoid this piece of junk at all costs.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Watch seems to be OK, lightweight with a clear screen. Setup with the app was fairly simple but after that there are no instructions on how to operate the watch. Sadly, we're not all tech experts and a manual of some description is essential.  Tried the Fossil website but no luck there. Trawled the web (we really shouldn't have to do this)  including YouTube but no real information on how to use the different functions. If manufacturers insist on saving a few pence by not including a manual, I will always mark the rating down to one star, however good the product is.  It may be the best product in the world but, without proper instructions, it's just another expensive paperweight!

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
I did allot of research including reading written reviews and watching videos, each time this wear OS watch came out on top even though the same few issues came up in every review. I have been wearing it for over a week now and It's a Great watch.

I was a bit concerned from reviews about the battery life but had listened to all the recommendations so knew what to expect.

The first day I used it, I played around with it allot and installed apps and updated the watch, The battery life was terrible. I knew this would happen as all reviews said the first few days all the updates would kill the battery.

After the first day and all updates were completed the battery seemed to be fine and I played around with the battery settings and got to know what settings did what to the battery. On the daily setting I have been having around 20% battery life left, that's from 6am-10pm but this is with light use and the watch being used mainly as a normal watch most of the day. Extended I found I can have as much as 40% left. Custom option you can really adjust the settings to what ever you like so if you wanted I guess you could get 2-3 days from the watch but then most of the smart options are turned off.

Once the battery gets below 10% it asks you to turn on time only mode which turns the watch in to exactly that a watch for telling the time. This is great if your out and cannot charge but want to make sure you can still tell the time easy.

Speaker and mic works great for calls and Google assistant works well and is clear.

I have quite small wrists so was concerned about the size but it doesn't look too big and the slim body helps.

The amount of options to make the watch your own is great including watch faces, battery settings and easy replaceable traps.

I would highly recommend this watch.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: It looks nice and the spec appears good but most things you would want to use simply don't work very well and bugs don't get fixed by Fossil/Google for months. Battery life as with most Wear OS watches is terrible.GPS operation is absolutely useless, and has been so for the last 4 months.. the forums are full of reports.  So if you're thinking of it for any fitness tracking or other sports, my advice is look elsewhere.

Review:
Decided to finally upgrade my old Fitbit and I must say this watch is just incredible!! I can do so much stuff on it I can make phone calls reply to text messages and Google to turn my lights on/ off!! The only downside is the battery only lasts about 1.5 days it even has a torch mode which is brilliant as now I don't wake the Mrs up when I need the toilet in the middle of the night

Pros :
Looks gorgeous best looking smart watch on the market in my opinion
Lots of features, like weather, Google assistant, reply to text make phone calls etc
Lots of watch faces to choose from
Different battery modes to increase the battery life

Cons:
Wear OS( operating system) has a very poor battery life and causes all wear OS watches to drain the battery faster than alternative watch brands like apple OS and Fitbit

Google assistant seems to struggle when you talk to it when you're replying to text messages for example I said " ok cool let me know how it goes" Google said/ heard " ja kabba klob kla " which makes no sense whatsoever
