Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
To get straight to the point, the battery life on this was well below what I was expecting for a £200+ watch. After the first connection and a fully charged battery, the life of the watch was about 10 hours.. I put this down to an update and gave it another chance.
After I had tuned the watch battery profile to what I would expect (not excessive use) I got just over a day out of the watch. Disappointed with this.

When setting up I struggled to sync the phone and watch. Took about 3 attempts of resetting the watch and then trying again.
WearOs is a great addition to Android users and acts as a bolt on to you phone. Everything is available. I liked the OS this was slick. I had a few lags in swiping when I first set this up but this reduced over time.

Music control was great, could even control music volume. Showed me an image from Deezer when playing.
Reading and reply to messages was all there.
Notification we're good and easy to navigate through.

For me I couldn't justify paying so much for a watch where the battery life doesn't stack up, and I imagine in time this would degrade. Returned device.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
Bought this watch in March 2020 to replace a Samsung galaxy watch.

Within the first month the silicon strap broke so I had to buy a new strap.

Within three months I have had to do a factory reset due to a charging problem.

The battery barely lasts day.

There is no built in sleep monitor, you have to download an app and then manually start the app when going to sleep. The app uses about 20% of battery in 7 hours of sleeping.

When a text had been read you can't read it again on the watch as there is no app for text messages (that I have found).

Good points are the ready to use Google pay, and that you can assign two apps to the function buttons to access quickly. Google fit is pretty good and links to Strava. The watch had some good watch face options that are customisable so you can get lots of info on one screen.

Overall it's very disappointing.

Update Aug 2020 - the heart rate sensor has stopped working. Watch is being returned and a full refund obtained

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: The watch is pretty good. Quality materials and very responsive. Wear OS still isn't the best. The only problem for the watch is the OS. Wear OS does not have a lot of features and has too much that you don't need. The Wear OS app is kinda useless, because you can't do nearly anything. No sleep tracking except for 3rd party apps. The battery life kinda sucks. You have to charge it every day even with nearly no usage. The strap was a little bit big for my hand but that's fine. The watch is very comfortable. Heart rate tracking is very accurate. GPS takes a long time to detect the first time(2-5 minutes ). It counts your steps which is useful. It has NFC and you can use it with Bluetooth earbuds. Sometimes fails to automatically connect to WiFi. Stable Bluetooth connection. A lot of nice watch faces. The notifications work perfectly and you can't miss it. Calls are kinda quiet sometimes but they are ok for a watch. As whole it is a very good watch, but Fossil should think about developing their own OS or Google to make Wear OS better. I am recommending the watch for everyone.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: My husband loves his new watch.He said he has reduced the heart rate checking to hourly as he is not using it for sport. He has also changed the watch face to Defender to reduce the amount the watch keeps checking things although I suspect it is because he is a Land Rover Nut.He has put on Alexa and a few other apps more appropriate to him and all work well as does the sleep checking, phone calls, diary etc. He said it will last all day and is charged in a few minutes while showers etc. He uses a stand charger as he does not like the included one.He recommends it if you are the sort of person that sets it up and does not keep playing with it or you will flatten the battery quickly.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
The watch is excellent, it feels extremely premium and performance has been very good for me.

Battery life was initially disappointing but after a week or so it settled down and would last just under 2 days with my usage. I use the "daily" profile mostly, I have found that having tilt-to-wake on has a significant impact on battery life, so I left it off. I also don't use it for workout tracking or use the location services very much so that would also impact battery life.

Unfortunately while the build feels very solid and premium they still haven't ironed out the issues with the charging ring from the Gen 4. After only owning my watch for about 2 months the ring started lifitng from the body and the watch wouldn't charge. The refund process was seamless and I plan on purchasing another one soon.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: This is a nice looking watch but unfortunately wear OS has some major issues which make the watch useless for my needs. The biggest issue is that the GPS is not currently working unless the watch is tethered to the phone, meaning you need to bring your phone with you on a run/ride - defeating the purpose of a GPS watch. As of the 23rd of July Google are aware of th issue but have been unable to supply a fix. The second big issue is that the outlook app currently won't load on this specific model. Again Google are aware of the issue but no fix has been mentioned yet. If you need standalone GPS or outlook, check the wear OS forums to make sure these issues are fixed before you buy. Sadly I will be returning my watch as I can't be sure that Google will fix these issues or that new ones won't arise in future updates.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
I have not tried many smartwatches, but this one is the best. It is elegant, durable, and tremendously useful. It looks fantastic; moreover, you can change face watches whenever you want. All the interactions are fast and smooth, I love how easily it connected to my phone (Huawei P9), and it syncs everything instantly. Now that I can see all my notification on my wrist, it is a lot easier for me to stay on track but not waste time using my phone. I have also got a black silicone strap, which is fantastic for sports; I use the brown leather one for more classy occasions. I admit, the battery is not the best, but with most of the functions on the battery easily last for a full day. It would be nice if it could go for more than 2 days with one charge but neither can my phone so I do not mind it at all. I wear the watch, almost 24/7 because I use it for smart alarm/ sleep tracking overnight. The only thing I would like more about this watch would be if the brown leather strap was only made from genuine leather and not rubberized bottom, but even with that, it is still comfortable. Considering that I use this watch nonstop, I think the value is terrific. (Currently using Ultimate Watch for watch face)

Comfort 8/10
Battery 7/10
Quality 10/10
Looks 10/10
Value 10/10

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: The design of the Fossil Gen 5 watch is great. The usability of Wear OS is great too and fast improving. The battery life of this watch though is awful - bad enough to make the watch not worth owning. I sent mine back due to a combination of having to charge twice per day, even when using extended mode. In addition to this, the software is glitchy and shut the watch down several times (even with sufficient battery) and refused to turn on except for performing a hard reboot each time.Lots of potential but until the battery can last more than 48 hours at the VERY LEAST while using many of its cooler functions, this watch is simply too high maintenance.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I originally dipped my toe into Android Wear with a 1st gen moto360, now long since gathering dust in a drawer somewhere. I gave up on it for years. Thought I'd give it another whirl with this and I've not been disappointed. Yes, the battery life could be better, but as with most smartphones, it lasts easily until I go to bed and that's all I want. In fact it lasts over 24 hours, but I charge it every night. I'm using daily battery mode, turned off all the unnecessary notifications from my phone. Setting it up was a pain, wear os crashed the setup procedure, needing a reset of the watch, but once past that it was a breeze. First day worried me though, the battery lasted about 4 hours! But there were several updates and I was messing with it. It's been much better since.In short, it's a like a mini smartphone so don't expect the battery to last like a Fitbit or Garmin wearable. It works brilliantly and looks great.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
Great piece of kit. Best android smart watch! Responsive, talks back, can answer calls, heart rate tracker and not to mention swim proof.
Shame about wear os not offering a preset option for tracking swimming though, to get around this I usually select other on the watch before swimming, then after my session I change it on my phone Google fit app to swimming. Really hoping wear os sort things out so that this amazing watch can be used to its full potential.

Battery life isn't too bad, I got 3 workdays out with custom setting where Bluetooth disconnected after certain time and started back up at a certain time.

Got this for my husband after I fell in love with mine!

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Overall I'm very satisfied, mainly with the physical aspect of it. I like the metal strap (although it was slightly annoying having to go and have it resized the day I got it, but there is nothing you can do to avoid this I guess). It works pretty smoothly and does what I need it to do, only two problems I've encountred so far is that for some reason about 60% of the time my location service is not working and can therefore not use it to check the weather or Google Maps. Second thing is, it cannot sign into public networks on its own, I live in a place where my wifi is a public network and you have to sign in, so it relies solely on the slower bluetooth network for internet conneciton, but this was no major problem except from the initial update which too an eternity.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
I wanted to buy a Wear OS watch because I want to use Google Pay and Google Fit. I also want to have a built-in GPS watch. So how it's this watch after 2 days? Let's see:
Pros:
- Beautiful watch and it feels Premium
- Clock and Date
- NFC and Google Pay
- Google Fit and other Google services
- Customizable faces
Cons:
- GPS - even if it has GPS, some apps like STRAVA need the phone GPS as well, otherwise, it won't work. So if you want to run only with your watch, it's impossible to track your activity
- SYNC with the phone. OMG, the SYNC is soooo slow. Sometimes you need to restart the watch to synchronize all your data.
- Firmware update. If you do the update, the watch won't work properly. And if the battery is not full you cannot update the firmware. So, if low battery and firmware update started, forget about the watch, go outside for a walk.
- STRAP - the Leather strap is something like that: 80% plastic, 20% leather
and finally
-BATTERY LIFE - the big elephant in the room. NO! If you buy this watch for battery life, don't use it and the battery will last few days. Otherwise, if you want to track your activity in a few hours it's DEAD.

Overall, this watch is a good experiment for 2019, but it's not the best one for 2020.

I will return it and wait for a better one.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Loved the actual wacth, most of the time but like other reviewers had lots of problems - the wifi dropping out, 'OK Google' not working, not counting steps sometimes, but mostly it was the battery life - mine could not make it through a normal 9-5 working day as a smart watch - by 3pm it was saying to turn off all the smart features and become a dumb watch to conserve battery.At first, I thought it was because I was 'playing with the features, but then when I didn't wear it one day untill later on it had already turned off most the features that make it smart.Absolutely loved the physical watch itself, screen , icons etc, but not paying over £200 for smart watch that just isn't smart most of the time - Returned.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I've come from the samsung s3 which I've had for a few years. The Fossil watch has a better display and battery life. Love the google assistant which in my option is better than Bixby and also I'm now able to use google pay via the watch as samsung pay only works with few banks some im very happy with the replacement.The only draw back is lack of apps but im not a big user of watch apps so not a real problem and love the fact I can update phone apps via the phone.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I held off getting a smartwatch - mostly because I don't like the look of the Apple watch and while I liked the better range of functions etc on the samsung one, it just looked too big/clunky and ugly.The watch I generally wear until now is a traditional looking Rotary with a leather strap. Nothing blingy about it, which was one of the things that put me off smartwatches - they seemed to be designed to shout "Look at Me!" rather than focus so much on quiet stylishness.I run Android on my phone (it's a Motorola, so doesn't have samsung's horrible bloatware) so was ideally looking for a watch that played nicely with android and I happened to discover that Fossil, a brand that I knew and liked, made smartwatches running on Google's own watch OS.I've been wearing it now for a good few weeks and am delighted with it. It looks classically stylish with its brown leather strap and functionally is superb. I've had no issues with it, other than the expected ones while getting used to where things are on the watch, and am really happy with it. Quite a few friends have asked me about it and are also now thinking of getting one or another of the Fossil Gen 5 range. I love it!

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Lasted 2 days and I sent ti back. Looks beautiful. On paper it's a perfect smart gadget. In reality it's completely impractical. Lags when loading apps, crashes frequently and your lucky if you get 7 hours from the battery. Completely impractical. Traded it in for the much reduced functionality of a huawei Gt2 which has a battery that I can get 10 days from. Much sleeker and has all the functionality I need with a usable battery life.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: WearOS is still a little buggy but not enough to make you dislike using it.Battery life is decent for an Android smartwatch. Unless you are doing something very weird you will easily get at least a day out of it even if everything is on. It's also light and not too big for smaller wrists.I'm guessing the extra memory and better chipset when compared to the older generations makes this overall a much better watch.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Not impressed. Wish I had gone for something different. Speaker is very poor and decides not to work most of the time. Functions work sometimes. Today it was the turn of the phone function not to work. No phone calls show while my phone is ringing! Google assistant is good but because the speaker decides not to work most of the time it's not worth having. Spend less on another watch with a little less functionality because 60% of the time some function on this watch does't work.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Spend absolutely ages trying to get this paired with my Google Pixel 3 phone.  It ws spawning lots of duplicate setup processes on my phone, all of them failing.It's a truly horrendous out of the box experience, and Fossil/Google should be ashamed of it.Will follow up a review, if/when I ever get it working..

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
I had been looking to upgrade my Huawei Watch 2 as the laggy OS was starting to get frustrating, and having looked at a few options I settled on the Fossil Gen 5.

First impressions were really good, a nice sized screen but still slim, and a really snappy OS.

A few weeks in and I remain really pleased, would recommend. The best WearOS watch I have owned by far.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
Great stylish watch. Easy to use and setup.
Battery life is about a day. I like to keep the display on as it looks smart with a classic dial which gives me just under a day wear on the battery.

Great value for money for what you get.
Google app works well with the watch.

The Fossil app works terrible with it.

Easy to install apps to the device and use for viewing messages. Writing messages that are not predicted is difficult as you'd expect.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: As all the reviews here and elsewhere state this is a good/very good Wear OS watch, absolutely no argument there. Looks wise the strap is indeed leather and a nice dark brown but if I'd realised it  was silicone backed then I'd have saved myself a tenner and gone for the silicone only varient. 'Genuine Leather' is more accurately described as 'Genuine Leather Bonded to Silicone'...Otherwise very pleased, functions very (very) well and a breeze to set up, battery life seems to be as quoted (allowing for initial set-up excesses) and does indeed recharge quickly - 8% to 100% in an hour +-, very pleased :) The leather does actually look good, just if you prefer it to silicone against your skin then...Oh, and if you like a more traditional watch face then Marine Commander from the Play Store is well worth the £1.79 to support, try it...

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I have the watch a couple of weeks and overall I am happy with it from tech, visual and ease of use point of view. Im a Type 1 Diabetic that uses Dexcom and the fact I can pull my instant data up on the watch is fantastic feature. Im still exploring what else can be brought up on it but excited by the potential - especially for golf.Only downside is the stiffness of the strap - I have the brown leather silicon strap. I dont think it will last through the exercise use and general everyday wear. I will look around for different strap if it doesn't last. Particular dont like the two straps to slip the main strap into.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
I love this watch. I don't have an issue with battery life. I charge every night. I don't overdo the use of the watch during the day. The always-on display is always activated. A great watch. Would recommend.

It feels and looks great. I have owned Apple, and Samsung watches and loved them too. But for me now using a Samsung phone, I have more choice of watch apps using an Android watch rather than with the great range of Samsung watches.

Very competitively priced.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I read reviews before purchase and most said it is one of the best smartwatches out at the moment.  Totally agree with those reviews.  Only had it a couple of weeks and there is so much it can do, I have only tried a few things so far but am well satisfied with the watch and look forward to using it and use more apps etc each day.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: This is an amazing looking watch with an amazing operating system. Looks classy with thousands of watch faces. Read, (you can even see the pictures which is attached) and Reply to your messages regardless of their origin (fb messenger, text, WhatsApp etc..) it has a microphone and a speaker. When you ask something to Google assistant it can talk back to you or you can listen to music or take a phone call on your watch. Brilliant heart rate and fitness tracking with a workout personal assistant. Has a GPS tracking, Wi-Fi and NFC for contacless payments which works perfect. It can pair with wireless headphones for your music. Battery easily lasts a whole day with everything turned on. Overall a really good looking classy watch, fitness tracker and a personal assistant. Definitely recommend it.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: What on paper is a great set of specs for a modern day smart watch sadly just doesn't work in the real world. I took th plunge on this item as I am embedded into the Google eco system and wanted something that I could use as a daily watch as well as some physical activity. The long and short is that although very powerful and capable, the system was still slow and unresponsive when scanning through the menus. I found its software to be overly complicated and lacked a logical thinking path needed to add value to using this on a daily basis. After three days I had enough and exchanged the item for a Fitbit versa 2. Simple and effective. Don't make the same mistake I did.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
Didn’t think I’d get so much functionality pairing with iPhone but pleasantly surprised with the results. No iMessage but it works for my 365 email and calendar.
Charges in 30 mins
Looks great
Cons
Needs a sleep tracker
Had to factory reset after adding call answering from iPhone. It wouldn’t reconnect to wear os app until this rather drastic step...

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Gen 5, metal strap. Use it mainly for alerts, from Freestyle Libre and Miao Miao and messages. Still have to use phone for most things, battery life about 75% after a day at work but drops rapidly if you start to use it for more than alerts. Found most apps are paid for if you want more than basics.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Overall my short time with the watch was nice when it worked, most of the time it would freeze or lock up and after 2 days it did this when I weren't using it. It would vibrate and restart while I was going about my day. Then on the 3rd day the strap broke so I had enough and sent it back. For reference I read online that certain watch faces can cause crashes, I had the stock face.And also Wear os is a waste of time, half the apps I downloaded are no longer supported for what ever reason such as the uber app or the nationwide banking app.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I have used WearOS based watches for a while now and they have always felt like they do the minimum to make them worth the purchase. This one however due to newer CPU and 1GB of RAM is snappy. its FAST and has NO lag at all. I REALLY like it!

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I'm really disappointed with this product.... I expect for 200 pound and amazing watch, no sleep tracking , really bad battery, lag in Google assistant, problems with Bluetooth connection...... I'm really disappointed after 2 weeks of use

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Brilliant watch. Battery was always a worry as I've read bad reviews about it. The reviews on the watch itself were good and I totally agree with them all. The watch is easily set up with your mobile. This is the first smart watch I've had so unable to compare to others but overall I'm really pleased with the watch. The only downside was the watch going missing on delivery on the first attempt. Amazon were great though and sent a new watch out. Its unfair to judge a company on mistakes happening but I was happy with how they dealt with the matter. very pleased

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I really love it. My friends and family all really like it. Some of them are thinking of replacing their apple watches. It feels well made, and solid. A proper watch unlike many smart watches. Wear os definitely needs some improvements (please bring back nest support), and more supported apps would be lovelyGreat watch overall. Love the third party watch faces.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: i purchased this item with high expectations, but i was sadly disappointed. the battery life sucked as it only lasted me 4 hours of the day, the watch does look really nice but did not perform as-well as expected, the watch would disconnect from my phone and from the wifi so often that there would be no point in me connecting to them in the first place. lastly the "ok google" feature rarely worked for me. i can say that this is a beautiful looking watch but the functionality was just not there for me.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Great smart watch which will do ALMOST anything you desire! Google has a long way to go if they wish to be the leader in this wearable market but it's a great step towards a great product. Apart from the battery being a bit pants, the watch delivers on all areas.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I thought battery life was v poor. It looks nice, more for a smart look, rather than a functional 'yes I am wearing a smart watch'. I have a dress watch already.However it is very good quality and if you want something discreet this is for you. I now have a Tic Watch Pro 2020 which is perfect.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
Beautiful, nice and clear screen. Relatively comfortable.

And wear os connects pretty well to all the apps I need. Fitness / sleep tracking and whatnot.

However, I spent days trying to optimize battery. And no matter what I got if I had sleep tracking and gym workout in one day. It lasted from 10pm before sleep, until about 6pm the next day.

This may be fine for some people, but the idea of having to charge a watch every single day was a bit much for me.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Great looks.Running smooth.Decent battery life (1 full day easy, charge overnight) with Custom Battery Setting: WiFi Off (Bluetooth connection), Tilt To Wake Off (don't need it with always-on screen), OK Google Off (hold the crown button to activate). Also, set Heart Rate measurements to be taken only during workouts (manual measurements still possible)The best Wear OS watch right now.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Works very well and I've dropped it already on a hard floor and kept working! Battery lasted all day, 75% used but didn't use all the watch features! The only problem is the strap, it's way too big so needs adjusting at a jeweller's

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Very nice to look at but Google's watch is isn't the best for a watch, I found that the crown would constantly activate the watch with a slight bend of the wrist making it come on all the time, especially swimming.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Loved to look of the product.Charged it, set it up ready to use.Wore it for 2 hours, died.. wouldn’t charge just dead.Not even going to get a replacement so disappointed am I.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Really good watchFairly easy to setup.Battery life is ok but needs charging daily if you use a lot of functions like heart monitor.Works with WhatsApp on from iPhone.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
The upgraded 1GB RAM really helps. It's fast.

Continues heartrate measure using Google Fit works nicely.

Battery life is good. Initially a bit more usage for few days during updates.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: It was a little bit laggy for the first like 5 hours but I believe it was because it had a few updates to do. Ever since it has been great! It is a lot more conspicuous than going on your phone in work. I bought one for myself and my partner and we both enjoy it a lot!The best messenger app is telegram, already got 6 of my friends to make the switch over, you can reply to WhatsApp and Facebook messages, but you can't start them, whereas if you have telegram you can.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Took a while before I got used to the functions but eventually got it as I wanted it. Battery life isn't as good as I expected and it will probably need charging every night if used heavily. I like the Google pay option and being able to use Strava to record my activities. Google assistant is a useful tool. Overall I'm quite satisfied with my purchase.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Wanted a smart watch with a circular body and good features. Good battery life, depending on the features active at the time. Plenty of apps available, great fitness capabilities and versatile all round.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Do not buy, the watch has had software issues for over a year where the internal GPS refuses to connect

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Very good all round watch, some minor connectivity issues from time to time but nothing that should sway you away from buying. Most people purchase a watch for the way it looks and this watch is by far the best looking / fastest watch on the market. I grabbed this in the Jan sales for 200, not too sure if I'd pay 3 for it however.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I love every thing with this watch, verry good quality and verry easy to use, but the battery life is not as good. If you are allways opening an app, the battery life goes down to 5-6 hours.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Main christmas present from my wife. Lasted 2days and bricked. When it worked was good barring battery was poor and wouldn't last 12hr working day. Won't get a replacement as brand faith is lost.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: One of the best wear OS watches on the market, got mine on offer for £209 on black Friday, I bit heaver than some but easy to change the strap for a lighter leather one

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: A good watch, very handy and the battery modes are really helpful.... I had to give 3 stars because the speakers broke after the first time it went underwater... It supposed to be waterproof!

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: it does what it says on the box and is very easy to use, but you need to have your phone with you at all times, therefor it makes very little sense to have the watch.also making phone calls via the watch is bad quality.is great for tracking your workout though

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: This product is amazing the screen is very nice and easy to see the colors are great it is easy to use and the sound is brilliant

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Its okay. Not as expected.. has a had battery life for the money that you are paying. Many straps not available on the company website are unavailable.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: This is my first smart watch, and was looking for something a little more stylish than a Samsung Galaxy. It looks really nice on your wrist and isn't very bulky at all. With the always-on screen turned off the battery life for me is very fine, charging once every other day. It takes a while to get used to the menu's and interface but thats to be expected with any new technology.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Great watch with sometimes meh connection and battery yet compared to others is great everything is great except for connection

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Works seemlessly with my android phone, Google for is great but doesn't do sleep tracking easily. Being able to change features to save battery life is great too. Onboard speaker helpful for answering calls through the watch.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Was anxious about the battery life but after the first day of updates it's pretty great , even with tilt-to-wake enabled. You can squeeze 2 days out of it but I bought the dock and charge it every night, no bother. It's pretty great, had the Huwaei watch 2 but this feel like a substantial upgrade. Looks good too.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: It was not good experience  the batter life is soo bad and my watch after month it’s stopped working completely it’s dead so I returned that watch ..

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Best looking watch. Does what it promises. Though slight glitches here and there, it's a decent watch. Battery can drain in 3-4 hours if all options are turned on. Surprisingly loud and calls can be made easily. Using Maps on the watch was an issue as the location did not turn on. Overall a 3/5 rating

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Terrible watch for the money , had 2 in the space of 2 weeks! Both went back ! First one speaker went in the first 2 days, and battery life wasn't very good. So sent it back. Second one, full battery lasted 4 hours so finally got money back . Would definitely swerve this watch

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: I loved it. Very easy to use and look great.But: battery is not that great, wifi is always turning off even you change the setting and after one year of using it my battery died completely.Anybody knows where to fix it?

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: It’s a great shame the battery life had reduced from 2.5 days to 1 day. It is not convenient to put it on charge regularly. The quality of the watch is super and comfortable to wear. I have decided to get a normal fossil watch.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Greate watch have all what I need but battery life is 0.5 day I need something what survive longer. Or I don't need smart watch what I can't use all of the option to save battery like time only. If I want time only I will use normal watch.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review:
Two days into using the watch, and it stopped working. It no longer turns on, can’t be charged, and is basically a dead piece of metal and glass. The Amazon returns service has been excellent, and a replacement is being shipped to me, so I will update the review once that one has been working for a couple of weeks or so.

First impressions:

The strap was impossible to adjust myself, even using the correct tool. The guy at Timpsons could do it, but a) that cost me £10 including fuel and parking to get there and get it done, and b) he said it was one of the hardest adjustments he has had to do. It may have just been my strap, but near it in mind.

The user interface is very easy to use and quite comprehensive. You can adjust pretty much everything. I like the fact that this looks like a proper watch, and being able to pretty much endlessly tinker with the dial to get it looking how you want it is great.

The fitness app it comes with is fine for most people. The Strava app (free) is a worthwhile addition to map walks / runs.

The Spotify app should be renamed “Spotify Lite”. It gives a very limited range of options in terms of selecting music, mostly limited to recent playlists you have played.

The battery is just about ok. I don’t use the apps that much on it, and it is down at close to 10% by the end of the day. If you are a heavy music or fitness user, or operate calls / messages from the watch screen, I can’t see it lasting a full day.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: Wear OS system and aluminium body, that's exactly what I was looking for.In addition, it works surprisingly quickly and smoothly.

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications

Product: Fossil Men's GEN 5 + 5E Touchscreen Smartwatch with Speaker, Heart Rate, NFC, and Smartphone Notifications
Review: IV had this watch a good few months now and I just wanted to change my review ok so I think the watch works very well the features are very good all work fine here's the but though the battery life is absolutely terrible it's rubbish because I do a lot of walking and the battery will run out before I finish my walk so bit pointless really If I want to walk nine or ten miles the watch will run out of battery so I dont get the full reading apart from that I am happy with everything else on the watch I think it looks nice and IV got the silicone strap witch is comfortable and good when it gets warm also actually nearly forgot to mention I'm not able to use Google pay on the watch it says Google pay on wear OS isn't available in my location yet even though iv Been using it on my phone for ages now so that's a bit rubbish as well although that might be because I live in Guernsey and it's still about twenty years behind the rest of the world here but anyway still for the price can't really complain to much it's a good little watch for the price one last thing if you buy this watch when your setting it up for the first time you may think it's slow and lagging but when you switch it on and start setting up for first time you'll get loads of updates and system updates so just be patient leave it plugged in to charge and wait and you'll be amazed how good the watch is after all the updates are properly finished because I know some people have switched it on and think it's broken or playing up but it's not it's just updating the system and apps.

Product: Ardell Duo Quick-Set Clear 5 g
Review: i decided to try duo after i heard that most professional MUAs use it, and i won't be going back to other brands. other glues, such as the eyelure lash adhesive have nothing on the strength of this. my lashes stick all day long. usually, they start to come away a little in the inner or outer corner after 3ish hours, but the duo glue keeps them in place all day. i would suggest using an oil based remover to take them off because it can be harsh on your lashes to just pull them off. the glue tends to stick a little in my lashes, so i spread vaseline with a spoolie through them at the end of the day and the glue comes right out. really good design, it doesn't clog and build up on the rim of the container. this is the best lash glue I've used. 10/10

Product: Ardell Duo Quick-Set Clear 5 g
Review: Compared to the duo glue in the squeezy tube, I much prefer this one. It definitely dries much quicker than others, which makes it easier to apply your lashes. I can't see much of a difference in how long my lashes stay on with this glue compared to the normal duo, but it definitely keeps them in place for a reasonable length of time! So far my favourite eyelash glue and I would definitely purchase again. The only thing I think might bother someone is the fact that the applicator is quite thick, however it doesn't really affect me too much as its still easy to apply the glue to the lashes.

Product: Ardell Duo Quick-Set Clear 5 g
Review: My friend who does my individual lashes recommended this brand to me. I have to say I was impressed. I was told.to wait until the adhesive became tacky and then attach lashes. The adhesive was easy to remove  from the lashes but did leave a small sticky residue on my eye lid, but this was easily removed.I found the applicator stick to be just the right size,so you can easily apply glue to the lash strip without too much mess.I would recommend  the adhesive to others, in fact my Mum has ordered some for herself. I am a prime member so I had next day delivery.

Specially if you are a latina mom that cooks rice every-single-day (cause if it's not rice, it's not food, amiright?). Those suckers always find their way -straight- into that crack! But not anymore with these! Not only they are easy to install, and kinda satisfying to cut, but they are amazing to clean! Pasta sauce? No problem. Sticky stuff? No problem... HOT OIL? NO-PROBLEMA! Too bad for them roaches wanting to reach MY kitchen for spills... no ma'am, not today! My kitchen is C L E AN all the way now! So find another home! Thank you ;)

Review: Ok... easy to clean NO, the silicone is actually sticky!! So even using a wet rag leaves crumbs and lint stuck to the surface. Heat Resistant definitely a  NO... I was using a cast iron pan and the heat coming off the pan (no physical contact was made) melted and charred the guard! Easy to install... yes you just lay it down. There’s nothing required to secure this in place, in turn causing it to continually be displaced and moved, bumped or pulled out of place with no effort or intent.

Review: This item looks like a piece of an old tire. I just had new countertops installed and bought this item after seeing how much food had fell between the stove and old counter tops. I put it flat on the counter for a day for it straighten out after being folded up in the package. The finish does look and feel like an old tire. It went in the garbage because I had cut it to length.

Review: I like this product very much. It is very easy to clean with a damp paper towel or disinfectant wipe. It has really helped keep crumbs and grease from falling between the gaps. The only thing I wish I that the piece that goes on between the stove and counter was made of a stiffer material so it could slide easier. If you look at my pictures, you will see the stove and counter were fit to size So there is t much room to get that middle piece in. If it were hard it would be easier to slide it. I hope that makes sense. But we really love it.

I had to cut a little off the end which was very easy to do. It isn’t a true dark black more of a matte black/deep grey. Even with the burners on high (electric) heat they did not get hot. They look very nice.  I highly recommend.

Review: I am so glad I found these. I hated having to move the whole stove all the time. Alot of crumbs accumulate through the gaps. Now I just wipe them away. These are so easy to install and clean. Easy to custom fit.  I had to cut one towards the back end to fit without lifting. I definitely recommend.Update..so I just realized I didn't have to cut the right side I had it backwards. Make sure the bigger side is facing away from the stove. Like in the last picture. I just flipped it and cant really tell that I made a cut.

This left the coverings not sitting flush which was very annoying and looked odd. Make sure the gap you’re trying to cover is wide enough for the wedge. These went in the bin. Bit of a waste of time and money :(

The top side is a nice matte finish, the bottom is a shiny rubbery finish that grips the surface. It's also easy to lift up the edge and wipe under it without removing it. Perfection!

Maybe a weighted one would be better or another material that actually does lay flat to fill the gaps and look nice.  The bulges where it doesn't lay flat make it look not attractive so takes away from the kitchen.

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review: I don’t normally leave reviews but I thought this may help other people in a similar situation. I’ve had a discoloured nail for at least 2 years and although many doctor trips and nail samples came back clear, it was obvious to me I had some form of nail infection. I tried lots of other treatments but nothing worked....until this product. During lockdown I’ve been working from home and so I haven’t had to wear shoes, paint my nails to cover the unsightly toes and it’s given me the chance to religiously treat the nails. I think I bought this product in April and the photo attached it from July. My large toe nails on both feet had a diagonal yellow colour going almost to the base of the nail but as you can see on this photo, it’s almost gone now. There’s just a small amount left on the top of the nail as it’s growing out. One bottle of this product has treated two large toe nails for a few months but you will have to buy more emery boards as you don’t get enough of those included. I’m going to continue using until all of the infection has disappeared and keep covering the whole nail as it seems to have done the trick!Give it a try but stick with it and do it every day!! I’m so much more confident about wearing sandals and I’m ready for summer!

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review:
So ive been using this for about 6-7 months now and have just bought my 3rd one. i had thick infected nails and as it stands my nails havnt completely cleared. however there is definitely a clear difference between when i started. i think the time it takes to clear depends on how bad your nails are.

i personally havnt been using the nail files provided with the product because it didnt make much of a difference with my nails, they wernt coarse enough. i think people with mild infections these will be fine. i found using and electric nail file i got weekly really helped take away the thickness of the nail and enabled the product to work better. you can use whatever works best for you.

if you stop using the product it starts to come back, where ive missed a week i can see my nails starting to darken. so this definitely needs to be maintained and your not going to get results over night. i am hoping this is the last one i will have to buy and that the nails will be completely clear by the time im done.

all in all good product does work but you have to main using it for a long period. in terms of the end result i cant tell you im not quite there yet. but if your struggling like i have been for years i would try it. use the electric nail file tip if you nail infection is bad. dont over do it so you have no nail left but it definitely helps you see results quicker.

all in all good product does work but you have to main using it for a long period. in terms of the end result i cant tell you im not quite there yet. but if your struggling like i have been for years i would try it. use the electric nail file tip if you nail infection is bad. dont over do it so you have no nail left but it definitely helps you see results quicker.

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review: If you're doing DIY and you get cross and kick a small coffee table, be aware that your big toenail might come off.  This is extremely painful yet very amusing for everyone else in the house.  When the new nail grows it might have a fungal infection (also very funny, apparently). Initially you'll hope that it will just grow out and get better on its own, but it won't.  So you buy this stuff from Amazon and diligently paint it onto your toenail every day and then every week, as instructed.  I hope it works for you but it didn't for me.  I will just have a horrible toenail for ever now, its my life. Even my GP laughed.

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review:
I am in my 4th week before moving on to the maintenance phase following some discolouration to my big toe nail similar to early fungal infection pictures - possible infection facilitated by toe nail crack/damage. The discolouration has gone now and just need to keep it in good shape with the weekly treatment til the damage grows out. That'll be a long haul.

The file dispenser is a spring loaded sliding gadget in the top of the product. I got the first file out OK. Not so the second. I had to resort to a pair of pliers to break the top off to extract the remaining files. Totally useless design. The files could just as well be loose in the packaging or in a simple envelope of something. Over-engineered or what? You could possibly injure yourself breaking the top off so maybe just buying simple disposable nail files on standby is a better idea.

The instructions do not say if you need to wash off/remove the daily varnish application before applying a new layer. I emailed Scholl and have had no response.

Note the product information does not declare an active ingredient or contain a sheet of side effects etc you'd expect of a pharmacological product. It must therefore be exempt. You are left with no idea what it is you are applying to your toenail. It could just be clear nail varnish for all you can gather.

So grumbles here - but at least it appears to be working for me so far.

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review: I first tried this product in the Summer of 2018 when I noticed my right toenail was yellow. However, after finishing the bottle I didn't see any results so I thought it would just go away on its own. But by the end of 2019 both of my big toenails were yellow so I decided to get another bottle and start again. I applied it at least once a day, often more. It says that you should reduce applications to once a week after the first four weeks but I just continued to apply most days. I also made sure to go barefoot/wear flip flops whenever I could, to ensure my toes/feet weren't damp. I have just noticed that my toes are basically back to normal and I am delighted! I ended using 2 bottles of the product, but will buy another one to have just in case.

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review: This really works but is not an over night remedy.  I used it on both feet every day for over a year.  All but one toe on the left foot were sorted.  Results on the right foot were mixed - all toe nails had some partial relief from fungus.  I have given my feet about a year's break and have been happy that the left foot has remained the same.  That being the case, I have been using this for a few months again to try and finally rid myself of this issue and am seeing, I believe, gradual results although some way off yet.

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review: I initially tried the product following their directions and i wasn't seeing any results after the end of the 5 weeks. I tried a more intense approach and bought myself a metal nail file and really scrubbed a layer of the nails surface off each week and used the varnish every day. The nail files they provided are a bit cheap and not very sturdy. I then extended the period of doing this until the nail went completely white where it used to have fungus under it (approx. 2-3 months). I then only started using the varnish 2-3 times a week and still filing occasionally. Eventually 7 months later i finally have a fungal free nail.

B/ My doctor said your not supposed to put the brush back in the liquid as it contaminates it when you slide it over a fungal infected nail, this defeats the purpose of it working properly and this could be the reason why so many people can't get it to stay away or actually work.

scrapping the nail with a shaver designed for toe fungal infections seems to work better than just using the nail file on its own shows some improvement but reverts back to being fungal infected because well this stuff doesn't work and your just giving away your money for no reason.

Started applying it every evening, following the instructions to the letter.Over two months later: no difference whatsoever.Two stars, not one, because it's so nicely disign.

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review: This product is fantastic. I have had 2 nail fungal on both of my big toe's & tried prescriptions and a few diffrent products with no luck. Althoug both my fungal nails were fully developed & this item is meant to only be used if it is mild or at the begininng i thought i'd give it a shot. Iv'e had both infections for nearly a year & know a few pepole who have had theirs longer and just live with it now & give up on treaments. I love flip flops so i am not going to be that person, i started off by fileing both nails every day & slowly cutting the nail sorter and shorter until i was physically unable to cut it off any more although slighly painful it was worth it. As soon as both nails were down to nothing all you could aee was the thick layer of the infection which i would file down & use this product every day for 2 weeks. I am now only 4 weeks in and my nails are growing back healthy as ever. I will countinue to apply the product every day until the nail is fully grown & there is no sign of infection. Really hope this review helps someone, i am so relived that iv'e managed to fix the problem when so many others suffer for years.

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review:
I've had really bad nail fungus for a long time -- decades. I keep treating it, with this product and with others, but it keeps coming back. Of the products I've tried -- and there have been many -- this one has been the least useless. That's not to say it's good -- it's just less worthless than all the other over-the-counter remedies.

Basically, this treatment causes the infected parts of the nail to degenerate, so they can be scraped or sanded away. When all the diseased nail is gone, and the nail-bed exposed, you can keep applying the medication (for months) until the new nail grows out. Hopefully, the new nail with be healthy, or at least healthier.

The product comes with five small sanding boards. Unless you're nail is only slightly affected, this won't be nearly enough. Fortunately, sanding boards are inexpensive.

There's no getting away from the fact that treating nail fungus needs really diligent attention for a long, long time. And, even when it looks like everything is fixed, it will probably come back eventually. Basically, when you've got nail fungus, keeping it under control will be a life-long task.

This product isn't marvellously effective, but nothing is.

Product: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment, 3.8 ml
Review: If you have a mild infection, then this product can help. But if you have a deep toenail infection like I did, then save your money. This is no substitute for terbinafine hydrochloride taken orally, but it's a lot easier to use and a lot friendlier on your liver! Don't expect miracles, even if you use it exactly as directed.

Product: Lakeland Induction Hob Protector Liner
Review: This is to replace the one I bought direct at the Lakeland shop in Peterborough.  I put a cast iron skillet onto my hob at full power to sear my sirloin steak but got distracted for  couple of minutes. When I returned the skillet was actually glowing red hot as if it had been in a blacksnith's forge.  Panic over I  found The  Lakeland Induction Hob Protector Liner had grey burnt patch the size of the skillet.  It had undoubtedly saved the  hob top from damage.  I washed the protector and the grey more or less vanished but the black coating has gone from the top surface of that area that area.  The damaged protector is still usable but I have bought a new one to assuage the beloveds anger.  I had no idea about the power of induction.  Lesson learned.

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review:
This is great stuff but it does take a bit of getting used to and I think you need to experiment to find what works. The first time I put it on dry hair when it arrived and I found it did very little even after using loads. The trick for me seems to be to use it after I’ve been in the shower, applying a decent amount to wet hair and then letting it dry naturally as close to the style I want as possible.

I find it gives my hair loads of texture and makes it look quite thick, it also gives it hold though not loads of hold like a clay or gel would.

A bottle for me seems to last just over a month and I use it quite heavily each day, I do agree with other reviewers that it’s slightly strange they don’t put more in the bottle.

Overall I really like this product!

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review:
I've been using this product for a few weeks now and I have been getting some pretty decent results with it.

I like to use this stuff on damp, towel dried hair. It's as easy as dusting it on and running through your hair until you get a style you like, then let it dry. I have quite thick hair that likes to curl when it gets to a certain length, this stuff seems to hold it quite well, sure it leaves the a few waves, but for me this stuff is my quick solution if I'm in a hurry, or for those days when I want a more natural look.

For me, the downside is the packaging.
The powder takes up roughly half of the space in the container, I would like to see them offer this product with more of the powder inside for a higher price or to just make the packaging smaller and cut out the waste.

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review: This is the best stuff I've found so far. Gives so much volume and a nice matt texture. Exactly what I was looking for.

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review: Bought some of this powder as I despise waxes/gels/mousses as they make my hair greasy and uncomfortable. Decided to try this product after seeing the ad on Instagram for it and it really does what the videos show (not a clue how as it feels just like baby powder). But there’s not grease, shine or nonsense. It’s textures and holds hair really nicely, of course because of its ‘light treatment’, I’ve topped off the hairdo with a couple licks of hairspray but it really gets that shape that you want. As a bonus, it rides of that greasy look after two or three days of not using shampoo (which gents, if you do use shampoo more than twice a week, you really shouldn’t). 5/5.Side note: I have dark, thick and straight hair, faded back and sides and about two hands worth of length on top.

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review: Just shake it into your hands, rub together and then into your hair and ...um....nothing really. It doesn’t add volume or thickness, it doesn’t hold or style, no extra control. If anything I’d say it just makes hair look lank and in need of a wash. And it’s not cheap. I got completely sucked in by the marketing.

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review:
I was excited to learn of this product as I like a matte, flexible product for my hair. My hair is the fine but lots of toilet-brush Far East style mousey mess...!

This stuff is tricky to apply, and does not hold my hair in the gentlest of breezes. Worse, after 15 mins, my hair actually looks worse than had I not applied any product at all.

It might work better for thicker-haired gentlemen, but alas this product is not for me. The search for a suitable hair product continues....

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review:
I bought this as I've been using water based pomade for some time and I really wanted something that would give a more natural looking style without a crazy amount of shine.

This does work really well on my hair which is very thick. It holds nice and firm and isn't greasy.

One problem is they give you a TINY TINY amount. The small tub they offer isn't even full it's not even half full. In terms of value for money it's a complete rip off. Imagine the hair product equivalent of a packet of walkers. It's mostly air.

No doubt the product works well though.

Review: So I've got to an age where I like to quiff my hair rather than mohawk, and was recommended this by a colleague. It's great stuff - dead easy to use, and simple to style. Also lasts ages as you don't need to use loads.

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review:
(For context, I spend lots of money on hair products. I buy different brands all the time and try most things going.)
You cannot compare this product to the pink V05 or purple Schwartzkopf hair powders. They are designed to give you all the volume with a bit of texture. This product is kind of the opposite to those. You will get some lift, but this is more about giving you fuller looking natural shine hair. I personally use one of the aforementioned powders first on dry hair, then whatever styling product I am using at the time then this product last for the finish.

The tube is maybe twice the size of the pink V05 one in the shop you may already be using so the fact its twice this price makes sense for me and I feel like I have got fair value for money.

Buy this product and keep it in your arsenal for when you are going out and want your hair to look and stay its best.

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review: This one beats the other hair powders for me. I have short thick coarse hair which I’m not always happy with BUT this gorilla hair powder manages to give my hair the right amount of volume and style without drying out my hair! It’s amazing! Other powders would dry out my hair and they would make it hard to run my fingers through it. Not Gorilla’s powder! Also it’s easy to wash out and not only that but even after I wash the product out it leaves my hair silky soft. Something I’ve never noticed my hair to be until using this product. It conditions my hair. I’d say its a great hair product for someone who has thick coarse hair like me.

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review:
Now there's two ways to apply this product, one is to dump it on your head and go from there.

The second is to pour the powder in your palms and run it through your hair.

Either way, some excess powder will come out of your hair and every time you inhale just a little. It feels like your lungs get clogged for a good hour or so and lost like 10 years of your life.

First time trying a powder hair product, it definitely works for short hair like mine and creates texture and volume, but I won't be using this in the future due to the inhalants making me feel like I have pneumonia.

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review: I saw the reviews were positive and negative so I went ahead and purchased this product to see if it would work. It was a fail !!!! the product added a tiny more volume than usual and it absolutely did not help with styling my hair. I had some hair that would not stay where I wanted it to. Therefore, I still had to use my clay product that I have used for so long to control and style my hair. Do not bother buying this product!!!

Product: Slick Gorilla Hair Styling Texturising Powder 20g
Review: This product works very well, just like any other hair texturizing powder. However, that isn't the problem. You get a 3-3.5 oz size plastic bottle with only 0.7 oz or powder in it. The bottle literally feels like its almost empty. With that said, there other other 1.0 oz hair texturing powders out there, for the same price, with a full bottle of powder. I would recommend buying those brands instead of "Slick Gorilla Hair" because they are price gouging. I will not be buying this again.

Review:
This has been purchased for overseas trips in the coming year and I've given it a nice long test drive and used it in the house for over a week, it has a very fast chill setting and it has not overheated despite being on for over a week, it comfortably holds 6 cans but I've opted just for four and maybe a couple of traveling chocolate snacks :)

It works just as well in the car as in the house and although I would not recommend usually leaving it on for such a long time it needed to be put fully through as many tests as possible and I am now looking forward to traveling in comfort with no need to spend a fortune at petrol stations across Europe.

Highly recommended mini-fridge that is lightweight and very effective.

Product: AstroAI Mini Fridge 4 Litre, 6 Can Portable Cooler and Warmer, AC/DC for Bedroom, Car, Office; Skincare, Makeup, Cosmetics, Food (White)
Review: My wife bought this little fridge for my study where I often end up sleeping with the dogs because I snore. I usually wake up very early and keep milk in this fridge to make a cup of tea when I first awaken, and also some water for the night. I expected the milk to be cool, but this little fridge actually keeps it cold. It fulfills its purpose for my needs perfectly and it represents value for money too .he downside is the noise of the fan, it’s probably on a par with a computer cooling fan, but I’m only ware of it when I am not using my CPAP machine, so it’s not really a problem as far as I’m concerned, but it may be an issue to consider for others. So, am I satisfied? Absolutely. Would I recommend the product to others? Asolutely.

Product: AstroAI Mini Fridge 4 Litre, 6 Can Portable Cooler and Warmer, AC/DC for Bedroom, Car, Office; Skincare, Makeup, Cosmetics, Food (White)
Review:
This is a remarkably decent little mini-fridge that’s capable of getting modest amounts of food or drink properly cold, and keeping it cold. The results are truly fridge temperature, almost-but-not-quite frozen, and for a refreshing drink portably, in the middle of nowhere (but still with access to a car lighter socket or a 3-pin plug), this really does the job it’s designed for.

Alternatively, it was a ‘warm’ function and that’s surprisingly impressive too. It’s not just lukewarm, it’s enough to keep a tub of food at proper eat-it-hot temperatures (it won’t warm food that’s cold, but food that’s already been warmed will stay that way). The circumstances where this would be useful do elude me to be honest, but in principle it’s a great option to have.

The sound level is fairly modest. One of the product photos is quite misleading and implies that four different volume levels can be selected, which isn’t true, at least not on the fridge I received, where the volume is only decided by whether it’s on or off. When on, it’s nowhere near silent, but it gives off a steady whirring sound that’s comparable in volume to a freestanding fan, or a slightly chuggy and unrefined desktop computer. It’s not a sound that I could sleep next to, but it’s not an annoying sound to work next to either. You only really notice it when the built-in thermostat keeps clicking it on and off. For outdoors use the sound should not annoy.

Obviously, it’s important you check the inner dimensions of this fridge to avoid disappointment. It’s fine for a few drinks cans, and will store some pots of food just about. I tried putting some takeaway containers in here and some fit, some didn’t. So make sure you know what it’s capable of storing before you buy.

The build quality and look of it is quite nice, I think. I’m not a fan of the branding on the front maybe, but the simple handle and soft curved style is quite sweet. Our kids have suggested we could stick googly eyes over the branding and make it into ‘Baby Fridge’. I think we’ll probably do that!

But if you’re happy with its capacity and you’re looking for a way to make food cold or keep food fresh, for a long car journey maybe or some camping adventure, then this is a decent and effective choice.

Review: Been a Zanusssi kitchen since forever. No more since we got the Bosch. Love it

Product: Bosch WTW85231GB Serie 4 Freestanding Heat Pump Tumble Dryer, 8kg load, White
Review: I replaced my 20-year- old top loader, and separate tumble drier, of a similar age, with a Bosch washer and this Series 6 Bosch, 8kg drier.We are retired, but apart from our own king-size bedlinen, we also often have family staying with double and single bedlinen to wash and dry.No problem with the old drier!!However, this drier does not have a reverse cycle, and I find that a large sheet just quickly rolls into a cylinder -  and when the cycle finishes, only the outer part of the "sausage" is dry and the inner part is still wet! if you have any other smaller items in the drier they are rolled into the middle of the "sausage" and stay wet!  Very frustrated at the waste of time and electricity - I find myself putting the oven timer on, and every ten minutes, running through to the laundry, to open the drier door, and take out the sheet, and give it a shake and put it back!! Time consuming and very annoying! Have decided to go back 40 years, to when we were first married, and if I could not get sheets out in the garden I dried them on an airer, in front of the fire, which I am doing again!! We have asked advice from Bosch and it was suggested we buy a net bag to fold and place the sheet in, and tie it up, before putting in the drier - does not work as the sensor says its dry but the inside of the inevitable "sausage" is still very wet!!

Product: Bosch WTW85231GB Serie 4 Freestanding Heat Pump Tumble Dryer, 8kg load, White
Review: Basically these need an ambient temperature of over 15 degrees ( doesn't say that in the manual)  .As the engineer told me , it may get to 61 degrees at the actual heat pump , but  in cold weather , you will struggle to feel the heat in the actual drum. We have had towels that have been in their for 6 hours that were still damp to the touch. no worries if you have the dryer indoors or if the weather isn't cold outside... but just beware..

Product: Russell Hobbs RHTTFZ1 31L Table Top F Energy Rating Freezer, White
Review:
Unfortunately my freezer was left laying outside next door despite the fact that I was at home and watching out for delivery.

I eventuality had to carry out a search to find the freezer. Very disappointed in Hermes delivery driver for not checking. I had to end up carrying it back to my house which wasn’t easy as it’s quite heavy.

The freezer is as described.
It’s compact. It’s very silent.
In fact I had to check a couple of times to see if it was working.
So far I am pleased with my purchase.

We have also had a problem with very rapid build up of frost, even though it's only opened once a day and isn't overfilled. It is serving is purpose but would not recommend for anything but emergency use.

Product: Subcold Super50 LED – Mini Fridge Black | 50L Beer, Wine & Drinks Fridge | LED Light + Lock & Key | Energy Efficient (Black)
Review:
I was searching for a minifridge for a while and I came across the subcold super 50. I've been using for a month now and I'm really impressed!
Pros:
The fridge is pretty quiet, I have it on the coldest setting and it only makes a noise for 2 minutes every 15 minutes or so, the noise itself isn't loud at all, sometimes I sleep next to it and I don't really notice it that much.
Fridge can get pretty cold, isn't as cold as advertised but I'd say it's around 5 degrees.
Fridge design is nice and stylish with an optional light and temp control.

Cons:
Temperature dial is at the back so annoying to get to.
Struggle with the top and middle shelf to fit normal size cans, it's a squeeze, literally needs a few mms.

Product: Subcold Super50 LED – Mini Fridge Black | 50L Beer, Wine & Drinks Fridge | LED Light + Lock & Key | Energy Efficient (Black)
Review: I looked for a nice little fridge for our home office during the lockdown, and looked at different models, but needed it to be able to hold much, without taking to much space, this was the only one I found to around 150, which could hold around 50l. It arrived quickly, and to be honest was bit bigger than I expected, but fit perfectly in, and can hold a lot - and have 5 different temperatures, we are using max, because we have filled the fridge as much as we can, its perfect for us, and is very good value.

Product: Subcold Super50 LED – Mini Fridge Black | 50L Beer, Wine & Drinks Fridge | LED Light + Lock & Key | Energy Efficient (Black)
Review:
Yes, it does what I want. It keeps items cold. Not actually using it as a drinks fridge, but to keep fruit and veg in. Works just fine.

I have the chill level set to 4 on the dial, and this keeps the temperature constant at around 3C or so.

Does it make too much noise when running? Not really, and it only runs for a couple of minutes anyway.

One thing to note that I didn't see anywhere in the product write-up (I may have missed it), but inside there is a switch to turn the internal light off. I didn't actually want the light running, and thought I would have to use some masking tape to cover it, but with the switch I can just turn it off.

Product: Subcold Super50 LED – Mini Fridge Black | 50L Beer, Wine & Drinks Fridge | LED Light + Lock & Key | Energy Efficient (Black)
Review: Bought a few of these, one for son going to Uni and one for my Man Cave. Both have performed great and kept a constant temperature in differing ambient conditions. The internal LED light is a great addition and makes the fridge look cool (pun intended).The fridge makes very little sound even in a quiet room. The lock is very useful and easy to operate and  comes with 2 keys.Brilliant fridge I would highly recommend.

Product: Subcold Super50 LED – Mini Fridge Black | 50L Beer, Wine & Drinks Fridge | LED Light + Lock & Key | Energy Efficient (Black)
Review: My bf absolutely loves this fridge and all the fab features for keeping his torps and other drinks cool at just the perfect temp. Only wish that it was a little bit quieter, of not being kept in the bedroom I can't recommend this enough but if looking for something to go in the bedroom, just be aware it might be not as quiet as you'd hoped. All in all great product and it's being moved into his man cave soon anyway so not a problem for us. 10 out of 10!

Product: Subcold Super50 LED – Mini Fridge Black | 50L Beer, Wine & Drinks Fridge | LED Light + Lock & Key | Energy Efficient (Black)
Review: I like everything about this fridge other than the shelf spacing. You cannot fit standard 330ml cans on the top shelf, it's about 1mm too short so only good for laying bottles on their side. You can fit standard 330ml cans in the middle shelf but only just, it's an extremely tight fit and there is a ridge in the middle of the top shelf which makes getting cans past this half way point difficult. There is loads of space at the bottom so I don't know why they haven't spaced these out a but better.Also the fridge is narrower at the back (internally), than at the front.

Product: Subcold Super50 LED – Mini Fridge Black | 50L Beer, Wine & Drinks Fridge | LED Light + Lock & Key | Energy Efficient (Black)
Review: Bought this for my bedroom and it fits nicely under my desk (did have to sit it on wood to keep it off the carpet). comfortably hold 6 2l bottles of Pepsi (front to back) having 3 on the top shelf and 3 in the middle shelf. The bottom section is good for any food, meds or eliquid that need to be kept cool as well. The light in the top isn't particularly bright but the door locking feature is nice. Will frost up at the back if turned too cold (had part of a Pepsi bottle freeze) but is fine when kept on a medium setting. Good purchase overall, very happy.

Product: Subcold Super50 LED – Mini Fridge Black | 50L Beer, Wine & Drinks Fridge | LED Light + Lock & Key | Energy Efficient (Black)
Review: Work amazing. Best purchase I've made in a long time and hoping to buy another soon for another room. Easy to lock aswell so our little one cant get into it. Not too noisy but does  randomly click on sometimes which can be annoying. It's not silent but definitely not loud.

Product: Subcold Super50 LED – Mini Fridge Black | 50L Beer, Wine & Drinks Fridge | LED Light + Lock & Key | Energy Efficient (Black)
