Review:
OK so firstly, it works and stays nice and cold. I can imagine that when it's active the noise may bother some people however I've got mine in the utility cupboard so that doesn't bother me. Basically, as a mini fridge, it's fine...

..however, the shelves..

Bottom shelf: Totally fine, using it to vertically store 440ml beer cans
Middle shelf: Will not hold cans stood vertically, especially if anything is on the top shelf. Unfortunately the shelves have a little flex so if you're storing something on the top shelf it encroaches on the space available on the middle shelf. If you're storing cans verically (think standard 330ml coke can) on the middle shelf they get completely squeezed between the shelves making them awkward to put in and get out. You can lie them down, but that's really bad use of space.
Top shelf: You can store cans upright in the middle of the top shelf due to the flex I mentioned earlier but if you try to store them near the edges the cans will get wedged between the shelf and the top.

However.... there is a solution - at least for the middle shelf. Turn the top shelf upside down. I found that by turning it upside down, it left just enough space to store cans vertically on the middle shelf. In this configuration, I can store 3 cans vertically and one laid on its side at the back of the fridge, and it seems to work quite well. This works for me as I use the top shelf for soft drink bottles anyway. Still, it's a shame that I had to resort to this.

Product: Aobosi Induction Hob,Double Induction Cooker,Portable Electric Induction Hob with Sensor Touch Control Black Crystal Glass Plate Multiple Power Levels and 10 Temperature Setting 4-Hour Timer 2800W
Review: UPDATE - Dear Olivia, thank you for your email 9th Sep 2020. I will not change my review just because you refunded me the money. This review tells exactly what happened. Although you make out it was so nice of you to refund my money, you are obliged to. Do not contact me again.Nice looking hob but broke second time I used it. Got E6 error constantly on either zone. Could only cook by powering off and on again every minute. Shame because it looked great. Book said to check pan was suitable but it was a Tefal induction pan I’ve used successfully for years on my other fitted induction hobs. Refund dealt with efficiently however.

Product: Aobosi Induction Hob,Double Induction Cooker,Portable Electric Induction Hob with Sensor Touch Control Black Crystal Glass Plate Multiple Power Levels and 10 Temperature Setting 4-Hour Timer 2800W
Review: Received on time opened and wow looked like a prop from star trek.Now I've had single hotplates infra red and solidbefore so I was expected some sort of redness to indicate it was heating up.Not with this item.Initially I thought it war broken but i left it and magically the water started to boil and in an acceptable time.There was no visible signs of heat (as with infrared) and no heat round the base).The heat seems to be directed directly into the pan.Now this heats up food /water very quicly and a you can control the temp easily.At a low level one click seems to take the the heat from visible simmer to off.Not so the heat is still ther and continues to cook.I tried this out on rice and it worked very well.I have not even used the higher level plate.I have found that if you experiment with the power level and temp level you will find your level of cooking.I bought this to replace a single hotplate I wasn't sure but now I'm glad I did So far a great purchase

Product: Aobosi Induction Hob,Double Induction Cooker,Portable Electric Induction Hob with Sensor Touch Control Black Crystal Glass Plate Multiple Power Levels and 10 Temperature Setting 4-Hour Timer 2800W
Review: I bought this hob on the basis that it would be suitable for use in the UK.  it came with a sealed 2 pin plug attached.  Although I could have cut the plug off and fitted a 13amp 3 pin plug, this may have voided the warranty and also caused problems should I not be satisfied with how it works.  I had no confidence in the product so I sent it back.  instead I bought one which came fitted with the correct plug.

Product: Aobosi Induction Hob,Double Induction Cooker,Portable Electric Induction Hob with Sensor Touch Control Black Crystal Glass Plate Multiple Power Levels and 10 Temperature Setting 4-Hour Timer 2800W
Review: Heats up quickly, and is definitely a money saver on electricity as it is efficient. The LED display is easy to use and provides wattage and/or centigrade settings and a timer to switch it off if you so wish. It displays an error sign if there is no pan on it and Willi switch off. Not a bad piece of kit. I will of course downgrade this review if it shows any signs of being faulty as I have only had it a few days and generally I don't review anything until I have had some use out of it, but this is a promising product

Product: Aobosi Induction Hob,Double Induction Cooker,Portable Electric Induction Hob with Sensor Touch Control Black Crystal Glass Plate Multiple Power Levels and 10 Temperature Setting 4-Hour Timer 2800W
Review: We were just in the process of furnishing a newly bought studio apartment, and I wanted to provide both, a good as well as a stylish option for our tenant, without breaking the bank. After using it myself for a few days, This dual induction hob does the job just well, it cuts normal cooking times in half and is very easy to maintain clean. The sensitive touch screen is a nice feature, allowing good heat control. The only thing that's perhaps a minus is the fact that the digital screen doesn't turn off, but displays Lo instead, would rather have the LED lights completely turned off when not in use, without the need to unplug it. Regardless, the hob itself does exactly what it's supposed to, without taking too much space and reaching high temperature quickly. Auto timer function is rather nice.We so much like it！

Review: The device overheats when searing a steak or deep frying. When you take off the pan it also beeps very loudly. Very annoying to use due to overheating and beeping. Okay for light tasks but not any serious cooking.

Product: Aobosi Induction Hob,Double Induction Cooker,Portable Electric Induction Hob with Sensor Touch Control Black Crystal Glass Plate Multiple Power Levels and 10 Temperature Setting 4-Hour Timer 2800W
Review:
I've been using it for a week now.
It works great.
Really really fast and easy to use.
Literally two seconds for oil to get hot, and a couple of minutes for a high quantity of water to boil (about 2-3 l)
Touch screen works perfectly.
The fan does make a little sound when on but nothing disturbing.
It is quite easy to clean.
Just follow the instructions and it will all be great.
It's perfect as you can move it and put it away if not needed, and it allows for more space in a small kitchen.

Product: Aobosi Induction Hob,Double Induction Cooker,Portable Electric Induction Hob with Sensor Touch Control Black Crystal Glass Plate Multiple Power Levels and 10 Temperature Setting 4-Hour Timer 2800W
Review: We bought this because our full size induction hob smashed and we didn't want anyone in the house removing or installing a new one during lockdown.  So this has been our only hob for 2 mlnths and it's been brilliant.  Only downside as others have mentioned is the fan is a little noisy but that honestly doesn't bother us.  It is, in effect, 2 single hobs in a double casing as there are independent controls for each separate ring.  The various heat settings are easy to use and respond immediately and the "keep warm" setting is a great idea.  Buy with confidence.

Review:

We are so glad we got this hob, it works perfectly and has been such a life saver! It is small and compact but still has two rings tops. It is also really stable and doesn’t slide everywhere because of its rubber feet.

Would be ideal for both indoor and outdoor use (as long as you have a power socket to plug it too). It also has a safety function where it beeps when the hob is on but no pan has been placed on the hob.

Would definitely recommend this product and we are glad we have it now in case of another emergency!
